<title>Arlington Small Business Development Center</title><H2>Arlington Small Business Development Center</H2>The Arlington Small Business Development Center (SBDC) provides free management and technical assistance to existing small businesses and new businesses. The SBDC has a full-time staff and the assistance of a large number of volunteer business professionals to provide business counseling in specialized areas.<p>The SBDC is sponsored by George Mason University, the U. S. Small Business Administration and the Virginia Department of Economic Development. The Center coordinates closely with the GMU Entrepreneurship Center in Fairfax and GMU's business school. <p>For more information, contact: <p><dl><dt>Arlington SBDC<dd>George Mason University<dd>Arlington Campus, Suite 322<dd>3401 N. Fairfax Dr.<dd>Arlington, VA  22201<dd>(703) 993-8128</dl><p>

