<Title>Public / Private Partnerships</title><h2>Public / Private Partnerships</h2><ul><li>Ballston Partnership<li>Clarendon Alliance<li>Columbia Pike Revitalization Organization<li>Rosslyn Renaissance</ul><p>These are four public/private partnership organizations in Arlington that help coordinate and promote the economic well being of their respective commercial sectors. The partnerships provide an excellent source for information and business contacts. Their goals are to:<p><ul><li>bring consensus to the planning and development process<li>help implement the approved plans for their area<li>market and promote the area to the development community, commercial tenants, and consumers</ul><p>They sponsor promotional activities, provide information, and meet frequently to work on common issues. Each organization is non-profit and includes business owners, residents, property owners, property developers and brokers, and area institutions in its membership. Funding comes from the private sector and Arlington County. To get more information, contact:<p><dl><dt>Ballston Partnership <dd>4301 N. Fairfax Dr., Suite 301, Arlington, VA 22203<dd>(703) 528-3527<p><dt>Clarendon Alliance<dd>3195 Wilson Blvd.<dd>Arlington, VA 22201<dd>(703) 276-0228<p><dt>Columbia Pike Revitalization Organization<dd>3717 Columbia Pike, Suite 209<dd>Arlington, VA  22204<dd>(703) 892-2776<p><dt>Rosslyn Renaissance<dd>1911 N. Fort Myer Dr.<dd>Arlington, VA 22209<dd>(703) 522-6628</dl><p>

