<title>Procurement Opportunities With Arlington County</title><H2>Procurement Opportunities With Arlington County</h2>Arlington County spends millions of dollars each year on goods and services, a large percentage of which is purchased from local businesses. Doing business with local government can be financially rewarding and can help a business obtain valuable market information. Local governments purchase virtually any commodity and service available in the community.<p><p>The Office of the Purchasing Agent processes and authorizes all purchases of the County except for the County School Board. The County encourages all small, women-owned, minority-owned, and other disadvantaged business owners to sell to the County government. Note, however, that Arlington County does not maintain a separate registration list for minority-owned contractors or use minority business set-asides. The County does not certify minority businesses.<p>The County publishes a brochure, "Vendor's Guide - How To Do Business with Arlington County." Call or write the office below to get a free copy.<p>In order to bid on Arlington County purchase requests, a business must register with the County's purchasing office. To register, receive the appropriate forms, receive a list of commodities, and obtain information on the procurement process, contact:<p><dl><dt>Office of the Purchasing Agent<dd>2100 Clarendon Blvd., Suite 500<dd>Arlington, VA  22201<dd>(703) 358-3410</dl><p>To bid on purchases made by Arlington County Public Schools, contact:<p><dl><dt>Purchasing Agent<dd>Arlington Public Schools<dd>1426 N. Quincy St.<dd>Arlington, VA  22207<dd>(703) 358-6123</dl><p>

