<title>Employee Training & Recruiting</title><H1>Employee Training & Recruiting</H1><dl><dt><b>ARLINGTON EMPLOYMENT CENTER</b><p><dd>This office provides an array of employment services to residents and businesses. The Center responds to employers' recruitment needs by providing a central place to list job vacancies and find qualified employees. It runs a job fair and periodic employment seminars. The Center also assists individuals with job referral, career counseling, skills training, testing and evaluation. For further information, contact:<p><dl><dt>Arlington Employment Center<dd>2050 N. 15th Street, Arlington, VA  22201<dd>(703) 358-4820</dl><p><dt><b>VIRGINIA EMPLOYMENT  COMMISSION</b><p><dd>A state agency, the VEC helps businesses find suitable employees for specific job openings. The VEC can recruit prospects through its statewide network of offices and provides testing services for specialized occupations. These services are free. Arlington businesses may contact either of two Job Service Offices:<p><dl><dt>Job Service Office<dd>5520 Cherokee Avenue, Alexandria, VA  22312<dd>(703) 823-4135<p><dt>or<p><dt>Job Service Office<dd>13135 Lee Jackson Highway, Suite 340 , Fairfax, VA  22033 <dd>(703) 803-1100</dl></dl><p>

