<title>VIRGINIA SQUARE</title><h1>Virginia Square</h1><img src="VASQ.gif"> Virginia Square, home to Arlington Central Library, George Mason University's Arlington Campus, the Arlington Arts Center and Quincy Park, is the cultural, recreational and educational center of the Rosslyn-Ballston Corridor.  In addition, the Virginia Square Sector Plan envisions the development of a high density residential core, limited office and retail development and preservation of surrounding single family areas.  This lively mix of uses will result in a stimulating neighborhood with easy access to the entertainment and shopping in the nearby Ballston and Clarendon areas.  <p>Recently completed or approved projects in Virginia Square offer a glimpse of the area's future.  The Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation training facility is an example of the high quality architecture and materials expected of new construction.  This project also included replacing a Giant grocery store with a new, expanded facility.  The Central Library renovation and expansion produced a state of the art facility able to offer a wide variety of services to both residential and business communities.  Ballston Square, formerly Pollard Gardens, will include a 140,000-square-foot office building and a total of 669 dwelling units in three buildings.  The first phase of the project, the Clarendon Court Apartments, is complete and contains 103 moderate income housing units.  Other approved site plans contain a total of 897 housing units and 597,000 square feet of office.<p>The current Virginia Square market is healthy with less than 7 % of the current 870,000 square feet of office vacant.  The retail sector, principally comprised of small restaurants and service businesses along with the Giant grocery mentioned earlier, is in even better shape with a vacancy rate of under 4 %.  The residential occupancy rate exceeds 95%.<p>
</DOC>
