<title>Ballston Tour</title><H1>Ballston Photo Tour</H1><img src="Ballston.gif"><p><hr><h4>INSTITUTIONAL NEIGHBORS</h4><hr>Ballston is home to a number of national, regional and local institutions which enrich the cultural and economic life of the area.  Libraries, science organizations and research centers are all located within a few blocks of each other creating a dynamic synergy.  Just as importantly, the support facilities such as hotel, conference facilities and auditoria are also either existing or under construction.<p><img src="Blstn1.gif"><i> Arlington Central Library: recently renovated, with an excellent business collection as well as general interest publications for employees' professional development and leisure time. </i> <p><img src="Blstn2.gif"><i> The National Science Foundation, in the heart of Ballston, provides technical leadership to the nation and will be a valuable resource to any business with scientific and research interests.</i><p><img src="Blstn3.gif"><i>Quincy Street Station is home to SAIC and other contractors with ARPA (the Advanced Research Projects Administration).  The building also houses the International Institute of George Mason University and the Center for European Community Studies.</i><p><img src="Blstn4.gif"><i>Marymount University's Ballston Campus, across the street from the NVGC site, houses the Business School and other programs.</i><p><p><hr><h4>CORPORATE NEIGHBORS</h4><hr>Major corporations, such as those shown here, play an active role in the Ballston community and are just steps away from central Ballston, as are other firms such as Systemhouse and Environ Corporation.  In addition, telecommunications giants like Bell Atlantic, MCI and Gannett Publishing are just a few Metro stops away.<p><img src="Blstn5.gif"> <img src="Blstn6.gif"><p><img src="Blstn7.gif"> <img src="Blstn8.gif"><p><p><hr><h4>YOUR NEW NEIGHBORHOOD</h4><hr>Within Ballston are a number of the corporations and institutions pictured on the preceding pages. Ballston's compact development pattern means that one is never more than a few minutes' walk from any of the area's businesses or amenities.<p><img src="Blstn9.gif"><i> Looking west from the corner of Glebe Road and Fairfax Drive.  Both projects shown have restaurants and support services such as dry cleaners and banks.  A Holiday Inn is located directly south of this corner.</i><p><img src="Blstn10.gif"><i> A view looking southeast from Fairfax Drive near Glebe Road. Among the tenants of the buildings shown are the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service and the Immigration and Naturalization Service.</i><p><img src="Blstn11.gif"><i> Looking east down Fairfax Drive from near Glebe Road.  The building with the rounded top is the Ellipse, home to the Environ Corporation and the Ellipse Art Gallery.  Beyond is the Ballston Metro Center, a mixed-use project which includes offices, condominiums, a variety of retail and restaurant establishments, and the 200 room Ramada Renaissance hotel, one of three hotels in Ballston. </i><p><img src="Blstn12.gif"><i> The Ballston Metro Station Entry.  This entry to the 103 mile Metro subway system is located at Fairfax Drive and Stuart Street in the center of Ballston.  </i><p><p><hr><h4>URBAN STYLE</h4><hr>Pictured on these pages are just a few of the outstanding examples of contemporary architecture in Ballston, including, at lower right, the Jefferson apartment building.  Because of the high quality of the planning which has shaped the area, Ballston is becoming nationally recognized as a leader in urban revitalization and development.<p><img src="Blstn13.gif"> <img src="Blstn14.gif"><p><img src="Blstn15.gif"> <img src="Blstn16.gif"><p><p><hr><h4>DINING OPPORTUNITIES</h4><hr>Ballston offers a wide variety of restaurants located throughout the area.  Diverse ethnic styles and price ranges appeal to every taste and budget whether the diner is on a student budget or that of a visiting corporate executive or foreign dignitary.  Ballston offers everything from unique sidewalk cafes and white table cloth restaurants to gourmet shops and fast food outlets. <p><img src="Blstn17.gif"> <img src="Blstn18.gif"><p><img src="Blstn19.gif"><p><p><hr><h4>SHOPPING OPPORTUNITIES</h4><hr>The 100+ shops of Ballston Common, shown here, are the heart of shopping in Ballston.  An attached public parking garage has inexpensive rates and monthly rates.  The mall's food court can provide quick meals.<p><img src="Blstn20.gif"> <img src="Blstn21.gif"> <img src="Blstn22.gif"><p>In addition to Ballston Common, a wide variety of shops and service businesses are located throughout the area.  These include a premier bookstore, dry cleaners, printers and banks, among others.<p><p><hr><h4>URBAN AMENITIES</h4><hr>Ballston's public art, tree lined sidewalks, decorative lighting, and fountains all bespeak the area's quality of life.  Devoted to creating an example of the best in urban development, Arlington County, the Ballston Partnership and area property owners consistently strive to enhance Ballston's public places.<p><img src="Blstn23.gif"> <img src="Blstn24.gif"> <p><img src="Blstn25.gif"> <img src="Blstn26.gif"> <p><p><hr><h4>A PLACE TO LIVE AS WELL AS WORK</H4><hr>Integral to the community's vision for Ballston is creation of a wide range of housing opportunities within or adjacent to the commercial core.  Shown here are some examples of nearby apartments that will appeal to mobile young professionals as well as to mature adults seeking an urban lifestyle.  Some of these properties also provide corporate apartments.  The Jefferson, pictured earlier, is targeted toward affluent retired people.  Other housing opportunities, including single family homes, moderate cost garden apartments and townhouses, are within easy walking distance of Ballston.  <p><img src="Blstn27.gif"> <img src="Blstn28.gif"> <img src="Blstn29.gif"> 
