<title>Clarendon</title><h1>Clarendon</h1><img src="claren.gif"> Clarendon is located in the geographic center of Arlington.  The area is the historic downtown of the county.  Access is provided by I-66, I-395, Route 50, Washington, Wilson and Clarendon Boulevards, Fairfax Drive and Metro.  Clarendon currently has some of the lowest retail and office vacancy rates in Arlington and is poised to take advantage of development opportunities in the 90's and beyond.<p>Clarendon offers a potential for almost two million square feet of office space, roughly 200,000 square feet of retail and over 100 residential units within two blocks of the Clarendon Metro Station.  These build-to-suit opportunities provide a wide range of design options which can accommodate the different needs of tenants such as associations, law firms and government agencies.  For those tenants looking for views and high-visibility buildings, Clarendon sits on a geographic high point in Arlington and the buildings offer exciting vistas of Washington DC and the region.  These are exciting opportunities to provide users with signature buildings on landmark sites in a solid business community.<p>Clarendon offers one of the best office locations in Arlington. Downtown Washington is only a five minute drive, the Pentagon is four minutes away and the rest of Northern Virginia is easily accessible.  Most major Arlington roads and the Metro Orange Line serve Clarendon.<p>The Clarendon Sector Plan calls for the community to be redeveloped under the "urban village" concept.  This includes retention and promotion of small businesses as well as for building design specifications.  Buildings are proposed to taper density and height to provide a smooth transition from the core office area to the residential neighborhoods.  In addition, the Clarendon Metro Park and 3100 Clarendon Boulevard serve as focal points of development and provide a sense of place.  The majority of development sites in Clarendon are z