<title>altarrow</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<p>Moving Text With &lt;Alt - [arrow]keys&gt;</p>

<p><a name="rt1"></a>You can move <a
href="definiti.htm#Paragraph">paragraphs</a> with in a document
with the following proceedure:</p>

<ol>
    <li>Place your cursor in the paragraph to be moved (or
        highlighting multiple paragraphs to be moved). </li>
    <li>Hold down the Alt key.</li>
    <li>Press the Arrow key (sometimes called &quot;Cursor
        Keys&quot;) that points in the direction you want the
        paragraph moved. Any paragraphs with auto - numbering
        (any of the Outline styles or NumList) will automatically
        renumber.</li>
</ol>

<p>Exercise:</p>

<p>Document Number 314987 is an excercise document that further
illustraits this trick.</p>

<p><a href="tips.htm">Return to Tips &amp; Tricks</a></p>
</body>
