<html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
<title>definitions</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<p>Definitions Page</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><a name="Paragraph">Paragraph</a> - For the purposes of this
discussion, a paragraph is anything between two returns.</p>

<p>examples:</p>

<p>¶</p>

<p>This is a paragraph because there is a return before and a
return after.¶</p>

<p>A paragraph does not need text to be a paragraph. Below is an
empty paragraph. It needs only two returns.¶</p>

<p>¶</p>

<p>How many paragraphs are there between the word
&quot;examples:&quot; and this question? </p>

<p>Click <a href="#There are three (3) paragraphs.">here</a> for
the answer. Click <a href="altarrow.htm#rt1">here</a> to return
to the Moving Text trick. Click <a href="tips.htm">here</a> to
return to Tips &amp; Tricks page</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Answers:</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><a name="There are three (3) paragraphs.">There are three (3)
paragraphs.</a></p>

<p><font color="#FF0080">examples:</font></p>

<p><font color="#FF0080">¶</font></p>

<p><font color="#400040">1. &gt;</font><font color="#FF0080">
This is a paragraph because there is a return before and a return
after.¶</font></p>

<p><font color="#400040">2. &gt;</font><font color="#FF0080">A
paragraph does not need text to be a paragraph. Below is an empty
paragraph. It needs only two returns.¶</font></p>

<p><font color="#400040">3. &gt;</font><font color="#FF0080">¶</font></p>

<p><a href="altarrow.htm#rt1">Return to Moving Paragraph Trick</a></p>

<p><a href="tips.htm">Return to Tips &amp; Tricks page</a></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
</body>
</html>
