<html><head><title>Steptoe & Johnson <font size=-1>LLP</font> Recruiting</head></title>
<h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson <font size=-1>LLP</font><p>Recruiting</h3>
<h2 align=center>Phoenix Office</h2>



 		Steptoe &amp; Johnson<B>
 </B>LLP's office in Phoenix, Arizona is both an integral part of the firm's national practice and the focal point for its expanding local and regional representations in Arizona and the Southwest.  Since opening in January, 1987, the Phoenix office has grown to twenty-five attorneys, and its practice has expanded significantly.<P>

<P>

		The Phoenix office has a broad-based practice, including business transactions, commercial and employment litigation, media and communications law, intellectual property, water rights and environmental law, and real estate development and finance.  Its work extends to other areas in which the firm also has a national reputation, such as government contracts law and sophisticated insurance coverage disputes.  In addition to Arizona matters, Phoenix office attorneys are involved in regional and national cases as well, often working closely with their Washington, DC office colleagues.<P>

<P>

		Steptoe &amp; Johnson <font size=-2>LLP</font> in Phoenix  is neither a free-standing branch operation nor merely an extension of the firm's original Washington, DC base.  The office manages its own representations and staffing requirements, but also is intimately involved in the work of the firm as a whole.  It is committed to maintaining the informal cooperative working relationships that characterize the Washington, DC office, and in particular promoting familiarity and collegiality between attorneys based in Phoenix and in Washington.<P>

<P>

		Associates joining the firm in Phoenix can expect to deal with a variety of transactional, counseling and litigation matters.  Given the office's relatively small size, associates have the opportunity to work on a wide range of matters and rapidly assume substantial responsibilities.  They have access to the firm's extensive research and in-house training resources, and receive detailed annual evaluations to assist them in understanding their strengths as well as areas that require additional attention.<P>

<P>

		Phoenix summer associates work on a variety of matters involving various aspects of the firm's practice.  We believe it is essential that the summer associate program provide a comprehensive exposure to the work of the firm as a whole and a thorough sense of what it is like to be a Steptoe &amp; Johnson <font size=-2>LLP</font> attorney.<P>

<P>

		We consider our hiring decisions -- both for associates and for summer associates -- critical to our ability to maintain both the practice and the practice environment to which we are committed.  We consequently seek applicants who have demonstrated excellence in the skills required by the practice of law and who have personal qualities and interests that broaden the firm as a whole.  The goal of the Phoenix office is to continue the firm's hiring of diverse, interesting individuals who are excellent lawyers as well.<P>

<P>

<P>

Spring 1996





