<center><STRONG>What's New . . .</STRONG></center>
<br>
<P><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/taxalert.htm">Daily Tax News Summary</a>
<hr>
<P><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sbw.htm">Legislation Limits Environmental Liability for Lenders and Trustees</a>: One of the last acts of the 104th Congress was to
 limit the environmental liability of lenders and trustees under the Comprehensive Environmental Response Compensation and
 Liability Act (CERCLA)  (frequently called Superfund).  The changes to the Superfund law are significant because they more clearly
 define the actions that lenders or trustees may undertake without risking CERCLA liability.  Courts have varied in their interpreta- tions of the activities that create CERCLA liability and the amendment provides increased certainty and uniformity.    

<P><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pest.htm">Pesticide Resource Center</a>:  <B><FONT size=+1>Welcome</B> </FONT>to the Steptoe &amp; Johnson LLP Pesticide Practice Resource Center.  We have included some information on our practice group, what we do, and recent publications.  We also have reproduced selected EPA documents important to practitioners in this area, and summarized others.  We hope you find the site helpful and interesting, and welcome your <I><a href="mailto:sgoldberg@steptoe.com">feedback</A>.</I> 

