<html><head><title>Steptoe & Johnson <font size=-1>LLP</font> Recruiting</head></title>
<h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson <font size=-1>LLP</font><p>Recruiting</h3>
<h2 align=center>Washington D.C. Office</h2>


 		Steptoe &amp; Johnson <font size=-2>LLP</font> is a Washington, D.C.-based law firm with an expanding office in Phoenix, Arizona and an affiliate in Moscow, Russia.  Although Steptoe is a diverse institution, with more than 200 attorneys from all regions of the country, its attorneys share a common firm culture that emphasizes two primary goals:  (1) the pursuit of excellence in the practice of law at the most challenging levels and (2) preservation of a cooperative, supportive atmosphere.<P>

<P>

		The distinctive characteristic of Steptoe's practice -- whether litigation, counseling or transactional -- is that it reflects the impact of policy and emerging economic, political and social trends on the law.  Steptoe &amp; Johnson <font size=-2>LLP</font> attorneys regularly appear as counsel in cases of substantial national or industry importance, and the firm is widely recognized as one of the nation's leading firms in a number of highly visible legal specialties.  The firm has an active appellate practice, including frequent appearances before the Supreme Court, and an extensive pro bono program.  Steptoe takes a strategic view toward expanding its practice.  We provide consulting services in international trade and have partners specializing in Eastern European trade, international communications and in representations involving privatization activities in Eastern Europe, Africa, and Latin and South America.<P>

<P>

		For administrative purposes, the firm's Washington-based practice is organized into eight broad management groups which include:  (1) energy, environment; (2) transportation; (3) transactions, including corporate, securities, financial services, real estate, intellectual property and East/West investment; (4) tax and ERISA; (5) international; (6) antitrust; (7) insurance, employment and commercial litigation; and (8) technology, contracts and crimes.  The firm is flexible about splits between groups and attempts to honor expressed preferences in practice group assignments.  Summer associates are not assigned to a group, but work on a variety of matters, usually of their choice, from all sections of the firm, including our active pro bono practice.<P>

<P>

		Associate training and development is a high priority for a firm that emphasizes the quality of its legal work.  We offer a comprehensive in-house training program covering legal writing, speaking, negotiation, trial advocacy and other lawyering skills.  We also have a written evaluation program to assist associates in understanding their strengths and weaknesses.<P>

<P>

		We want to work with interesting people who are outstanding lawyers.  If your goal is the same as ours -- the pursuit of excellence in the context of an informal, collegial atmosphere -- we invite your application.<p><p><p>
Spring 1996





