<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>CALVIN H. COBB, JR. BIOGRAPHY</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Calvin H. Cobb, Jr.</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Corporate and Securities</a></center></blockquote>


<P>Calvin Cobb has for many years rendered corporate advice to
numerous business corporations and non-profit organizations.
He has represented clients in a broad range of corporate and
securities transactions, including mergers and acquisitions and
public and private sales of securities.  He also frequently
serves as counsel in corporate and securities adversary
proceedings (trial and appellate litigation, arbitration, SEC
administrative), including, for example, hostile takeovers, proxy
contests, securities fraud, broker/dealer and investment company
compliance cases, and corporate reorganizations.</P>  <P>Mr. Cobb
occasionally serves as an arbitrator for the American Arbitration
Association and the Municipal Securities Regulation Board.  He is
a past national president, Navy League of the United States, and
is Chairman of its National Advisory Council. </P>

