<html><head><title>F. Michael Kail Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
F. Michael Kail</h2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/ferc.htm">Energy</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/antitrst.htm">Antitrust</a></center></blockquote>

<P>Since 1972, Mike Kail has worked on a variety of matters, including internal corporate investigations, an antitrust grand jury and various pieces of litigation, all of which shared the characteristics of unusual factual density.  His principal focus over these years has been on the petroleum industry.  He was
involved in a structural antitrust case, followed by the Trans Alaska Pipeline tariff proceedings and a "private" Department of Energy overcharge action.

<P>More recently, he has litigated a series of cases relating to the valuation of Alaska North Slope crude oil.  These cases, look at the administrative and superior court level, touched on everything from the nature of the foreign crude oil market to the valuation of tanker transportation to economic theories of
pricing.  In this connection, he has participated in three substantial settlement negotiations with Alaskan officials. 

<P>Because of the complex nature of his practice, Mr. Kail has become intimately familiar with the use of computers, and has helped design both litigation support systems and substantive data bases.

<P>Mr. Kail is the author of What Washington Said, Administration Rhetoric and the Viet Nam War: 1949-1969, published by Harper & Row in 1973.

<P><DIR><LI> Oxford University Certificate in Education, 1971
<LI> Yale University LL.B. 1970
<LI>Yale University B.A. magna cum laude, 1967</DIR>
