<html><head><title>Lawrence A. Katz Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
Lawrence A. Katz</h2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/emplyben.htm">Employment Law</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/labor.htm">Labor Relations</a> | Litigation</center></blockquote>

<blockquote><center>Resident in <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/phoenix.htm">Phoenix, Arizona Office</a></center></blockquote>




<P>With more than 25 years of experience in labor law, Larry Katz enjoys a very broad based practice, including labor relations, employment discrimination, and employment litigation.  Mr. Katz represents clients in federal and state courts in the Southwest at both the trial and appellate level, as well as in the U.S. Supreme Court.  

<P>Mr. Katz's practice involves the representation of employers facing wrongful discharge suits, employment-related tort and contract claims, sexual harassment and other discrimination claims, and proceedings before all pertinent state and federal agencies, such as EEOC, OFCCP, NLRB, OSHA, and
DOL.  He has successfully litigated several jury trials in which companies were sued by former employees.  Mr. Katz has also represented numerous employers in union organizational campaigns, and in unfair labor practice and other proceedings before the NLRB. 

<P>There is a substantial counseling and advice component to Mr.Katz's practice, and he has drafted employee handbooks and policies for numerous clients.  In addition, Mr. Katz is frequently called upon to protect companies from unfair competition, theft of trade secrets, and business disparagement, and he
advises his clients on the preparation and enforcement of no compete clauses and other restrictive covenants and on labor relations issues relevant to the change of ownership of a business.

<P>Mr. Katz represents such major clients as Motorola, Allied-Signal, Albertson's, Bull HN and Circle K in labor relations and employment law matters.  

<P>He is a member of the National Banking Industry Labor Law Committee and the Labor Lawyers Advisory Council to the National Association of Manufacturers. 

<P>Mr. Katz is a frequent lecturer and writer on matters of employment law.  He has lectured at numerous seminars sponsored by the State Bar of Arizona, the American Law Institute, the American Bar Association, and others.

<P><DIR><LI> Boston College Law School J.D., 1967 Order of the Coif, Editor-in-Chief, Boston College Law Review
<LI> Harvard University B.A., 1964</DIR><p><blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/phoenix.htm">Phoenix Office</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></center></body></html>
