<html><head><title>David L. Roll</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>David L. Roll</h2>
<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/antitrst.htm">Antitrust & Trade Regulation</a> | Administrative Law | <a href= "http://www.steptoe.com/ferc.htm">Energy</a></center></blockquote>
<hr>



<P>Dave Roll's practice emphasizes antitrust and trade regulation
litigation and counseling; civil jury trials; litigation
involving energy issues, particularly oil pricing; administrative
law and litigation; and practice before the Department of Energy.
</P>
<P>Mr. Roll has a broad antitrust background which includes treble
damage litigation, mergers, antitrust exemptions and the handling
of investigations and enforcement actions initiated by the
Antitrust Division of the Department of Justice and the Federal
Trade Commission.
</P>
<P>He has also challenged and defended federal regulations and
regulatory actions involving energy, banking, insurance, ocean
carriage and consumer credit in federal agencies as well as
federal district and appellate courts. </P>

<P>Mr. Roll served as Assistant Director, Bureau of Competition,
General Litigation, Federal Trade Commission, 1972-75.  He is on
the Council of the Antitrust Section of the American Bar Association and served as Chair of the Clayton Act Committee (mergers,
joint ventures and interlocks).  On behalf of the ABA, Mr. Roll
was author and editor of a book-length publication entitled:  The
FTC as an Antitrust Enforcement Agency:  Its Structure, Powers
and Procedures.</P>

<P></p><ul><LI>University of Michigan J.D. 1964<BR>
