<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Frederick S. Frei Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Frederick S. Frei</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intellip.htm">Patent Law</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/antitrst.htm">Antitrust Law</a></center></blockquote>
<P>

Frederick Frei specializes in the protection, licensing and enforcement of intellectual property,
with particular emphasis on patents and antitrust.  Mr. Frei contributes a broad range of
experience in the areas of patents, trademarks, copyrights and tradesecrets.  His legal
background and experience extends to business law, including antitrust and trade regulation
and business torts.

<P>Mr. Frei was a Patent Examiner at the United States Patent and Trademark Office from 1968
to 1973.  Following graduation from law school, Mr. Frei was a law clerk to the Honorable
Harry Phillips, Chief Judge, United States Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit.
<P>Mr. Frei has handled patent infringement litigation in diverse areas of technology, such as
motor vehicle coolant systems, solar cells, medical devices, road milling equipment, and
optical disc products and methods of manufacture.

<P>Mr. Frei has been a speaker on patent and litigation topics at the Judicial Conference of the
United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit, the American Intellectual Property
Law Association and other continuing legal education groups.  Currently, Mr. Frei is an
instructor for Patent Resources Group, Inc. in its Patent Bar Review course and its Advanced
Application and Amendment Workshop.
