<HTML> <HEAD><TITLE>Steptoe & Johnson LLP <i>Pesticides Resource Center</i></TITLE><body bgcolor="#FFFFFFF"><CENTER><IMG SRC="http://www.steptoe.com/logo63.gif" ALT="Steptoe & Johnson LLP Pesticides Regulation Update"></CENTER></HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFFF">


<P><B><FONT size=+1>Welcome</B> </FONT>to the Steptoe &amp; Johnson LLP Pesticide Practice Resource Center.  We have included some information on our practice group, what we do, and recent publications.  We also have reproduced selected EPA documents important to practitioners in this area, and summarized others.  We hope you find the site helpful and interesting, and welcome your <I><a href="mailto:sgoldberg@steptoe.com">feedback</A>.</I> <P>

<P>

<B>
<FONT size=+1>Steptoe &amp; Johnson LLP's pesticide practice</B></FONT> has worked continuously since the late 1970's on behalf of pesticide registrants and applicants.  Our work has concerned a broad range of antimicrobials, wood preservatives, agricultural pesticides (including soil treatments), biologicals and innovative technology-based pesticides.  Our work encompasses the full range of pesticide regulatory issues, including, e.g., registrations, data compensation, special review, reregistration, suspension and cancellation proceedings and enforcement (including GLP) defense, on federal and state (especially California) levels.  For more extensive information, please see our <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/envisup2.htm">
practice description.</a><P>

<P>

<B>
<FONT size=+1>The Key Professionals </B></FONT>in Steptoe's pesticide practice are Partner <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/goldberg.htm">Seth Goldberg</a>, who heads the group, Of Counsel <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/watson.htm">Sara Beth Watson</a> and Specialist <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/crescenz.htm">Sue Crescenzi</a>.  Each of us has many years of experience in this highly specialized regulatory field.  <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/fox.htm">Anita Fox</a>  handles our pesticide-related product liability litigation.  <P>

<P>

The Group publishes a <B><font size=+1>Newsletter</font></B> on pesticide regulatory issues of interest to our clients approximately six times a year.  The <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/291162.htm">most recent issue</a> and several articles from <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/293117.htm">back issues</a>  are available on this site.  If you would like to be included on the mailing list for the newsletter, please fill out a <I><a href="mailto:sgoldberg@steptoe.com">mailing list request</A>.</I> <P>

<P>

One issue in working on pesticide regulation is that much of the critical <B>EPA guidance material</B> is not generally available.  PR Notices have not been readily accessible and EPA has many internal documents that function as regulations, but are never publicly issued.  To help address this situation, we have included the full text of some EPA documents, and summaries of others on our site.  We hope to add additional documents and categories over time.<P>

<P>

Selected<FONT size=+1><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pubtoc.htm #pr">
PR Notices</a></FONT> from 1993 forward are available here in full text.  This is not the entire set, but includes the most recent ones and those we frequently refer to.<P>

<P>

Summaries of <FONT size=+1><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pubtoc.htm #pcn">EPA Policy and Criteria Documents </a></FONT> that generally were issued before PR Notices became widely used at EPA are available here.  You can request hard copies of each complete document as well.<P>

<P>Links to Other Sites Concerning Pesticides:<P>

<P><ul><li><a href="http://www.epa.gov/PestToxics.html">EPA OPPTS</a><P>
<li><a href="http://www.vtpp.ext.vt.edu/homepage.html">Virginia Tech. Pesticide Program</a><P>
<li><a href="http://www.cdpr.ca.gov/index.htm">California Department of Pesticide Regulation</a><P>
<li><a href="http://www.acpa.org/">American Crop Protection Association</a></ul><P>

Thanks very much for visiting our site.  We hope you found it helpful, and would very much appreciate your <I><a href="mailto:sgoldberg@steptoe.com">feedback</A>.</I><P>
<hr>

