<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Jerald .S Howe, Jr. Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Jerald S. Howe, Jr.</H2>

<blockquote><center>Space Law and Transactions</center></blockquote>



<P>Jerry Howe leads Steptoe & Johnson LLP's commercial space practice.  He has been extensively involved in strategic/legal planning for space infrastructure transactions; in drafting and negotiation of
a number of government and private agreements relating to the commercial development of outer space; and providing compliance related advice in a number of fields relevant to commercial space ventures.  These matters have involved space platforms, launch vehicles, communications satellites, and microgravity scienceprojects.

<P>This practice has also extended to providing international trade advice with respect to space commerce, and advice and representation regarding export controls and other aspects of
international space-related transactions.

<P>Mr. Howe's commercial space practice is complemented by an extensive practice in procurement law, primarily for clients engaged in aerospace, electronics, and other high-technology contracting.  This practice has involved him in matters of procurement integrity and government ethics requirements,
procurement costing and pricing, contract interpretation and administration, liability and indemnification, trade secrets and data rights and information law, and corporate acquisition projects involving government contracts.

<P>Before coming to Steptoe & Johnson LLP in 1984, Mr. Howe served for a year as judicial clerk to Judge George E. MacKinnon of the United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit.  He
is the immediate past President of the Federal Circuit Bar Association and chairs that Association's Judicial Selection Committee, participates as an active member of the Public Contract Law Section of the American Bar Association, and serves on the Board of the Washington Space Business Roundtable.

<P><DIR><LI> Harvard Law School J.D. cum laude, 1983 Editor, Harvard Law Review
<LI> Oxford University M.A. 1980; Sachs Scholar
