<html><head><title>John E. Nolan, Jr.</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>John E. Nolan, Jr.</h2>
<blockquote><center>Litigation</center></blockquote>
<hr>


<P>John Nolan has been counsel in cases involving the pharmaceutical
and insurance industries and the environment, including the Trans
Alaska Pipeline, automobile emission standards, federal subsidies
for supertankers and development of coal fields in the West.  He
is also experienced in cases involving federal regulation of
business and civil rights litigation.</P>

<P>In recent years representing insurance companies, he has
successfully argued before the Supreme Court of the United States
in cases involving punitive damages and preemption under ERISA. 
Earlier, he represented Pentagon whistleblower Ernest Fitzgerald
in two Supreme Court cases that defined the scope of official
immunity.
</P>
<P>Upon graduation from law school, Mr.Nolan was law clerk to
Justice Tom C. Clark, the Supreme Court of the United States.  He
was Administrative Assistant to Attorney General Robert F.
Kennedy, Department of Justice, 1963-64.
</P>
<P>He has served as counsel to the Robert F. Kennedy Memorial since
1968, and has been active in Democratic presidential campaigns. 
He is on the Executive Committee, National Lawyers' Committee for
Civil Rights Under Law and served as Chair of the Washington
Lawyers' Committee in 1968-69.</P>

<P>He is a director of Hooper Holmes, Inc. and Iomega Corp.  Since
1980, he has been a Moderator, Aspen Institute for Humanistic
Studies and, in 1987 and 1992, was a Visiting Fellow
at Wolfson College, Cambridge University, England.  He also is a
member of the Board of Visitors, Georgetown University Law
Center.
</P>
