<html><head><title>Roger E. Warin Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>Roger E. Warin</h2>
<blockquote><center>General Litigation | Malpractice Litigation | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Securities Litigation</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/insuranc.htm">Insurance Law</a> | Federal Election Law</center></blockquote>
<hr>


<P>Roger Warin handles a wide range of litigation.  His cases have
involved securities, RICO, libel, trademark, products liability,
directors' and officers' liability, voting rights, employment
discrimination, attorneys' fees, First Amendment, professional
liability, negligence, real estate, surety, construction,
environmental, toxic tort and insurance coverage claims.  In
recent years, he has been involved in numerous major nationwide
insurance coverage disputes involving asbestos, toxic substances
and environmental claims.  He is also currently defending law
firms in national securities class actions arising out of bond
offerings.
</P>
<P>Mr. Warin has served as counsel to a number of corporations,
individuals, candidates and political campaigns on matters
involving federal and state election laws and federal lobbying
laws.</P>
<P>
Mr. Warin is a frequent lecturer and author on insurance and
reinsurance coverage disputes, legal malpractice claims,
attorneys' fees litigation, and federal election law issues.
</P>
<P>Mr. Warin was law clerk to Judge Oliver Gasch, U.S. District
Court for the District of Columbia, 1970-71.  He was an Adjunct
Professor of Insurance Law, The American University Law School,
1978-81.</P>

