<html><head><title>Monroe Leigh Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
Monroe Leigh</h2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltran.htm">International Law</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade</a> | Administrative Law 
</center></blockquote>



<P>Monroe Leigh practices primarily in the area of international law and international trade.  He has served in various capacities with the United States Government, most recently as the Legal Adviser of the Department of State, 1975-77.  From 1975-80 he was one of the United States members of the Permanent Court of Arbitration.  He is on the advisory boards of the Procedural Aspects of International Law Institute; the Parker School of Foreign Law, Columbia University; and the International and Comparative Law Center, The Southwestern Legal Foundation.  From 1964 to 1988 he was on the faculty of the University of Virginia Law School as Lecturer on legal problems of international trade.

<P>Mr. Leigh served on the Advisory Committee of the American Law Institute's Restatement of the Foreign Relations Law of the United States.  He was Chair of the International Law Association's Committee on State Immunity, which prepared the Montreal and Buenos Aires Draft Conventions on State Immunity.  He was President of the American Society of International Law, 1980-82, and is a member of the Council of Foreign Relations, the Washington Institute of Foreign Affairs.  Mr. Leigh served as
Editor of the Judicial Decisions section of the American Journal of International Law, 1981-88.

<P><DIR><LI>University of Virginia LL.B. 1947 Editor-in-Chief, Virginia Law Review
<LI>Hampden-Sydney College A.B. 1940</DIR><p><blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></center></body></html>
