<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>THOMAS M. BARBA BIOGRAPHY</TITLE></HEAD>
 <BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Thomas M. Barba</h2>


<blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/apellate.htm">Civil Litigation</a> |
<a href="http://www.steptoe.com/govtcont.htm">Government Contracts</a></CENTER></blockquote>

<P>Tom Barba has been of counsel to Steptoe & Johnson LLP since May of
1991 and has been with the firm since 1988.  His practice
involves civil litigation, primarily in the areas of government
contracts and products liability.  Mr. Barba has extensive
experience in litigation and counseling in the area of government
contracts.  He has litigated cases on behalf of government
contractors in the federal district and appellate courts as well
as the boards of contract appeals, the General Accounting Office,
the Small Business Administration Office of Hearings and Appeals
and the U.S. Department of Labor.  Mr. Barba has also
participated in defending several complex federal white collar
criminal investigations in the government contracts area.</P>  Prior
to arriving at Steptoe & Johnson LLP, Mr. Barba served at the U.S.
Department of Justice, most recently as Deputy Assistant
Attorney General for the Civil Division.</P>  <P>While a trial lawyer
in the Justice Department's Civil Division from 1982 to 1986, Mr.
Barba conducted civil litigation on behalf of the government in
federal courts around the country.  He also served as chief of
staff to the Assistant Attorney General for the Civil Division
and in this position advised on the government's positions in
various significant cases.</P> <P>Upon departing the Justice Department
in 1988, Mr. Barba was awarded the Department's Distinguished
Service Award by the Deputy Attorney General.</P>

<P></p><DIR><L1>Temple University J.D. 1979<BR>
