Pipelines Committee of the Public Utility, Communications and Transportation Law Section of the American
Bar Association.  He is also a past member of the Executive Committee and Chair of the Oil Pipelines
Committee of the Federal Energy Bar Association, and has served on the Editorial Board of the Energy Law
Journal.  He has testified as an expert witness and has spoken frequently on oil pipeline and natural gas
issues at bar association meetings and industry seminars.</P>  <P>Mr. Brose was law clerk to Judge William H.
Timbers, U.S. Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit, 1972-73. </P>

