<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Stuart T. Huang Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Stuart T. Huang</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intellip.htm">Patent Law</a> | Trademarks | Trade Secrets</center></blockquote>




<P>Stuart Huang's practice areas include patent prosecution and litigation specializing in electrical arts and aerospace engineering.  Mr. Huang's experience includes all phases of practice before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office, counseling on corporate patent acquisition strategy, and evaluation of
patents relating to a variety of technologies, including spread spectrum radio navigation and communication, digital signal processing, neural networks, computer system architecture, data
encryption, optical discs, non-boolean digital logic, and the manufacture of semiconductor devices.

<P>After receiving his Bachelor of Engineering Science degree from The Johns Hopkins University, Mr. Huang joined the Pratt & Whitney Aircraft Group of United Technologies where he engaged in
research and development of military jet engines, including design of electronic engine controls, engine performance analysis, flight test analysis, computer simulation, and development of computerized test facilities for emulated altitude testing.  Mr. Huang next served as a design engineer at Fairchild
Industries Space and Electronics Company, where he designed avionics and communications equipment, and was part of a management team designing a time division multiple access satellite communication system for telemetry, tracking and control of military space vehicles.

<P>While at Fairchild, Mr. Huang earned his Masters Degree in Electrical Engineering from the University of Maryland with research related to the propagation of digital timing jitter through sequentially-traversed communication satellites.


<p></p><dir><li> The American University Washington College of Law  J.D. cum laude, 1989

<li> The University of Maryland M.S.E.E., 1986 Electrical Engineering

