<html><head><title>Walter H. White, Jr. Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP<br>Steptoe & Johnson Company</h3><h2 align=center>Walter H. White, Jr.</h2>
<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade Law</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/cistrade.htm">CIS Practice</a></center></blockquote>
<hr>





<P>Walter H. White, Jr. is a partner in Steptoe & Johnson LLP and Managing Director of Steptoe &
Johnson International, in Moscow, where his work consists of multinational securities transactions and international business law issues.  Mr. White has represented clients in major business transactions in the U.S., Canada, Europe, throughout the C.I.S., and South Africa.  He has also advised governments of the C.I.S. on economic development issues and legislation.  

<P>Mr. White served as Commissioner of Securities for the State of Wisconsin from February 1988 until January 1991.  

<P>Mr. White serves by Presidential appointment on the Board of the Central Asian-American Enterprise Fund and also is a member of the Council on Foreign Relations in New York, New York.  In the North American Securities Administrators Association, he has served as Chair of the International Corporation Finance Committee, and as Vice Chair of its Corporation Finance Section.  He was a member of the SEC Task Force on the U.S. Canadian Multi-Jurisdictional Disclosure System.  He has also acted as U.S. Presidential Delegate to the Association Internationale Des Jeunes Avocats, Brussels, Belgium; Chair-elect of the Section on International Law of the State Bar of Wisconsin; Director of the Wisconsin Trust Account
Foundation, Inc. and a Trustee of the Milwaukee Foundation.  Mr. White is a former President of the Milwaukee Urban League and currently serves as a Director of Church Mutual Life Insurance Company of Merrill, Wisconsin.

<P>Mr. White has been an active member in the American Bar Association where he served as a member of the House of Delegates, on the Special Advisory Committee on International Activities, Chair of the C.I.S. Law Committee of the International Law Section, Chair of the Young Lawyers Division, Executive Council liaison to the Business Law Section, and currently as a member of the Executive Council of the Individual Rights and Responsibilities Section. 

<P>Mr. White has published books and articles on multinational business activity and lectured extensively in North America, Europe, Central Asia and Africa.

<blockquote>Boalt Hall School of Law, University of California, Berkeley  J.D. 1980<br>

Amherst College B.A. 1977, Russian Studies Political Science<br>

Leningrad Pedagogical Institute Certificate in Russian Studies 1975</blockquote>

