<P>Danny Sauls has a broad ranging litigation practice focusing on
insurance law, construction litigation and other commercial
litigation.  He represents several major casualty insurance
carriers in insurance coverage disputes relating to asbestos,
environmental and professional liability claims.  He also handles
large construction claims throughout the country, bid protests,
and related matters in the government contracts area.  His
previous experience includes representation of a number of
corporations in employment and commercial litigation.</P>

<P>Mr. Sauls is a member of the American Bar Association and the
Litigation Section of the ABA.  He clerked for the Honorable
Collins J. Seitz, Chief Judge, United States Court of Appeals for
the Third Circuit, 1979-80.
</P>
<P><ul><LI>University of Virginia J.D. 1979 Editor, Virginia Law Review Order of the Coif<br>
<LI>University of Virginia B.A. highest distinction, 1976 Phi Beta Kappa</DIR>
