<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Stewart A. Baker Bio</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Stewart A. Baker</H2>
<blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/technolo.htm">Technology</a> |
<a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intlarbt.htm">International Arbitration</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade</a> | 
<a href="http://www.steptoe.com/apellate.htm">Appellate Litigation</a></CENTER></blockquote>

<P>Stewart Baker's practice covers international arbitration,
international trade and appellate litigation. Mr. Baker, former
General Counsel of the National Security Agency, has a technology
practice that focuses broadly on the interaction of law and policy
with changes in computer and telecommunications technology.  He has
advised clients and the U.S. government on such topics
as <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pubtoc.htm #net">encryption</a>, digital commerce, U.S. export controls, foreign
government controls, and wiretapping and electronic surveillance
(including the requirement of the 1994 digital telephony bill). 
Mr. Baker's international practice includes export controls and
other aspects of U.S. international law.</P>  <P>In addition, he has
handled numerous international trade matters, including successful
cases under the antidumping and countervailing duty laws of the
United States, European Community and Australia (for both importing
and domestic industries).  In the field of international
alternative dispute resolution, he has handled the arbitration of
claims exceeding one billion dollars and is a member of national
and international rosters of arbitrators, as well as the author of
articles and a book on the UNCITRAL arbitration rules.</P>  <P>Mr. Baker
has been asked to testify before Senate and House committees on
issues relating to international trade, foreign affairs and
appellate jurisdiction.  He has also served on the advisory council
for a congressionally sponsored study of international
pharmaceutical labeling.</P> <P>In addition to having filed many Supreme
Court and appellate  briefs, Mr. Baker founded the State and Local
Legal Center, which represents state and local governments before
the Court; he is currently Chair of the Center's Advisory Board. 
His writings on appellate and constitutional issues have been cited
in opinions of the Supreme Court of the United States.</P> <P>Mr. Baker
was a law clerk to Associate Justice John Paul Stevens of the
Supreme Court of the United States, as well as to Judge Frank
Coffin, U.S. Court of Appeals for the First Circuit and (during law
school) Judge Shirley Hufstedler, U.S. Court of Appeals for the
Ninth Circuit.</P>

<p></p><DIR><L1>University of California, Los Angeles J.D. 1976<BR>
<L1>Brown University A.B. 1970</DIR><p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pubtoc.htm">Publications</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/partners.htm">Partner Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
