<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Douglas G. Green Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Douglas G. Green</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/elecpwer.htm">Energy</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/antitrst.htm">Antitrust and Trade Regulation</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/apellate.htm">Litigation</a></center></blockquote>

<P>Doug Green's practice encompasses antitrust, electric power industry restructuring, commercial and nuclear litigation, and matters before the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. In 1992-93, Mr. Green was lead trial counsel for Entergy Services, Inc. in FERC proceedings associated with its $2.3 billion acquisition of Gulf States Utilities Company.  He represents Entergy and a number of electric utility companies on restructuring matters.  These representations involve counseling and litigation on regulatory and antitrust issues related to the evolution of the electric power industry.
<P>In addition to administrative proceedings at the state and federal level, Mr. Green's antitrust
practice includes treble damages litigation, and the handling of merger investigations by the Department of Justice.  Mr. Green also handles complex commercial litigation in the energy area.  He was lead trial counsel for plaintiff Public Service Electric and Gas Company in its breach of contract and tort suit over the
shutdown of the Peach Bottom nuclear power plant.  The case was settled in 1992, after an Alternative Dispute Resolution mini-trial, for $131.985 million.
<P>From 1981-1985 Mr. Green represented Houston Lighting & Power Company in litigation with Brown & Root, Inc. and the Halliburton Company over the design and construction of the South Texas Nuclear Project.  Mr. Green led a team of lawyers from several law firms in developing plaintiffs' case on the engineering issues.  The case was settled in 1985 for $750 million.
<P><DIR><LI> Georgetown University Law Center J.D. 1973 Editor, Georgetown Law Journal
<LI> University of Virginia M.A., English, 1969
<LI>Bowdoin College B.A., cum laude, 1968</DIR>
<p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
