<HTML> <HEAD><TITLE>Edict of the President of the Russian
</TITLE></HEAD><body><h3 align=center>Edict of the President of
the Russian Federation <I>On Measures to Observe the Law in
Development, Production, Sale and Use of Encrypting
Information</I></h3>
 <P>For the purpose of securing unconditional
implementation of the Russian Federation Law "On the Federal
Organs of Government Telecommunications and Information," as
well as with the view to intensify combat against organized
crime and improving protection of the government systems of
information and telecommunications, Russian credit and financial
institutional, enterprises and organizations, I hereby
decree:<P>
<OL><LI>Grant the status of Presidential Program
to the Program on creation and development of special purpose
information and telecommunications system for the organs of
state power.  The Center for the Presidential Programs of the
Administration of the Russian Federation President in
conjunction with the Federal Agency of Government
Telecommunications and Information attached to the Russian
Federation President's Office is to ensure completion and
realization of the program.<P>
<LI>Prohibit state
organizations and enterprises from using in their information
and telecommunications systems encryption devices, including
cryptographic devices for providing authenticity of the
information (electronic signature), as well as protected
technological means for storing, processing and transmitting
information which do not have a certificate of the Federal
Agency of Government Telecommunications and Information attached
to the Russian Federation President's Office.  Forbid grants of
government contracts to enterprises and organizations using the
technological and encryption devices, which do not have a
certificate of the Federal Agency of Government
Telecommunications and Information attached to the Russian
Federation President's Office.<P>
<LI>The Central Bank
of the Russian and the Federal Agency of Government
Telecommunications and Information attached to the Russian
Federation President's Office are advised to take necessary
measures with regard to those commercial banks of the Russian
Federation which in the course of exchanging information with
divisions of the Russian Federation Central Bank are evading the
requirement to use protected technological devices for storing,
processing and transmitting information, which have a
certificate of the Federal Agency of Government
Telecommunications and Information attached to the Russian
Federation President's Office.<P>
<LI>In the interests
of informational security of the Russian Federation and of the
intensification of combat against organized crime to ban the
activities of legal entities and natural persons connected to
the development, production, sale and use of encryption devices,
as well as protected technological means for storing, processing
and transmitting information; or providing services in
encrypting information without licenses issued by the Federal
Agency of Government Telecommunications and Information attached
to the Russian Federation President's Office in accordance with
the Russian Federation Law "On the Federal Organs of Government
Telecommunications and Information."<P>
<LI>The Russian
Federation State Customs Committee is to take measures in order
to prevent import of encryption devices manufactured abroad into
the Russian Federation territory without a license of the
Russian Federation Ministry of Foreign Economic Relations,
issued after consultation with the Federal Agency of Government
Telecommunications and Information attached to the Russian
Federation President's Office.<P>
<LI>The Russian
Federation Federal Counterintelligence Service and the Russian
Federation Internal Affairs Ministry in conjunction with the
Federal Agency of Government Telecommuni- cations and
Information attached to the Russian Federation President's
Office, the Russian Federation State Fiscal Service and the
Russian Federation Tax Police Department is to elicit entities
and natural persons violating requirements of the present
Edict.<P>
<LI>7.  The Office of the Russian Federation
Prosecutor-General is advised to intensify a prosecutorial
supervision over the compliance with the Russian Federation Law
"On the Federal Organs of Government Telecommunications and
Information" with regard to the development, production, sale
and use of the encryption devices, as well as with respect to
the provision of services in encrypting information in the
Russian Federation, which are subject to licensing and
certification by the Federal Agency of Government
Telecommunications and Information attached to the Russian
Federation President's Office.<P>
<LI>Create the Federal
Center for the Protection of Commercial Information adjoined to
the Federal Agency of Government Telecommunications and
Information attached to the Russian Federation President's
Office (within the limits of the staff of this Agency) in charge
of the development and implementation of complex programs of
providing security of the economic information of Russian
credit, financial and other economically important institutions
of the country.</P> 

<P>The Director General of the Federal
Agency of Government Telecommunications and Information attached
to the Russian Federation President's Office is to adopt Bylaws
of this Center within two months period.<P>
<LI>The Edict
becomes effective on the date of its publication.</ol>

<P>President of the Russian Federation B. Eltsin Moscow, The
Kremlin

<P><I>April 1995, No. 334</I>

<P><blockquote><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/cyber.htm"><I>Issues About Cyberspace </I>Memo</A> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pubtoc.htm">Publications</A> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</A> | <A
HREF="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</A></center></blockquote></body>
</HTML> 
</DOC>
