<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>SARAH C. CAREY BIOGRAPHY</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Sarah C. Carey</H2>

<blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Corporate</a></CENTER></H4>

<P>Sarah Carey specializes in trade and investment in the countries of the former Soviet
Union.  She provides trade consulting and legal services to a broad range of U.S. and
other OECD companies, both agricultural and industrial, that are involved in these
markets.  Ms. Carey has been active in the evolution of the Soviet -- and now Russian
-- laws governing foreign investment and pioneered in structuring many of the new
business forms now available in Russia -- including joint ventures, joint stock
companies, production sharing arrangements, limited liability partnerships,
branches and representations and others.</P> <P>Ms. Carey, who speaks Russian, has
served on USDOC delegations to the USSR, has participated in bilateral
conferences on legal and trade policy issues and has on a number of
occasions organized and presented seminars for Soviet policy makers on such
issues as joint ventures, intellectual property protection and others.  She was named
by President Clinton to serve on the first board of directors of the Russian American
Enterprise Fund.</P>  <P>Ms. Carey is also a director of the Eurasia Foundation and the U.S.
Co-chair of the Legal Committee of the U.S.-Russian Business Council.  Ms. Carey
created and heads the U.S. Roundtable on Investing in the Commonwealth of
Independent States.  She writes and lectures extensively on U.S.-Soviet/East
European trade and has been invited to testify before Congress on U.S. trade and
economic policy towards the region.</P>  <P>Besides her transactional work in the former
Soviet Union and Eastern Europe, Ms. Carey's international trade practice has
involved her in joint venture projects in the People's Republic of China, Latin and
Central America.  Outside of the international arena, she has worked on a broad range
of corporate matters.</P>

<P></p><DIR><L1>Georgetown University Law Center LL.B. 1965 Member, Georgetown Law Review<BR> <l1>Radcliffe College B.A., magna cum laude, 1960</DIR><p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/partners.htm">Partner Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
