<html><head><title>Michael Solton</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>Michael Solton</h2>
<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.us.net/~steptoe/intltrad.htm">International Corporate Law</a> | <a href="http://www.us.net/~steptoe/intellip.htm">Intellectual Property</a></center></blockquote>
<hr>

<P>Michael Solton's practice focuses on corporate law and
intellectual property.  He is extensively involved in the
privatization of Russian enterprises, representing U.S. and
Canadian companies buying stock in such companies and advising
Russian clients on restructuring options.  Mr. Solton has been
instrumental in facilitating the conclusion of one of the first
successful privatizations of a large Russian enterprise.  For
this project, Mr. Solton designed the legal framework of a deal
involving the Federal and local privatization authorities, the
enterprise, and a foreign investor.   Mr. Solton was involved in
determining the schedule and conditions for the allocation of
stock, and worked closely with Russian privatization officials
on both the Federal and local levels. Mr. Solton's privatization
work is complemented by his expertise in intellectual property. </P>
<P>After the breakup of the Soviet Union, Mr. Solton advised a
team of experts and Russian government officials charged with the
restructuring of the USSR Copyright Office (VAAP), and actively
participated in the drafting of bylaws for the first Russian
copyright office -- the Russian Intellectual Property Agency
(RAIS).</P>  <P>As an associate of Steptoe & Johnson LLP's Moscow affiliate,
Mr. Solton facilitated contacts between RAIS and various
international intellectual property organizations, including the
Motion Pictures Association of America and the International
Publishers Copyright Council.</P>  <P>Mr. Solton is extensively
involved in negotiating and drafting technology transfer
agreements between U.S., European and Russian companies, has
assisted a New York law firm representing a famous Russian
performer in a copyright infringement case brought in a U.S.
federal court, and is advising major U.S. corporations on a day-
to-day basis regarding Russian copyright, trademark and patent
matters. </P> <P>Prior to joining Steptoe & Johnson LLP in 1992, Mr. Solton
was General Manager and General Counsel for the Russian-American
publishing house Interperiodica where he specialized in
copyright, labor and corporate law.  Interperiodica is a joint
venture of the Russian Academy Sciences and General Media
International established to develop new publishing venues
for Russian scientific journals. </p>

<p>At the same time Mr. Solton also served as Chief of Legal 
Department of a U.S. publishing house, Pleiades Publishing, Inc.,
and as a senior research fellow in the Bureau for International
Publishing of the Russian Academy of Sciences.<P>

<UL><LI>Georgetown University Law Center
 LL.M. 1994<BR>
<LI>Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the
USSR Ministry of Foreign Affairs
M.L. 1982 (diploma in international law with honors)</UL><hr>
