<HEAD>
<TITLE>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP/Steptoe & Johnson Company Almaty
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H3><CENTER>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP
</CENTER></H3>


<H2><CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson Company Almaty</CENTER>
</H2>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP is a full-service law firm based in Washington D.C.  With over 200 lawyers, Steptoe & Johnson LLP offers legal expertise in virtually every field of law, including corporate transactions, international tax, international trade and finance, intellectual property, general litigation (including international arbitration), antitrust, telecommunications, transportation, energy, and labor and employment law.  Steptoe & Johnson LLP was among the first U.S. law firms to establish a presence in the former Soviet Union, and several of its partners have been actively involved in trade and investment in the region since the detente period of the late 1970's.  

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP established its affiliate in Almaty, Kazakstan -- Steptoe & Johnson Company (Almaty) -- in March of 1994.  The Almaty office has provided legal services -- ranging from the creation of joint ventures and the preparation of loan documents to assistance in obtaining government licenses to the negotiation of leases and the registration of branches and representation offices for clients in the mining, telecommunications, energy, food processing and other sectors, as well as for non-profit and governmental entities.

<P>The Almaty office works in close coordination with Steptoe & Johnson LLP's affiliate in Moscow, Steptoe & Johnson Company.  Established in 1989, the Moscow affiliate has continually expanded to become one of the largest and most prominent western law practices in Russia.  Its eight full-time lawyers, supported by over a dozen local specialists and administrative personnel, offer substantial expertise and experience in a broad range of CIS transactions.  In addition, the Almaty office works closely with Steptoe & Johnson LLP lawyers in Washington D.C. who also have extensive experience in structuring investments in the CIS.  By integrating the CIS expertise of attorneys located on the ground in Almaty and Moscow with the subject area expertise of U.S.-based lawyers specializing in such fields as international tax, intellectual property, project finance, real estate and environmental law -- an integration that is enhanced by a comprehensive communications network involving satellite phone, facsimile and electronic mail links -- the <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/cistrade.htm">CIS Trade and Investments</a> practice of Steptoe & Johnson LLP brings to any client matter literally decades of collective experience and insight.   
      
<P>Steptoe & Johnson Company (Almaty) is widely recognized as one of the leading western law firms in Kazakstan, based on its representation of several large clients in the mining, telecommunications, and investment fund sectors and its work with the Kazak government on several USAID and World Bank technical assistance projects. The firm is regularly featured in panel discussions on Central Asia and has published extensively on legal issues related to investment in the region.

<P>The Almaty affiliate is staffed by three senior associates with extensive experience in East-West transactions.  <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/altynbae.htm">Gulzhan Altinbajeva</a> is a Kazak lawyer trained in the U.S. legal system, who has worked on commercial law matters for several years with Steptoe & Johnson LLP's affiliate in Moscow and as legal counsel to the Kazak Cultural Fund.  She received her Masters of Law degree from the University of Illinois, and is fluent in English, Russian and Kazak.  <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/abbey.htm">Michael Abbey</a> is a U.S. lawyer who joined Steptoe & Johnson LLP's international trade practice in 1989, and has participated in structuring CIS investments and related agreements in a wide variety of industries.  Mr. Abbey, who speaks Russian, recently served as Project Manager on a major U.S. AID project in Kazakstan, assisting the Kazak government in developing and implementing competition law.  <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/samuelia.htm">Tom Samuelian</a> is an American attorney with experience in a variety of CIS transactions, particularly international arbitration, international project finance and customs law.  Mr. Samuelian is fluent in Russian.  Ms. Altinbajeva, Mr. Abbey and Mr. Samuelian are assisted in Almaty by two junior attorneys, Kairat Serikpaev and <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/titkov.htm">Alexander Titkov</a>.  Mr. Serikpaev is a Kazak attorney who serves as a link between Steptoe & Johnson LLP and the Kazak bureaucracy and specializes in registration, land and visa issues.  Mr. Titkov recently completed work on a USAID Mass Privatization project in Kazakstan, where he advised on a wide range of company formation, privatization and securities registration issues.  The head of Steptoe & Johnson LLP's CIS practice is <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/carey.htm">Sarah Carey</a>.  A corporate lawyer for more than 30 years, Ms. Carey has over the past decade negotiated and structured hundreds of joint ventures and other investment and trade transactions in the CIS, as well as advised U.S. and Russian companies on privatization and restructuring alternatives.  Ms. Carey serves on the Boards of the Eurasia Foundation, the Russian-American Enterprise Fund, and the Defense Enterprise Fund--all under Presidential nomination.  <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/white.htm">Walter White, Jr.</a> is a partner in Steptoe & Johnson LLP and Managing Director of Steptoe & Johnson International, in Moscow.  Mr. White has represented clients in major business transactions throughout the CIS and advised governments of the CIS on economic development issues and legislation.  Mr. White was appointed by President Clinton to the Board of the Central Asian-American Enterprise Fund.  <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/bregman.htm">Randy Bregman</a> is Director of Steptoe & Johnson LLP's Moscow affiliate and a partner of Steptoe & Johnson LLP.  Mr. Bregman has worked in the area of U.S.-Soviet law and commerce for over 20 years, and has an extensive network of relationships and contacts throughout the CIS.  Together with Ms. Carey, Mr. White and Mr. Bregman supervise the activities of the firm's affiliate in Almaty.
<p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Areas Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></body></html>
