<html><head><title>Mindy A. Kaiden Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
Mindy A. Kaiden</h2>

<blockquote><center>Litigation</center></blockquote>




<P>Mindy Kaiden's practice extends to a wide variety of counseling and trial and appellate litigation matters, and has included such diverse areas as insurance coverage, employment law, legal malpractice, commercial contract disputes, and attorneys' fees.  Ms. Kaiden also provides advice regarding education law issues. In 1989 she published an education law Note in The American University Law Review entitled Albert v. Caravano:  The Second Circuit Redefines Under Color of State Law for Private Universities.
<P>Ms. Kaiden has worked on over a dozen attorneys' fees cases and has been the associate coordinator 
for our firm's attorneys' fees practice since early in 1994. In addition, Ms. Kaiden has an active pro bono practice which emphasizes family law, civil liberties, and court-appointed cases representing children who are alleged to have been abused or neglected.
<P>Ms. Kaiden was a law clerk to the Honorable Frank E. Schwelb, District of Columbia Court of Appeals, for the 1990-91 term.  She is a member of the Bar of the District of Columbia, the Maryland Bar, and several federal trial and appellate court bars.
<p><DIR><LI> Washington College of Law, The American University J.D. 1990, summa cum laude Senior Staff, The American University Law Review
<LI> Cornell University B.S. in Biology and Society, 1986</DIR>
