<html><head><title>J. William Koegel, Jr. Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
J. William Koegel, Jr.</h2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Commercial Litigation</a></center></blockquote>



<P>Bill Koegel's practice centers on the litigation of complex cases.  His cases have involved business torts, breach of contract, intellectual property, the Uniform Commercial Code, civil securities fraud, RICO, directors' and officers' liability, employment discrimination, libel & slander, professional malpractice and bankruptcy adversary proceedings.  He has experience in a variety of criminal investigations, and has
represented clients in Foreign Corrupt Practices Act, government procurement fraud, securities, tax and bank fraud, Ethics in Government Act, criminal environmental, bribery, and criminal antitrust matters.

<P>Mr. Koegel also serves as legal counsel to Steptoe & Johnson LLP.

<P>Mr. Koegel was a law clerk to Judge Anthony J. Celebrezze, U.S. Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit, 1979-81.

