<html><head><title>Joseph E. Stubbs Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>Joseph E. Stubbs</h2>
<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/FERC.htm">Federal Energy Regulation</a></center></blockquote>
<hr>


<P>Joseph Stubbs represents electric utilities and other clients in
Federal Energy Regulatory Commission matters and in judicial
review proceedings involving FERC orders in the United States
courts of appeals.  He has experience in FERC electric utility
merger proceedings, tariff interpretation, rulemaking, rate, and
qualifying facility (QF) proceedings.  He also has been involved
in QF-related rate and rulemaking proceedings before the
California Public Utilities Commission.  On behalf of commercial
and industrial users of natural gas, Mr. Stubbs developed a major
complaint case against a pipeline involving its gas purchasing
practices.</P>

