<html><head><title>Mary Margaret Scharf</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>Mary Margaret Scharf</h2>
<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/ferc.htm">Energy Law</a></center></blockquote>
<hr>



<P>Mary Margaret Scharf's practice focuses on federal energy
regulation.  Ms. Scharf also has an interest in public utility
diversification efforts, including domestic and international
power projects.  While in law school, Ms. Scharf organized a
March 1994 symposium of legal scholars and practitioners held in
the Netherlands on the topics of energy, environment, merger
control and taxation.  Prior to attending law school, Ms. Scharf
worked for Ingersoll-Rand Company from 1988-1991 as a Project
Manager for manufacturing plant recapitalization programs.</P>

