<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Monica L. Goebel Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Monica L. Goebel</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/emplyben.htm">Employment Law</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/labor.htm">Labor Relations</a> | General Litigation | Commercial Transactions | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/govtcont.htm">Government Contracts</a></center></blockquote>
<blockquote><center>Resident in <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/phoenix.htm">Phoenix, Arizona Office</a></center></blockquote>



<P>Monica Goebel's practice focuses on employment-related litigation.  She represents clients before state and federal courts at both trial and appellate levels.  She has obtained defense judgments on behalf of employers in Arizona trial courts and has successfully defended against appeals to the Arizona Court of Appeals, the Arizona Supreme Court, the Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals, and the United States Supreme Court.  She also practices before all pertinent agencies, including the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission, the National Labor Relations Board, and the Civil Rights Division of the Arizona Attorney General's Office.
<P>Ms. Goebel's practice
centers on representing employers facing sexual harassment, disability, gender, age, race and religion discrimination charges, wrongful-discharge suits, and related tort and
contract claims.  She also counsels employers on non-compete contracts, employee discipline, accommodation of disabled individuals, drug testing, wage and hour issues, and other human resource policies and procedures.  In addition to employment matters, Ms. Goebel has experience with general litigation, commercial transactions and government contracts.
