<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Filiberto Agusti Bio</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Filiberto Agusti</H2>
<blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Corporate</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/finserv.htm">Commercial Finance</a></CENTER></blockquote>
<hr>
<P>Fil Agusti represents major business lenders, equity investors, and
other participants in complex corporate and commercial financing
transactions.  These have included project financing and leveraged
leasing of electric generating stations, telecommunications
facilities and other substantial facilities, U.S. government
guaranteed refinancings, loan asset-backed public debt offerings,
and international corporate acquisitions and venture financings. 
These international deals include the first private project
financing in Russia, concluded in 1992.  He has also negotiated
agreements in several nationally significant workouts and
reorganizations.  </P>
<P>Mr. Agusti has authored several articles for the
Harvard Law Review and other legal publications in the corporate
area and is a reviewer of commercial law texts for a major
publishing company.  He is the co-author of International Business
Law and Its Environment, the second edition of which was released
by West Publishing Company in 1992.  He frequently speaks on
corporate and commercial finance issues at industry and
professional seminars.</P> 
<P>Mr. Agusti's biography appears in Who's Who in American Law and in Who's Who in Finance and Industry.  Mr.
Agusti was law clerk to Judge William H. Timbers, U.S. Court of
Appeals for the Second Circuit, 1977-78. </P> <P>He is a member of the
Bars of the District of Columbia and the State of New York.</P><P></P>

<DIR><L1>Harvard University J.D. 1977 Senior Editor, Harvard Law Review<br>
<L1> University of Illinois B.A. summa cum laude, 1974 Phi Beta Kappa</DIR>
<hr>
