<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Scott A. Harman Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Scott A. Harman</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/elecpwer.htm">Electric Utilities</a></center></blockquote>

<P>Scott Harman's practice has concentrated on representation of clients with respect to the
corporate and regulatory aspects of developing new energy projects, including the
drafting, review and negotiation of contractual arrangements required to organize,
finance and implement these projects.  He has also represented clients in proceedings
before state and federal regulatory commissions in connection with such projects.

<p>Before joining Steptoe & Johnson LLP, Mr. Harman was in private practice with Newman &
Holtzinger, P.C. in Washington, D.C. from 1984-94.  Prior to that, he was in
private practice in Washington, D.C. and Vermont from 1977-84.

<dir><li> University of Connecticut School of Law J.D. 1977
<li>Middlebury College B.A. 1973</dir>
<p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
