<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>ARTHUR L. BAILEY BIOGRAPHY</TITLE></HEAD><BODY> <H3 ALIGN=center>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Arthur L. Bailey</H2>


<blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/taxprac.htm">Federal Income Taxation</a></CENTER></blockquote>

<P>Art Bailey's practice focuses on the taxation of insurance
companies and their products.  He has represented major life
insurers in legislative matters and in tax controversy work before
the Internal Revenue Service, Treasury and federal courts.  For
property casualty insurers, Mr. Bailey has represented companies in
controversy work relating to loss reserves and captive insurer
issues.  His tax practice involves substantial contacts with the
Internal Revenue Service, Treasury Department and congressional
staff with responsibilities for insurance taxation.</P>  <P>Prior to
coming to Steptoe & Johnson LLP in 1983,  Mr. Bailey was Vice President
and General Counsel at Phoenix Mutual Life Insurance Company in
Hartford, Connecticut.  He also held various tax positions at both
the Internal Revenue Service and the Tax Division, Department of
Justice.  He is the past chair of the Committee on Insurance
Companies, Section of Taxation, American Bar Association.</P>

