<html><head><title>William L. Martin II Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
William L. Martin II</h2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecut.htm">Securities Litigation</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade</a></center></blockquote>





<P>Bill Martin practices principally in the areas of securities litigation, SEC enforcement, and international trade litigation.

<P>Following graduation from law school, Mr. Martin was a law clerk to Judge Murray M. Schwartz, U.S. District Court for the District of Delaware.  He then went to the Securities and Exchange Commission as a staff attorney and later served as Special Counsel, Division of Enforcement.

<P>He is the author of "Federal Regulation of Real Estate Investment Trusts:  A Legislative Proposal," 127 U. Pa. L. Rev., 316-90 (1979), and co-author of "Government Equity Participation in State Owner Enterprises:  An Analysis of the Carbon Steel Countervailing Duty Cases," 14 Law & Policy in International
Business, 1101-58 (1983). 

