<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>James P. Holden Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
James P. Holden</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/taxprac.htm">Taxation</a></center></blockquote>



<P>Jim Holden, a 1960 graduate of Georgetown University Law Center, practices in the area of federal taxation, with emphasis on tax litigation and tax policy and in the resolution of matters considered by the IRS National Office.  Litigation in various courts under Mr. Holden's supervision has involved major issues
for the railroad, energy, steel, financial service and other industries.  

<P>In addition, he has  represented many major taxpayers in administrative proceedings before the Internal Revenue Service and in policy issues before both the Congress and the Treasury Department.  He formerly served as chair of Steptoe & Johnson LLP.

<P>Mr. Holden, served as chair of the Section of Taxation of the American Bar Association during 1989-90.  He is president of the American Tax Policy Institute and is a Regent of the American College of Tax Lawyers.  Mr. Holden served as chair of the Advisory Group to the Commissioner of Internal Revenue in
1992-93.  He served in 1990-91 as chair of the Commissioner's Review Panel on IRS Integrity, a seven-member panel appointed by the Commissioner of Internal Revenue to review and report on integrity issues within the Internal Revenue Service.  He is a former member of the advisory group to the Senate
Finance Committee on Subchapter C revision.  He is a member of the American Law Institute and a member of its Tax Advisory Group. Long active in education and continuing legal education activities, Mr. Holden taught in the Georgetown University Law Center LL.M. program for many years.  He is a co-author of two
books on the subject of ethics in tax practice, Ethical Problems in Tax Practice, and of Standards of Tax Practice, the recognized reference texts in this area.  He has produced numerous articles on tax subjects and appears frequently as a speaker at tax seminars and institutes.

<P><DIR><LI> University of Colorado, B.S. 1953
<LI> Georgetown University J.D. 1960 Board of Editors Georgetown Law Review</DIR><p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
