<html><head><title>David B. Raskin</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>David B. Raskin</h2>
<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/ferc.htm">Energy Law</a> | Litigation | Antitrust Law</center></blockquote>
<hr>



<P>Dave Raskin specializes in the representation of electric utility
companies and other participants in the electric power industry. 
He has represented electric clients before the Federal Energy
Regulatory Commission in cases involving mergers and
acquisitions, wholesale electric and transmission service rates,
transmission access, contract disputes, fuel procurement
practices, antitrust issues, and stranded investment.  Mr. Raskin
has negotiated and helped structure complex bulk power and
transmission service transactions and joint projects to construct
and operate transmission lines and generating facilities.  He
regularly advises clients on the regulatory and commercial
aspects of transactions involving the sale and delivery of
electric power and on issues associated with the restructuring of
the electric utility industry.  Mr. Raskin has also represented
clients in proceedings before the Nuclear Regulatory Commission
concerning the licensing and operation of nuclear power plants.</P>

<P>Mr. Raskin has acted as lead trial counsel in a number of
proceedings, including representation of Northeast Utilities in
the FERC proceeding on the acquisition of Public Service Company
of New Hampshire, representation of Idaho Power Company and
Montana Power Company in the FERC proceeding on Pacificorp's
merger with Utah Power & Light Company, representation of San
Diego Gas & Electric Company in a coal procurement dispute with
Alamito Company, and representation of Carolina Power & Light
Company in FERC proceedings relating to a capacity purchase from
Duke Power Company.</P>

<P>Mr. Raskin is a former Notes Editor of the Energy Law Journal. 
He is a member of the District of Columbia.
</P>
<P></p><ul><LI>Georgetown University Law Center J.D. 1979
Topics Editor, American
Criminal Law Review <BR>
<LI>University of Pennsylvania  B.A., cum laude, 1976 Economics</ul><hr>
