<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>David J. Bodney Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>David J. Bodney</H2>
<blockquote><CENTER>Media and Constitutional Law | Native American and Natural Resources Law</CENTER></blockquote>
<blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/phoenix.htm">Resident in Phoenix, Arizona Office</a></CENTER></blockquote>

<P>David Bodney's practice areas include media and constitutional law, natural
resources and Native American law, and employment law and civil litigation.
Over the years, Mr. Bodney has successfully defended print and broadcast media
in defamation and privacy lawsuits in numerous federal and state courts.
He teaches media law at Arizona State University, and has served as the
coauthor of the Arizona sections of the LDRC's 50 State Survey on libel and
privacy law since its inception. Mr. Bodney's practice covers a wide range of
media and constitutional law issues, including prosecuting FOIA and open
meetings law actions, blocking prior restraints and subpoenas of reporters by
government and third parties, and handling copyright, trademark and other
media law cases. At present, Mr. Bodney also serves as general counsel to one
Arizona Indian tribe, and in that capacity advises the tribe on issues
including tribal governance, water rights and the constitutionality of state
taxation.  Apart from his advocacy of tribal environmental rights, he also
represents developers, recyclers and other environmental interests in the
Southwest. </P><P>Before joining the firm, Mr. Bodney practiced at Brown & Bain from
1979-90, and served as general counsel from 1990-92 to New Times, Inc., which
publishes metropolitan weekly news magazines in Phoenix, Denver, Miami,
Dallas, Houston and San Francisco.  Mr. Bodney is the past president of the
Arizona Center for Law in the Public Interest and a member of the Arizona
Chief Justice's Commission on Juvenile Justice.  He currently serves as a
director of the Children's Action Alliance. </P><P></P>

<DIR><L1>University of Virginia J.D., 1979 M.A. Foreign Affairs, 1979 Senior Editor,
