<P>Alfred Mamlet specializes in communications, computer and litigation matters.  He represents one of the
world's largest international telecommunications companies and its U.S. affiliates in the U.S. and in matters
in other countries.  Mr. Mamlet also represents a Fortune 50 company in numerous proceedings before the
FCC and other federal departments.  In addition, he advises a number of other clients on communications
and computer issues.

<P>Mr. Mamlet's practice has also included a number of complex litigation matters, including nationwide class actions, regulatory, antitrust, copyright, trademark, false advertising, valuation and alternative dispute
resolution matters.

<P>Mr. Mamlet chairs the National Information Infrastructure Committee of the American Bar Association's
Science and Technology Section.  He also moderates the National Information Infrastructure electronic on-
line forum on Counsel Connect.  Mr. Mamlet is a frequent speaker and writer on communications,
computer and information law issues. 


