<P>Jim Vasile is a partner in the Washington, D.C. law firm of
Steptoe & Johnson LLP.  Mr. Vasile's practice has involved the
representation of electric and gas utilities in a substantial
number of federal agency and court proceedings in connection with
energy and environmental matters.  A significant part of his
experience includes the representation of electric utilities
before the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (and its
predecessor, the Federal Power Commission) and the federal courts
in connection with the licensing and regulation of hydroelectric
projects, particularly on behalf of electric utilities operating
within the Pacific Northwest.  In addition, he has extensive
experience in assisting investors and project developers with the
development of qualifying facilities and in advising electric
utilities on regulatory issues arising under the Public Utility
Regulatory Policies Act of 1978.  He also represents clients in
regulatory proceedings arising under the Federal Power Act and
the Public Utility Holding Company Act of 1935 in connection with
the development and operation of domestic and foreign independent
power projects.
</P>
<P>He is a member of the Bar of the District of Columbia and of
several federal circuit courts, the American Bar Association and
the Federal Energy Bar Association.  Prior to graduation from law
school, Mr. Vasile worked for the U.S. Central Intelligence
Agency as an analyst in the Nuclear Energy Division, and for the
University of California, Lawrence Radiation Laboratory as an
experimental physicist in the Atomic Energy Commission's
thermonuclear weapons research and development program.</P>

