<html><head><title>Robert D. Wallick Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>Robert D. Wallick</h2>
<blockquote><center>Government Contracts | Litigation</center></blockquote>
<hr>


<P>In his thirty years at Steptoe & Johnson LLP, Bob Wallick has
developed a wide reputation in the areas of defense, aerospace,
electronics, international, ADP, architect, engineering,
construction, and commercial contracts; contractor compliance,
internal investigations and suspensions/ debarments; litigation
under contracts and subcontracts; protests; cost principles and
standards; joint ventures and teaming; intellectual property
rights under government contracts.  Mr. Wallick is also a
Certified Public Accountant and an electrical engineer.  He has
served as Chair, Section of Public Contract Law, American Bar
Association; President, Federal Circuit Bar Association;
President, National Assistance Management Association; and member
of U.S. Claims Court Advisory Council.  He currently is a member
of the Advisory Panel on Streamlining and Codifying Acquisition
Laws created by the 1991 Defense Authorization Act and of the
American College of Construction Lawyers.
