<HEAD><P><P>
<TITLE>Steptoe & Johnson LLP/Phoenix Office<P><P>
</TITLE><P><P>
</HEAD><P><P>
<BODY><H3><CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP
</CENTER></H3>
<H2><CENTER>The Phoenix Office</CENTER></H2>
<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP is an international law firm with offices in Washington, D.C. and Phoenix, Arizona, and an affiliate in Moscow, Russia. Its Phoenix office serves the needs of corporate and business clients in Arizona and the Western United States.

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP in Phoenix is neither a free-standing branch nor a mere extension of the firm's Washington, D.C. base. It manages its own representations, but also is intimately involved in the<P><P>
work of the firm as a whole. The Phoenix office draws upon the expertise of the firm's Washington office, and Phoenix attorneys are involved in Arizona, regional, and national cases.

<H4>Litigation</H4>
<P>Our Litigation attorneys handle:<p>
<DIR><LI>Complex corporate and commercial litigation, including contract, business tort, securities, and RICO actions, and antitrust litigation and counseling;<p>
<LI>Professional liability litigation and arbitrations involving alleged securities violations and RICO, fraud, professional malpractice, and other allegations against attorneys, accountants, broker/dealers, and corporate officers and directors;<P>
<LI>White collar criminal defense of corporations and their officers and directors;<P>
<LI>Environmental, public lands, natural resources, and water rights litigation involving federal, state, and Indian law;<P>
<LI>Government contracts litigation and counseling, including civil and criminal enforcement, suspension and debarment, and claims and bid protests;<P>
<LI>First Amendment, media law, and constitutional litigation;<P>
<LI>Intellectual property litigation involving patent, trademark, copyright, trade secret, unfair competition, and computer law;<P>
<LI>Real estate and construction litigation; and<P>
<LI>Appellate advocacy in federal and state courts.</DIR><P>

<H4>Labor Relations and Employment Law</H4>
<P>Our Labor Relations and Employment Law attorneys are involved in counseling, dispute resolution, and litigation, including:
<DIR><LI>Defending wrongful discharge, breach of contract, and other employment litigation involving discrimination claims, whistleblower allegations, harassment, public policy or constitutional issues, emotional distress, and associated tort claims;<P>
<LI>Representing employers before all federal and state labor relations agencies, including the EEOC, NLRB, DOL, OFCCP, and OSHA;<P>
<LI>Assisting in union avoidance efforts;<P>
<LI>Litigating trade secret and unfair competition cases involving alleged theft of proprietary information and employee or client raiding;<P>
<LI>Negotiating labor and employment contracts, trade secret and confidentiality agreements, and severance agreements;<P>
<LI>Counseling regarding mergers, acquisitions, plant closures, and separation agreements;<P>
<LI>Drafting and reviewing personnel manuals, policy statements, employee termination policies, and intellectual property protection programs;<P>
<LI>Representing companies in agency proceedings and litigation relating to occupational safety laws and injuries resulting from chemical hazards and technological risks.</DIR>

<H4>Media and Communications</H4>
<P>Our Media and Communications attorneys are engaged in:<p>
<DIR><LI>Defending publishers, broadcasters, and others against defamation, invasion of privacy, and related claims;<P>
<LI>Prosecuting litigation under the Freedom of Information Act, Arizona Public Records Act, and Arizona Open Meetings Law to secure access to information;<P>
<LI>Responding to civil, criminal, and grand jury subpoenas that seek testimony from reporters or their work product, and to &quot;prior restraints&quot; and gag orders that seek to prevent publication;<P>
<LI>Reviewing news and other copy pre-publication to minimize the likelihood of any successful defamation, privacy, or other action against the press;<P>
<LI>Counseling and litigating intellectual property matters for print, broadcast, and cable industry clients.</DIR>

<H4>Intellectual Property</H4>
<P>Our Intellectual Property attorneys provide a broad spectrum of services in the fields of patent, trademark, copyright, trade secret, unfair competition, art, multimedia, and computer law, including:<P>
<DIR><LI>Drafting and prosecuting utility and design patent applications before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office, and securing foreign protection of inventions through the Patent Cooperation Treaty and other international conventions;<P>
<LI>Securing United States and foreign trademark, service mark, and copyright registrations;<P>
<LI>Assisting clients in licensing, selling, borrowing against, and otherwise exploiting intellectual property assets;<P>
<LI>Advising clients as to acquiring intellectual property through transfer, license, or mergers and acquisitions, and as to obtaining security interests in intellectual property assets;<P>
<LI>Helping clients to identify and protect their intellectual property through corporate audits;<P>
<LI>Litigating intellectual property matters in federal and state courts, administrative agency proceedings, and alternative dispute resolution forums.</DIR>

<H4>Corporate and Real Estate</H4>
<P>Our Corporate and Real Estate attorneys handle:<P>
<DIR><LI>Purchases and sales of businesses and tangible and intangible assets;<P>
<LI>Private placement securities transactions;<P>
<LI>Purchases, sales, and leases of commercial real estate, including office buildings, shopping centers, industrial buildings, apartments, hotels and resorts;<P>
<LI>Real estate development transactions;<P>
<LI>Construction contract matters;<P>
<LI>Representation of lenders and borrowers in agribusiness loans; real estate loans and work-outs; equipment, receivables, and asset-based financings; and unsecured loans;<P>
<LI>Representation of entrepreneurs in the creation and operation of corporations, partnerships, and limited liability companies;<P>
<LI>Transactions involving the exchange of water rights, including assignments of Central Arizona Project allocations; and<p>
<LI>Land exchanges and other matters involving the Bureau of Land Management, Department of the Interior, and other federal and state government entities.</DIR>

<H4>Washington, D.C. Practice</H4>
<P>Our Washington attorneys provide substantive expertise and have substantial experience with the Executive Branch, independent agencies, and Congress. The firm enjoys a national reputation in:<P>
<DIR><LI><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/antitrst.htm">Antitrust</a><P>
<LI>SEC Proceedings<P>
<LI>White Collar Crime<P>
<LI><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade</a><P>
<LI><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/apellate.htm">Supreme Court and Appellate Advocacy</a><P>
<LI><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/govtcont.htm">Government Contracts</a><P>
<LI><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/environ.htm">Environmental</a><P>
<LI><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/transpt2.htm">Transportation</a><P>
<LI><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/ferc.htm">Energy and Pipelines</a><P>
<LI><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/elecpwer.htm">Electric Power Regulation and Transactions</a><P>
<LI>Bank Regulation<P>
<LI><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/insuranc.htm">Insurance Coverage</a><P>
<LI>Legal Malpractice<P>
