<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>J. Walker Johnson Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
J. Walker Johnson</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/taxprac.htm">Taxation</a></center></blockquote>


<P>Walker Johnson practices in all areas of federal income taxation.  His specialty is the taxation of financial institutions, particularly insurance companies, as well as the taxation of other industry groups such as railroads and natural resource companies.  His practice consists of tax planning and tax controversy work, including ruling requests, protests, refund claims, and Tax Court and refund litigation.

<P>Mr. Johnson was a Trial Attorney, in the Department of Justice, Tax Division, 1978-84.
<P>He is the author of a Tax Management Portfolio and numerous articles on taxation and has contributed four chapters covering financial institutions and products to the Tax Management Tax Practice Series.

<P>Mr. Johnson was appointed in 1987 as an Adjunct Professor of Law at Georgetown University Law Center, Graduate Program, where he teaches a course entitled Taxation of Financial Institutions and
Products, covering banks, thrifts, insurance companies, RICs, REITs, REMICs, insurance products, and related topics.
<P><DIR><LI> Georgetown University M.L.T. 1984
<LI> University of Kansas  J.D. 1978 Senior Articles Editor, Kansas Law Review
Order of the Coif</DIR><p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
