<HEAD>
<TITLE>Steptoe & Johnson LLP/Tax Practice

</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H3><CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson  LLP
</CENTER></H3>

<H2><CENTER>Tax Practice</CENTER></H2>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has one of the largest and most diverse tax practices in the country. 
The practice covers the entire spectrum of federal taxation,
including representation of business and individual clients in
controversy, compliance, transactional, planning and policy
matters, in the context of both international and domestic
interests.  The firm's tax practice encompasses all aspects of
ERISA and estate planning.

<h4><CENTER>Tax Controversy and Litigation</CENTER></h4>

<P>A major component of Steptoe & Johnson LLP's wide-ranging tax
practice is our extensive experience in handling tax
controversies, both at administrative levels and in litigation
before the courts.
<P>We represent clients in controversy matters at all levels within
the Internal Revenue Service.  During the audit phase, we assist
our clients in analyzing and evaluating factual and legal issues
and in making presentations to local IRS officials and to the
IRS National Office in referrals for technical advice.  In
Coordinated Examination and Industry Specialization audits we
deal with IRS attorneys to eliminate issues and to minimize the
need for litigation.  We work closely with our clients during
the administrative stages of a case to develop an optimum record
in the event litigation is necessary.  That work includes the
preparation of administrative settlement agreements, drafting
refund claims, securing reputable and effective expert
witnesses, and respoanding to or contesting IRS information and
document production demands.  We frequently prepare protests of
proposed IRS audit adjustments, and we represent our clients in
conferences with IRS Appeals Officers.

<P>The needs of our clients are such that we continuously have
cases pending in the United States Tax Court, the United States
Court of Federal Claims, and various federal district and
appellate courts on many different substantive and procedural
tax issues.  In some of these cases, we serve also as counsel
for our clients through the administrative process; in others we
are engaged initially as litigation counsel.  The types of
litigation that we have handled cover a wide range of issues and
thus reflect the broad scope of the firm's substantive tax
practice.  As part of our litigation activities, we represent
clients in negotiations before the IRS and the Tax Division of
the Department of Justice with the objective of obtaining
favorable settlement of pending litigation matters.

<P>The firm's tax controversy and litigation practice also includes
the representation of individuals and corporations who are
alleged to have engaged in conduct exposing them to criminal
sanctions.  These representations involve a variety of factual
circumstances and legal issues, and they include representation
that extends from pre-litigation proceedings, such as jeopardy
assessment review hearings and summons enforcement contests, to
post-trial proceedings, such as the preparation of sentencing
memoranda.

<P>Our attorneys have briefed and argued numerous tax cases before
the Supreme Court of the United States.  In recent terms, we
have handled before that Court such diverse matters as state
insurance premium tax questions, federal statutory limitations
on state taxation, corporate tax issues, and ERISA preemption
matters.  In addition, the firm is often asked to assist other
law firms in drafting petitions for certiorari and in preparing
briefs on the merits, as well as in counselling them with
respect to the unique nature of Supreme Court practice.

<h4><CENTER>Transactional Tax Practice</CENTER></h4>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP's transactional tax practice involves the
representation of both publicly-traded and closely-held
corporations and partnerships with respect to all aspects of tax
and business planning.

<P>We plan and negotiate all types of acquisitions, restructurings,
and dispositions, both taxable and tax free, foreign and
domestic.  These transactions include acquisitions, stock
purchases, LBOs, spin-offs and joint venture arrangements.  We
advise with respect to choice of entity issues and have
significant expertise in using partnerships and S corporations
to structure major business acquisitions.  Our work often
involves the issuance of opinion letters and discussions with
Congressional, Treasury, and IRS personnel, and we regularly
obtain IRS private letter rulings.

<P>We are involved in the formation and structuring of venture
capital companies, including the development of hybrid debt and
equity instruments.

<P>Our firm has developed significant expertise in the area of debt
restructurings and workouts, both within and outside of
bankruptcy.  In this context, we analyze tax issues relating to
net operating losses, cancellation of indebtedness income, and
original issue discount.

<P>We advise affiliated groups of corporations with respect to
consolidated return issues, often negotiating and drafting tax
sharing agreements in the context of acquisition transactions. 
In addition, through our work with closely-held affiliated groups, we encounter with great frequency the at risk rules,
passive loss rules and interest limitation provisions,
particularly as they apply in a consolidated return setting.

<P>As a corollary to our transactional planning, we render general
business tax advice on a continuing basis to a variety of
companies.  We provide these clients with advice concerning such
matters as tax accounting, depreciation and other forms of
capital cost recovery, and the corporate alternative minimum tax.

<h4><CENTER>Real Estate and Partnership Matters</CENTER></h4>

<P>Our tax group provides tax advice in connection with the
planning, negotiation and documentation of real estate
transactions involving billions of dollars of property each
year.  Our clients include commercial, residential and shopping
center developers, homebuilders, institutional investors, hotel operators,
property managers, and others.  We represent large organizations
that operate nationally and internationally as well as
individual entrepreneurs who operate regionally and locally. 

<P>Our representations span the entire life cycle of a real estate
project and include raising equity funds through joint ventures
and public and private securities offerings; structuring debt
financing from institutional lenders and domestic and foreign
debt placements; planning site acquisition and development of
the project; planning and execution of leasing, operation and
refinancing of the project; and counseling in connection with
disposition of the project in taxable or nontaxable transactions.

<P>The recent depression in the real estate markets has given rise
to a spate of loan work-outs and restructurings.  We have
assisted many clients in handling these transactions in a manner
that minimizes the adverse tax consequences usually associated
with them.  We have also assisted clients in accessing the
evolving capital markets through innovative securitization
transactions, including the formation of real estate investment
trusts (REITs) and "umbrella partnership" real estate investment
trusts (UPREITs).

<P>While real estate has historically been owned through
partnerships, much of the rest of the business world has only
recently discovered the partnership form.  Major tax law changes
enacted in 1986 have enhanced the partnership as a favored
choice of business entity, and we have been in the forefront in
planning under the new regime.  We have been heavily involved in
developing the use of partnerships as acquisition vehicles and
in leveraged buyouts.  We have also been active in the evolving use of partnerships to effect tax-free
disposition of assets.  We have planned and executed "frozen"
partnerships and used other tax-free disincorporation techniques
to reduce corporate taxes.  Our clients include publicly-traded
and closely-held operating businesses, as well as organizations
that are active players in the merger, acquisition and leveraged
buyout arena.

<h4><CENTER>International Taxation</CENTER></h4>

<P>Much of the firm's tax advice is provided in the cross-border
context.  Specifically, Steptoe & Johnson LLP represents foreign and
domestic clients in connection with the acquisition and
disposition of businesses located in the United States and
abroad.  In this regard, the firm has provided a full range of
legal services including structuring transactions, negotiating
and drafting contract terms, and advising clients of the tax
legislative and regulatory climate that may affect their
transactions.

<P>The firm also has provided clients, both individuals and
corporations, with tax advice concerning the most advantageous
ways to structure investments and international business
operations, including establishing Foreign Sales Corporations,
deferring current taxation of income, and maximizing the
availability of foreign tax credits.  We have particular
expertise advising clients with respect to the detailed rules
restricting the ability of U.S. persons to defer income through
the use of offshore corporations.

<P>We have been instrumental in the development of joint venture
arrangements throughout Europe, Latin America, Asia, Russia,
Kazakstan, Ukraine and other former Soviet Republics, and we
have helped to structure license agreements and technology
transfer arrangements designed to minimize U.S. and foreign tax
burdens.
<P>In addition to representing clients in connection with the
planning of international transactions and the structuring of
operations carried out around the globe, our lawyers have
advised foreign and domestic clients regarding the audit of
their returns by international examination agents of the IRS and
by foreign tax collection agencies.  We have also participated
in Competent Authority matters, generally relating to transfer
pricing, involving government-to-government negotiation of
issues relating to the tax returns of specific taxpayers.  In
addition, we advise clients regarding the required disclosure of
treaty-based return positions and the filing of the special
returns for foreign-owned businesses operating in the United
States.

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP is experienced in the transfer pricing area. 
We advise clients with respect to transfer pricing methodologies (working
both with economists and independently), document those
methodologies to help clients avoid penalties and represent
clients in the IRS Advance Pricing Agreement ("APA") program.

<P>We are one of the few American law firms with an affiliate in
Moscow.  Steptoe & Johnson International serves our clients in
Russia, other former Soviet Republics, and Eastern Europe in all
aspects of doing business in and with those countries.
<h4>
<CENTER>ERISA</CENTER></h4>

<P>Our firm's ERISA practice covers the full range of tax, labor
and legislative issues.  We represent plans, plan sponsors,
actuaries and other plan consultants, banks, insurers,
investment entities and trade associations that focus on ERISA
issues.  These representations give us a very broad range of
experience and expertise in issues that relate to employee
benefit plans.

<P>In the course of our practice we represent clients before the
Department of Labor on requests for advisory opinions and
information letters as well as on prohibited transaction
exemption requests.  We have an active fiduciary litigation
practice specializing in preemption issues and damage questions.

<P>Our ERISA practice extends to transactional matters, and we
provide relevant advice in mergers and acquisitions, including
issues relating to funded plans and unfunded retiree health
costs.

<P>In the tax ERISA area we provide advice concerning taxation of
benefits, deduction of contributions, and qualification of
plans.  We represent clients before the IRS and the Tax Court
when adverse rulings are threatened or issued.  We actively
represent clients at all administrative levels before the IRS
and the Treasury Department with respect to new or evolving
matters of law to help shape policy.  In addition, we have been
extensively involved in crafting new products or approaches in
welfare benefit areas and with respect to ESOPs.  We also have
assisted clients in developing sophisticated and novel
nonqualified deferred compensation programs.

<P>Our plan termination and multi-employer withdrawal liability
practice takes clients through the termination or withdrawal
process and seeks to minimize liability on account of such
events.  We have obtained favorable rulings and settlements in
all areas under ERISA Title IV.  In addition, we have advised
clients on the relationship between the bankruptcy laws and
ERISA, taking an active role in troubled company work-out
situations.

<P>Finally, our ERISA attorneys have extensive experience in
legislative lobbying and in keeping our clients abreast of
legislative issues and initiatives in the ERISA field.

<h4><CENTER>Insurance Tax</CENTER></h4>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has one of the preeminent insurance tax
practices in the country.  It covers both company and product
tax issues, and involves tax controversy and tax planning, as
well as legislative and administrative lobbying.  Our attorneys
have extensive experience with prior and current law, and are
directly involved in ongoing developments affecting taxation of
the industry.

<P>In the controversy area, we represent clients at all
administrative levels within the IRS.  We assist companies in
responding to audit inquiries and proposed adjustments and in
presenting Technical Advice requests to the IRS National Office.

<P>In addition, we work with clients to prepare protests, to
effectuate settlements, and to file claims for refund.  We often
litigate cases for our clients, appearing before the United
States Tax Court, the United States Court of Federal Claims, and
other courts.  We have successfully represented insurance
company clients in several cases before the Supreme Court.  Two
of those matters, in which we successfully represented industry
groups, raised constitutional issues relating to state premium
taxes.

<P>In the tax planning area, we work with clients to devise and
implement tax strategy, to obtain private letter rulings, and to
develop return positions.  We provide advice on the structure of
transactions, including stock and asset acquisitions and
dispositions, and with respect to the application of the
consolidated return regulations.  Also, we often assist clients
with product tax matters, including questions concerning the
definition of life insurance.

<P>Our attorneys were extensively involved in the legislative
processes resulting in TEFRA and the 1984 Tax Act and are
continuously involved in legislative developments affecting the
industry.  Additionally, we often represent insurance interests
before the IRS and the Treasury Department regarding coordinated
issues, proposed regulations, and other matters of general
importance to the industry.

<h4><CENTER>Tax Exempt Organizations</CENTER></h4>

<P>We have a team of lawyers who specialize in all aspects of the
representation of tax-exempt organizations.  The firm's clients
include professional and trade associations, educational
institutions, health care organizations, private foundations,
lobbying and other advocacy groups, political organizations,
religious organizations, veterans' and other membership groups,
medical research organizations, and a wide variety of other
charitable, educational, scientific, religious, and social
welfare organizations.  In addition, we advise business entities
that participate in commercial ventures with tax-exempt
organizations.

<P>Our tax-exempt organizations practice provides a full range of
services for nonprofit organizations.  We assist our clients in
establishing and maintaining exempt organizations, including
advice as to the formation of the organization and its
qualification for tax-exempt status under IRS procedures, and,
where applicable, state requirements.  Once an organization has
been created and qualified, we provide ongoing counseling on a
broad spectrum of tax issues, including: qualification for
public charity status; unrelated business income; reporting
obligations; eligibility to conduct legislative or political
campaign activities; use of for-profit subsidiaries;
participation in partnerships and joint ventures; and
maintenance of charitable giving, including planned giving
programs.

<P>Our attorneys work closely with our charitable organization
clients in the development and operation of fund- raising
programs.  We provide advice relating to the contributions,
record keeping, and reporting in the context of capital
campaigns, special events, direct mail solicitations, and planned
giving.  In the case of planned giving, the firm provides advice
and prepares the documents for major gifts or bargain sales of
appreciated property, and the use of charitable remainder
trusts, pooled income funds, charitable gift annuities, and life
insurance for charitable giving. 

<P>As part of our tax-exempt organizations practice, we advise our
clients with respect to federal and state fund raising
regulation requirements, including the constitutionality of
these laws.  We monitor developments in this area of the law,
and assist our clients in registering and reporting under these
laws.

<P>Our tax-exempt organizations practice includes the handling of
complex audits, litigation, and criminal investigations.  We
also provide advice and counsel concerning many other areas of
the law as they relate to tax-exempt organizations, including
leases, employment contracts, intellectual property matters,
antitrust issues, labor law questions, and matters pertaining to
employee benefits and executive compensation planning.

<h4><CENTER>Information Reporting and Employment Tax Matters</CENTER></h4>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP actively represents major institutions in the
financial services industry with regard to extensive tax
information reporting obligations.  Our work includes ongoing
advice regarding federal and state tax information reporting
obligations for interest, dividends, and other taxable payments
to various domestic and foreign payees.  We also assist clients
in complying with information reporting for ERISA plans, tax
shelters, and exempt organizations, and deal with IRS personnel
at the national, regional, and local levels in devising
practical solutions to frequent technical problems that arise in
the context of the reporting requirements.  In addition, we
represent clients before the IRS in seeking the abatement of
civil penalties that have been imposed for alleged failures to
comply with various information reporting requirements.

<P>We provide legal advice on employment tax issues.  We represent
employer coalitions before the IRS with regard to the employee/
independent contractor status of large classes of workers, and
we represent classes of taxpayer-employees in test cases
involving both foreign employment and domestic employment.  Our
attorneys are very familiar with issues faced by large
corporations, issues that are receiving increased administrative
attention in the current enforcement environment.

<h4><CENTER>Trusts and Estates</CENTER></h4>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has an extensive and diverse estate planning
practice.  Our practice includes the preparation of complex
wills and trusts and the effective planning and implementation
of important tax strategies, including charitable giving
strategies.

<P>Our estate planning and administration practice provides
services for estates of all sizes and is national in scope.  One
of the practice's most notable features is the breadth and depth
of its tax expertise.  Whether our client's concern is with
planning to preserve business interests, the "freezing" of
estate values, international tax issues, gifts to family or
charity, or simply to accommodate changes in the tax law, we are
able to bring to bear an array of experience and resources.  We
are particularly well experienced at the interplay of estate
planning and other legal concerns, including the protection of
family interests when a threat of bankruptcy arises or the most
effective use of transactional mechanisms to achieve estate
planning objectives.

<P>In addition, our attorneys administer many estates, trusts and
private foundations, and we are well equipped to address all
related tax matters.  By utilizing experienced tax accountants
and paralegals whenever feasible and appropriate, we are able to provide these services on a very cost effective
basis.

<P>Our lawyers are also experienced in dispute resolution relating
to trusts and estates.  We represent affected trusts and
estates, their fiduciaries, and all classes of beneficiaries in
connection with disputes over the validity and interpretation of
wills and trusts. 

<h4><CENTER>Tax Policy</CENTER></h4>

<P>We represent our clients in presenting their points of view on
tax policy matters pending before the Congress, the Treasury
Department, and the IRS.  In this practice, we maintain regular
contact with Congressional tax staff, Treasury and IRS
officials.  We counsel various industry groups and individuals
in obtaining technical revisions to, and clarifications of,
pending legislation.  We assist our tax clients in developing
their legislative objectives and strategies.  Similarly, once
legislation has been enacted, we represent our clients before
Treasury and the IRS with respect to the issuance of regulations
under the new law.  Our regular contacts with tax policy
officials enable us to respond quickly in providing information
to our clients and in presenting our clients' concerns to those
officials.

<h4><CENTER>Ethical and Practice Standards</CENTER></h4>

<P>One of our more unique areas of practice centers on the
standards of conduct for tax professionals.  This practice has
two principal dimensions.

<P>First, we represent tax professionals who have been charged with
misconduct by federal or state officials who exercise regulatory
jurisdiction over such professionals.  In this connection, our
clients include professional firms, large and small.  Typically,
these clients are alleged to have violated the ethical standards
of the American Bar Association, the American Institute of
Certified Public Accountants, or similar organizations, as
adopted by the licensing authority of the particular practice
jurisdiction.  Our representation of professionals and
professional organizations also includes advice respecting
conflicts of interest and the effect of prior government service
on private practice in related areas.

<P>The second dimension of this practice involves alleged
malpractice by tax professionals.  In this connection, we
represent either the aggrieved client or the allegedly negligent
tax professional.  For this kind of case, we are frequently
retained by professional liability insurers to represent insured tax professionals who have been
charged with malpractice.

<P>The law regarding the ethical responsibilities of tax
professionals has evolved rapidly over the last few years, and
changes in these professional standards have influenced the
development of the law of malpractice in the tax field.  In
addition, we have recently witnessed the phenomenon of a large
number of tax shelter investments that have failed to achieve
their advertised tax or investment objectives.  These failed tax
shelters have spawned extensive litigation focused on the
professional responsibility and liability of the professionals
who were involved in their promotion and sale.

<P>The authoritative text on the subject of ethical standards in
tax practice was co-authored by a Steptoe & Johnson LLP partner, and
we have been closely identified with the development of the law
in this area.

<h4><CENTER>Professional Standing</CENTER></h4>

<P>Our firm is internationally recognized as having a premier tax
practice.  This recognition stems from the quality of our
clients, from the breadth and significance of tax issues that
they entrust to us, and from the quality and experience of our
tax attorneys.

<P>We encourage our tax attorneys to undertake professional
development activities, to contribute to the development of the
tax law, and to serve as leaders of the tax bar.  These lawyers
speak regularly and frequently on important tax subjects, they
teach in formal and informal educational institutions and
institutes, they author respected texts and articles on tax
subjects, they participate in leadership roles in the major tax
professional organizations, and they are widely respected in
their fields of tax law.

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP's tax group includes a number of attorneys who
have had government experience.

<hr>
