<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>JOHN T. COLLINS BIOGRAPHY</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>John T. Collins</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/finserv.htm">Financial Services</a> | 
<a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Banking and Savings Institution Law</a></center></blockquote>

<P>John Collins counsels depository institutions, securities firms and insurance companies
on regulatory, structural and legislative issues.  Specific representations have included
bank and thrift institution acquisition transactions, federal agency interpretive requests,
enforcement cases and the pursuit of amendments to federal banking and tax
legislation.  He has also counseled a federal bank regulatory agency on matters
affecting troubled and failed banking organizations.</P>  <P>Before joining Steptoe & Johnson LLP
in January 1985, Mr. Collins spent thirteen years with the Federal government.  During
that period, he was a staff attorney with the Securities and Exchange Commission, a
senior attorney with the Federal Reserve Board and the General Counsel to the U.S.
Senate Banking Committee.  Mr. Collins is Vice Chair of the Banking, Currency and
Treasury Committee of the American Bar Association and is Past Chair of the Federal
Bar Association's Banking Law Committee.  He is also an adjunct professor at
Georgetown University Law Center, where he teaches a course on financial
institutions.  </P>

