<html><head><title>Scott H. Katzman Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
Scott H. Katzman</h2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/finserv.htm">Corporate Finance</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Commercial Transactions</a><br><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Transactions</a></center></blockquote>




<P>Scott Katzman specializes in complex corporate finance, commercial and international transactions.  These transactions include project financings, lease financings, bank financings, securities offerings, municipal securities offerings, asset-backed financings acquisitions and joint ventures.  He also
provides general corporate and commercial advice to numerous corporations, including, among others, high-technology ventures involved in the aerospace, electronics, and computer industries.  Mr.Katzman also represents major creditors in sophisticated bankruptcy and restructuring transactions.  He has represented the largest creditors in some of the largest and most complex bankruptcy and restructuring transactions ever consummated.

<P>Mr. Katzman is a member of the Committee on Law Firms of the Business Law Section of the American Bar Association and participates in the Subcommittee on Quality Control.</P>

<P><DIR><LI> Columbia University J.D. 1981, Articles Editor, Columbia Journal of Law and Social Problems Stone Scholar
<LI> Cornell University, School of Industrial and Labor Relations B.S. 1978</DIR>

