<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>William T. Hassler Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
William T. Hassler</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/environ.htm">Environmental Law</a> | White Collar Criminal Law</center></blockquote>



<P>Bill Hassler's practice encompasses civil and criminal environmental counseling, toxic tort litigation, and white collar criminal matters.  Mr. Hassler is a former Iran/Contra prosecutor, and has also prosecuted environmental crimes for the U.S. Department of Justice.  He is the co-author of a well-known study of the Clean Air Act, Clean Coal/Dirty Air (Yale Press 1981), as well as related articles.
<P> Mr. Hassler was law clerk to Judge Robert R. Merhige, Jr., U.S. District Judge for the Eastern District of Virginia, and has served as special assistant to the Director of the FBI, the Hon. William H. Webster.  He is a member of the Bar of the District of Columbia.

