<html><head><title>Richard L. Roberts</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>Richard L. Roberts</h2>
<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/ferc.htm">Energy Law</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/antitrst.htm">Antitrust Law</a> | Litigation</center></blockquote>
<hr>



<P>Rick Roberts' practice focuses on electric power matters.  He has
represented electric utilities in a variety of regulatory and
antitrust proceedings before the Federal Energy Regulatory
Commission, federal courts, and state regulatory commissions.
These proceedings have involved issues of industry restructuring,
mergers, transmission access and pricing, retail direct access,
power pools, wholesale power rates, and cogeneration and small
power production.
</P>
<P>Mr. Roberts has also provided counseling on a wide variety of
antitrust and other legal issues to clients in both the electric
and natural gas industries, and has participated in the
negotiation and drafting of contracts for the construction,
coordination, and use of electric power facilities.</P>

<P>Mr. Roberts is a member of the bars of the District of Columbia
and Maryland, the Federal Energy Bar Association, and the
American Bar Association, in the sections on antitrust, energy,
and litigation.
