<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Randy Bregman Biography</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson Company</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Randy Bregman</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade Law</a></center></blockquote>

<P>Randy Bregman is a partner of Steptoe & Johnson LLP and was the Director of its Moscow
affiliate for four years.  He has worked in the area of U.S.-Soviet/Russian legal, commercial, cultural and academic exchanges for over 25 years and has developed an extensive network of relationships throughout Russia and Eastern Europe.  

<P>In Moscow and Washington, D.C. Mr. Bregman has represented a number of multinational corporations from their start-up meeting through concluding transactions and operational matters.  He has served as counsel to a Russian-Canadian oil production venture for four years. In that capacity, he participated in initial registration, obtaining required licenses, restructuring, tax and currency issues and loan documents.  Mr. Bregman has been working with several major western consumer goods and pharmaceutical companies in their efforts to establish sales offices and distribution networks.  Recently, he has advised major investors in Russian securities and foreign firms acquiring majority ownership in Russian production companies.

<P>Before joining Steptoe & Johnson LLP, Mr. Bregman served as Director for Soviet and East European Services for APCO Associates.  In that capacity, he advised Western companies on commercial and
legal problems involved in doing business in the former Soviet Union and East European countries.  He accompanied a number of such clients during negotiations with government officials and individual
enterprises.  He also worked with Soviet parliamentary officials and government representatives to design laws dealing with bankruptcy, securities, corporate structures and property. 

<P>Mr. Bregman was the Director for Soviet and East European Law at the International Law Institute in  Washington, D.C.  There he conducted conferences and information exchanges between Soviet
and U.S. scholars and attorneys on international trade law and joint ventures.  These conferences functioned as advisory bodies to the Soviet legislative drafters preparing the first Soviet joint venture laws.

<P>As an adjunct Professor at Georgetown University Law Center from 1989-1991, Mr. Bregman led seminars on Soviet law.

<P>Mr. Bregman is the founder and Chairman of the Editorial Advisory Board of the Russia and Commonwealth Business Law Report, a monthly newsletter published by Buraff Publications,
Washington, D.C.

<P>He is a member of the American Bar Association and its International Law Section

<blockquote>Georgetown University J.D., cum laude, 1985<br>
Yale University M.A. 1969 Soviet and East European Studies<br>
Columbia University B.A. 1968 Russian Language and Literature</blockquote>

