<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mark F. Horning Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Mark F. Horning</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/antitrst.htm">Antitrust</a> | Litigation | Counselling | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/insuranc.htm">Insurance Regulatory Litigation</a></center></blockquote>



<P>Mark Horning specializes in antitrust litigation and counselling.  His clients include property and casualty insurers, life insurers, health insurers and health care providers, transportation companies, high technology companies, industry trade associations and joint ventures.  Mr. Horning has represented these clients in a variety of government enforcement proceedings, including Antitrust Division civil and criminal
investigations, Federal Trade Commission investigations and adjudicative proceedings, and investigations and parens patriae actions brought by the state attorneys general.  He regularly represents clients in treble damage class actions brought by private parties.  He also represents clients in Supreme Court and
appellate cases involving antitrust issues.

<P>In addition, Mr. Horning advises clients on internal antitrust compliance programs and conducts compliance audits.  He similarly counsels clients on the antitrust aspects of mergers, acquisitions, managed health care networks and joint ventures.  Mr. Horning represents clients on antitrust legislative issues, in particular, exemptions for regulated industries.  He has written extensively on antitrust issues, including, most recently, as co-author of the ABA Antitrust Section's Insurance Antitrust Handbook.

<P>Mr. Horning also represents insurance industry clients on federal and state regulatory matters.  In recent years, he has represented clients in litigation bringing constitutional and state law challenges to insurance regulatory laws in California, Maine, Minnesota and New Jersey.

