<P>Ben Cooper practices primarily in the area of intellectual property and antitrust litigation, with emphasis in trademark, copyright, trade secret, and unfair competition law.  He counsels and represents clients in litigation, trademark and copyright administrative practice, and transactional matters. 
He has been Chairman of the State Bar of Arizona Intellectual Property Section, and is active in the International Trademark Association.  He is also a founding officer and director of Arizona Volunteer Lawyers for the Arts, Inc.
<P>Mr. Cooper served as law clerk to Judge Alex Kozinski of the U.S. Court
