<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Gulzhan S. Altynbaeva Biography</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson Company</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Gulzhan S. Altynbaeva</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade Law</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/cistrade.htm">CIS Practice</a></center></blockquote>


<P>Gulzhan Altynbaeva is an attorney with Steptoe & Johnson Company (Almaty).  Her practice primarily involves assisting Western corporations in establishing joint ventures and other business forms in the gold
mining, telecommunications and other sectors.  Ms. Altynbaeva has also provided extensive technical assistance to Kazak enterprises and government agencies, principally in the area of privatization under a variety of USAID and World Bank contracts.  Among other projects, she has served as lead counsel to the
Government of the Kyrghyz Republic regarding the creation of a World Bank-sponsoredinvestment fund for support of privatizing Kyrghyz enterprises.

<P>Prior to joining the firm's Almaty affiliate office, Ms. Altynbaeva worked in Steptoe & Johnson LLP's Moscow-based affiliate where she developed substantial experience in Russian privatization through her work as lead counsel on AID-sponsored projects for the privatization of the Ports of Murmansk and St.
Petersburg.

<P>Ms. Altynbaeva, who is a native Kazak born in Russia, has provided independent legal counsel to a variety of Kazak enterprises and has taught at the Kazak Polytechnic Institute.

<P>Ms. Altynbaeva is fluent in Russian and English.

<blockquote>University of Illinois LL.M., 1993<br>
Sverdlovsk Law Institute J.D., 1984</blockquote><p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/cistrade.htm">CIS Trade</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/assocs.htm">Associate Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
