<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>RICHARD O. CUNNINGHAM BIOGRAPHY</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Richard O. Cunningham</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltran.htm">Foreign Investment Law</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/apellate.htm">Class Action Litigation</a></center></blockquote>

<P>Dick Cunningham's practice is devoted primarily to issues of
international trade policy, to the structuring of international
transactions and to international litigation.  Recent advocacy
matters have included both prosecution and defense of import
relief cases under the antidumping and countervailing duty laws
and sections 22, 201, 301, 337 and 406, product liability and
class action litigation, and trade policy issues such as access
to foreign markets, foreign investment in the United States, U.S.
investment abroad, trade in services, and intellectual property
issues.</P>  <P>In addition to litigation and trade policy advocacy, Mr.
Cunningham advises U.S. and foreign companies on international
transactions, on countertrade and other aspects of dealing
with nonmarket economies, and on the development
and implementation of international competitiveness strategies.</P>
<P>Mr. Cunningham has served as Chairman of the American
Bar Association Standing Committee on Customs Law and is active
in the Sections of Litigation, International Law, Public Contract
Law and Administrative Law. He has spoken and written widely in
the fields of international law and class action litigation,
and has served as advisor on trade law issues to Congressional
committees and U.S. Government agencies.</P>


<P></p><DIR><L1>George Washington University J.D. l968 Editor George Washington Law Review Order of the Coif A.M. 1966<BR> <l1>George Washington University A.B. with distinction and special honors, l964 Phi Beta Kappa Valedictorian</DIR><p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/partners.htm">Partner Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
