<HEAD>
<TITLE>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP/Insurance and Reinsurance Practice 
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H3><CENTER>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP
</CENTER></H3>

<H2><CENTER>Insurance and Reinsurance Practice </CENTER></H2>



<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has one of the largest and most diverse insurance and reinsurance
practices in the country.  Since this field exploded in the late
1970s, we have represented and continue to represent numerous
insurers and reinsurers on a wide variety of coverage questions.
 Our practice involves litigation at both the trial and
appellate levels, arbitration, and client counseling and advice
regarding a broad spectrum of coverage issues.  



<P>We also have had extensive experience in representing insurers
in many large, complex declaratory judgment actions regarding
asbestos and other product claims, and environmental and
hazardous waste claims.



<P>In addition, we have one of the preeminent insurance tax
practices in the country.  This practice includes company and
product tax issues, tax controversy and tax planning, and
legislative and administrative lobbying.  





<h4><CENTER>Hazardous Products Coverage Issues</CENTER></h4>



<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has represented numerous insurance companies
in litigation concerning virtually all aspects of asbestos bodily
injury and building coverage claims. Our work in this area has
made us very familiar with all of the asbestos coverage issues,
including trigger and scope of coverage, the expected and
intended defense, the notice defense, and the meaning and intent
of various asbestos-related exclusions.  These cases also have
required us to become familiar with both the technical
literature and technical experts relating to asbestos hazards
and the propriety of removing asbestos from buildings.  In
addition to asbestos, Steptoe & Johnson LLP has been involved in
litigation or advice concerning coverage for a variety of other
hazardous products including formaldehyde, Agent Orange and
termiticides.  Our practice in this area also includes a
substantial amount of non-litigation settlement negotiations,
counseling and advice.





<h4><CENTER>Environmental Coverage Litigation
</CENTER></h4>


<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP currently is representing insurance industry
clients in more than forty environmental coverage lawsuits. 
These suits involve disputes arising from EPA Superfund and
state enforcement actions as well as private lawsuits.



<P>In these actions we have addressed all major environmental
coverage issues, including the pollution exclusion, the expected
and intended defense, and the "suit" and "damages" issues.  For
example, Steptoe & Johnson LLP authored the first amicus brief filed
by IELA in the landmark Armco case, one of the first cases
decided in favor of the insurance industry on the "damages"
issues.



<P>Our expertise in handling environmental coverage issues has been
enhanced by our active participation on behalf of Aetna Casualty
& Surety Company in a series of lawsuits brought by state
attorneys general and various private plaintiffs regarding the
terms of liability insurance and reinsurance available for
environmental exposures in the 1970s and 1980s.  A principal
focus in this suit has been the development of policy language
to cover and to exclude environmental and hazardous waste risks.





<h4><CENTER>Environmental Tort Liability</CENTER></h4>



<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has a unique ability to handle all issues
arising out of environmental tort litigation because of the
presence of Richard Willard.  Prior to joining Steptoe a year
ago, Richard served as Assistant Attorney General in charge of
the Civil Division.  In that position Richard was responsible
for representing the government in most civil and tort suits
brought against the federal government.  A substantial portion
of the Civil Division's efforts during this period was devoted
to representing the federal government in toxic tort litigation,
including cases involving exposure to asbestos, radiation and
hazardous wastes.





<h4><CENTER>Other Coverage Issues</CENTER></h4>



<P>Beyond environmental and hazardous product coverage issues, we
have been involved in the entire gamut of coverage issues
arising under liability, property, health, life, title
insurance, professional liability, D&O policies, as well as
surety, fidelity, and financial guarantee bonds.  These included
coverage disputes arising out of antitrust, employment
discrimination, RICO, securities fraud, financial institutions,
and ERISA claims.  We have represented insurers against claims
of bad faith and unfair claims handling.  We have also
represented insurers and reinsurers on a variety of treaty and
facultative reinsurance matters.





<h4><CENTER>Insurance Tax
</CENTER></h4>


<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP's insurance tax practice covers both company
and product tax issues, and involves tax controversy and tax
planning, as well as legislative and administrative lobbying. 
Our attorneys have extensive experience with prior and current
law, and are directly involved in ongoing developments affecting
taxation of the industry.



<P>In the controversy area, we represent clients at all
administrative levels within the IRS.  We assist companies in
responding to audit inquiries and proposed adjustments and in
presenting Technical Advice requests to the IRS National Office.

<P>In addition, we work with clients to prepare protests, to
effectuate settlements, and to file claims for refund.  We often
litigate cases for our clients, appearing before the United
States Tax Court, the United States Court of Federal Claims, and
other courts.  We have successfully represented insurance
company clients in several cases before the Supreme Court.  Two
of those matters, in which we successfully represented industry
groups, raised constitutional issues relating to state premium
taxes.



<P>In the tax planning area, we work with clients to devise and
implement tax strategy, to obtain private letter rulings, and to
develop return positions.  We provide advice on the structure of
transactions, including stock and asset acquisitions and
dispositions, and with respect to the application of the
consolidated return regulations.  Also, we often assist clients
with product tax matters, including questions concerning the
definition of life insurance.

<P>Our attorneys were extensively involved in the legislative
processes resulting in TEFRA and the 1984 Tax Act and are
continuously involved in legislative developments affecting the
industry.  Additionally, we often represent insurance interests
before the IRS and the Treasury Department regarding coordinated
issues, proposed regulations, and other matters of general
importance to the industry.<p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Areas Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></body></html>
