<html><head><title>Ellen M. McNamara Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
Ellen M. McNamara</h2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/antitrst.htm">Antitrust</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/govtcont.htm">Government Contracts</a> | Litigation</center></blockquote>




<P>Ellen McNamara's practice includes complex civil, criminal and administrative litigation and counseling, with particular emphasis on antitrust and government contracts matters.

<P>Her recent antitrust work has included a government investigation into joint bidding activities, private treble-damages litigation, defense of a multi-state price-fixing investigation, representation of corporations and corporate officers in connection with investigations into bid-rigging and boycott allegations, and counseling clients with respect to teaming agreements, cooperative research and production ventures, and trade association activities.

<P>She also represents U.S. defense contractors in connection with government investigations into antitrust, product substitution, defective pricing and labor mischarging claims.  She has represented clients in civil proceedings under the False Claims Act and administrative debarment proceedings.

<P>Ms. McNamara has extensive experience in conducting internal corporate investigations and has advised clients with respect to corporate compliance, ethics and self-governance programs.  

<P>She has spoken and written on these topics at bar association and continuing legal education programs.

