<html><head><title>Errol R. Patterson</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>Errol R. Patterson</h2>
<blockquote><center>General Litigation | Products Liability Law | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Corporate</a><br><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Privatization and Rules of Law</a></center></blockquote>
<hr>



<P>Errol Patterson received a Bachelor of Science degree in
Mechanical Engineering from Purdue University in 1975.  He joined
the Monsanto Company, where he gained considerable experience in
Plant Engineering and technical sales.  In 1979, he was awarded
the Monsanto Achievement Award.</P>

<P>Mr. Patterson is a 1984 graduate of the Georgetown University Law
Center.  At Georgetown he was selected as a semifinalist in the
1981 Beaudry Cup Moot Court Competition.  Upon graduation, he
joined the law firm of Chapman, Duff & Paul.  In April 1986, he
joined Newman & Holtzinger as an associate.  In 1991 he became a
partner in the firm.</P>

<P>Mr. Patterson is a litigator whose legal practice has focused in
large part on the review, analysis, and resolution of disputes
concerning the contract rights and obligations of parties
operating in the electric power industry.  He currently
represents the Government of Kenya in a project to restructure
the electric power and petroleum sub-sectors.</P>

<P>Mr. Patterson has substantial legal experience in the area of
commercial and employment law litigation before the federal and
state courts.  Most recently, he has represented Arizona Public
Service Company (APS) in matters relating to claims by
"whistleblowers" that they were discriminated against because of 
having raised safety concerns. 
</P>
<P>This representation has included advice to APS on responding
internally to such complaints and responding to investigations by
the Nuclear Regulatory Commission and the Department of Labor. </P> 

<P>Mr. Patterson was the lead trial counsel before a jury in the
winning defense of a Japanese corporation charged with
discrimination based on gender and pregnancy.  He has also
represented individual clients in litigation involving claims for
wrongful discharge and employment discrimination, claims for
social security benefits, and commercial landlord-tenant
disputes.
</P>
<P>Mr. Patterson had an active role in a suit brought by Southern
California Edison Company and San Diego Gas and Electric Company
against Westinghouse Electric Corporation arising out of
intergranular corrosion of nuclear steam generators.  He has
represented Public Service Enterprise Group and Public Service
Electric & Gas Company (PSE&G) in a lawsuit against Philadelphia
Electric Company based upon breach of contract and tort claims,
in the management of the Peach Bottom Atomic Power Station.  The
case was ultimately settled through an alternative dispute
resolution process.  He has also provided legal defense counsel
to PSE&G and Potomac Electric Power Company in complaint
proceedings before the New Jersey Board of Regulatory
Commissioners and the District of Columbia Public Service
Commission involving developers of non-utility generation
projects.   </P>
<P>He was lead counsel in a successful products liability lawsuit
against a Japanese automobile manufacturer.  His product
liability experience includes litigation on behalf of the Puerto
Rico Aqueduct and Sewer Authority against several manufacturers
of polybutylene tubing used for residential water service
connections.  He also currently represents a minor who was
seriously injured as a result of an accident involving a
stationary exercise bicycle without a full chain and sprocket
guard.</P>

<P>Mr. Patterson is a member of the District of Columbia Bar.</P>

<P></p><ul><LI>Georgetown University Law Center J.D. 1984<BR>
<LI>Purdue University B.S. M.E. 1975</ul>
