<HEAD>
<TITLE>Steptoe & Johnson LLP/Transportation Practice
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H3><CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP
</CENTER></H3>

<H2><CENTER>Transportation Practice</CENTER></H2>

<P>Transportation has been a key element of Steptoe & Johnson LLP's practice since the firm's
inception, and our diverse transportation practice now spans
every mode -- rail, air, water carriage and motor carriage.  The
foundation for that practice is an intimate understanding of the
nature of the transportation industry and the regulatory
structure in which it operates.  Our attorneys have extensive
experience in dealing with the federal agencies that regulate
interstate carriers, and they have litigated a broad range of
transportation issues before state and federal trial courts, the
courts of appeals, and the Supreme Court of the United States.
<h4>
<CENTER>Railroad Regulation and Litigation</CENTER> </h4>

<P>The backbone of Steptoe & Johnson LLP's railroad practice is the
representation of carriers, shippers, and state and local
governments before the Surface Transportation Board ("STB") (formerly known as the Interstate Commerce Commission).  From
complex merger and acquisition proceedings to straightforward
abandonment and construction cases, Steptoe & Johnson LLP has
provided expert advice and representation to parties seeking
regulatory action on railroad issues.  

<P>We also have taken a leadership role in litigation of railroad
rate matters; our experience over the past decade has given us
thorough understanding of this complex and developing area.

<P>We have been instrumental in securing STB approval for a number
of significant rail transactions, including acquisition of
carriers, creation of short-line carriers, and sales of rail
assets, lines, and equipment.  Our expertise in these areas has
enabled us to provide innovative advice on structuring
transactions, securing regulatory approval, and defending the
agency action from procedural or substantive challenge on
judicial review.  In addition, because of the broad nature of
Steptoe & Johnson LLP's practice, we are able to support our
regulatory advice with necessary expertise in rail finance, tax
aspects of rail transactions, and equipment recordation.

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP's attorneys have litigated a wide range of
rail-related issues in the state and federal courts, including
antitrust, complex contract claims, constitutional challenges to
state legislation, and RICO defense.  Well known for our
specialization in appellate matters, we have participated in a
number of recent Supreme Court cases involving rail issues,
including state taxation of railroads, creation of short-line
carriers, and regulation of employee drug use.

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP regularly assists members of the industry in
business and financial planning.  We have been involved in the
corporate restructuring of a number of carriers and carrier
holding companies.  We counsel carriers, investors, and rail
equipment companies on the regulatory impact of proposed
corporate actions. 

<P>Our attorneys also have substantial experience in interpreting,
applying, and litigating the Railway Labor Act, providing advice
on the labor aspects of proposed transactions and management
programs and responding to litigation challenges by labor
representatives and individual employees.  We have been involved
in the front-line issues in this rapidly evolving area,
including employee drug testing, secondary strikes, and
bargaining and representation issues arising from acquisitions
and rail line sales.  Our attorneys also have demonstrated
knowledge of the STB's intricate jurisdiction to condition
regulatory approval of rail transactions on protection of
employee interests.

<P>In addition to these regulatory matters, Steptoe & Johnson LLP's
attorneys have handled complex equal employment opportunity
matters, including class actions, brought against carriers.  We
have also provided advice on Title VII and ADEA enforcement,
employee drug testing, AIDS concerns, and similar matters.

<h4><CENTER>Motor Carriage</CENTER></h4>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP represents  motor carriers, shippers and trade
associations in a variety of regulatory and commercial contexts.

<P>Our attorneys practice extensively before the Department of
Transportation, Federal Highway Administration, National
Highway Traffic Safety Administration, Surface Transportation Board and other regulatory bodies.

<P>The firm has had considerable experience in the representation
of carriers and shippers in complex rate and tariff proceedings
in the federal trial and appellate courts and before the former Interstate Commerce Commission.  Steptoe & Johnson LLP attorneys
also counsel entities in strategies for avoiding undercharge
claims and limiting potential exposure to future damage claims.

<P>The firm has also been very active in counseling parties with
respect to contracts between motor carriers and shippers and in
drafting and reviewing such contracts and other shipping
documents that govern the relationship between carriers and
shippers.

<P>In addition to representing clients in a variety of proceedings
before the STB, such as operating rights and rate and tariff
proceedings, Steptoe & Johnson LLP attorneys also have substantial
experience in handling major rulemaking and adjudicatory cases
before that agency and other federal agencies that regulate
highway transportation.  Our attorneys are also conversant with
the complex regulations concerning vehicle safety and hazardous
materials transportation, and in representing carriers in
related enforcement and rulemaking proceedings before the
Department of Transportation.  We have also represented various
interests in connection with cross-border trucking involving
both Mexico and Canada and have counseled clients with respect
to the myriad issues relating to the boundary between STB
regulation of interstate commerce and state regulation of
intrastate commerce.

<h4><CENTER>Aviation</CENTER></h4>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP's aviation practice focuses on the
representation of both domestic and foreign air carriers in a
variety of commercial and regulatory settings.  Our attorneys
bring substantial expertise and experience to the full range of
matters that relate to air transportation of passengers and
property, including the representation of carrier and other
interests before the Department of Transportation in route and
other proceedings, the taxation of air transportation services,
computer reservation systems, relationships with travel agents
and other transportation intermediaries, immigration and customs
matters, aviation safety and security issues, and federal and
local noise regulations.

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP attorneys also have expertise in a range of
commercial transactions in the aviation field, including leasing
of commercial aircraft and other financing transactions, as well
as negotiation of contracts with a variety of aviation vendors. 
The firm also represents aviation interests in litigation
matters before regulatory agencies and federal and state courts,
and in legislative matters as well.

<h4><CENTER>Maritime</CENTER></h4>

<P>The firm has substantial expertise in representing ocean
carriers and shippers in proceedings before the Federal Maritime
Commission and in other forums.  Steptoe & Johnson LLP attorneys
handle a wide range of matters for these clients, including
counseling with respect to service contracts, tax issues,
cooperative agreements, and antitrust matters.  Our attorneys
have also been involved in major FMC rulemaking proceedings of
interest to the maritime community and in advising clients on
the requirements imposed by the Shipping Act of 1984, the Jones
Act and other statutes and regulations governing maritime
commerce.

<P>The firm has also handled a number of significant and complex
intermodal matters involving arrangements between ocean carriers
and other transportation modes for the through movement of
property.  Steptoe & Johnson LLP attorneys are knowledgeable with
respect to the laws relevant to the international shipment of
property by ocean carriers or by ocean carriers jointly with
rail, motor and air carriers and regularly advise clients on
liability and other issues pertinent to joint carrier
arrangements.
<hr>

<p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Areas Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></body></html>
