<HEAD>
<TITLE>Steptoe & Johnson LLP/International Transactional Practice 
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3>


<H2 align=center>International Transactional Practice</H2>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has an  active practice in all areas of legal advice relating to
international transactions.  The firm is uniquely qualified to
handle the financial, corporate, regulatory, national security,
export control, and cross-cultural aspects of such transactions.

<P>The discussion below highlights particular specialties of the
firm's international transactional practice and summarizes a few
interesting recent representations.

<H4 align=center>Acquisitions</H4>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has represented participants in numerous
international transactions involving the sale of companies, both
publicly and privately held in whole or in part.  For example,
the firm represented Swissair, the national airline of
Switzerland, in a transaction whereby Swissair acquired $194
million of the stock of Delta Air Lines and Delta acquired $90
million of Swissair stock.  The firm also represented Inter-City
Gas, a major Canadian natural resources and manufacturing
company, regarding the U.S. financial aspects of a $700 million
sale of two business units.  Most recently, Steptoe & Johnson LLP
has assisted a major U.S. defense contractor in obtaining
U.S.government clearances for a significant foreign stock
purchase. 



<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has worked on international acquisitions
involving many different industries and financing techniques and
implicating many legal specialties.  As the circumstances
require, Steptoe & Johnson LLP has taken advantage of its great
diversity of talent to call on specialists in different legal
disciplines.  Working as an interdisciplinary team, Steptoe &
Johnson LLP lawyers can identify, address, and resolve issues
quickly and comprehensively.



<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP married its international financial and
telecommunications expertise in helping a Swiss corporation
acquire 5% of a leading international supplier of satellite
transmission and distribution services.  In another context, the
firm has employed its broad experience in utilities finance to
assist a major Canadian utility in concluding strategic
eight-figure investments in the United States.  The firm's
corporate department worked with its government contracts
section as counsel to an Italian conglomerate, in a delicate
proposed acquisition of a major supplier to the United States
Department of Defense.  The firm's transportation and corporate
lawyers have advised clients regarding major international
investments in railroad concerns.  The firm's intellectual
property professionals combined with corporate finance
specialists to assist an important Australian computer
networking firm in implementing its international acquisition
program.  The financial specialists brought in the law firm's
environmental and high technology specialists to represent a
manufacturer of high reliability sealing components for military
aircraft engines and environmental control systems in its
acquisition by a multinational conglomerate.  Many more
instances could be recounted, but the essential point is made: 
the firm brings to the table the whole range of legal talents
necessary to conclude an international acquisition.


<P>In sum, Steptoe & Johnson LLP's attorneys have guided companies
through a whole range of transactional, financial and regulatory
issues arising from international acquisitions. 

<H4 align=center>Privatization</H4>

<P>Privatization of activities previously performed by government
entities is a comparably recent phenomenon, not only in the
United States but throughout the world.  As counsel experienced
in regulatory matters and corporate compliance, Steptoe &
Johnson LLP attorneys have been closely involved in various aspects
of this process.  Through our administrative, corporate, and
commercial representations, we have developed a thorough understanding of the way government enterprises work, an acute sense for the needs of private business, and how to bridge the two.  We have been consulted by governmental entities, financial institutions, private participants in privatization programs, and those affected by the changes in governmental regulation.  


<P>In the last several years, Steptoe & Johnson LLP attorneys were
prominently involved in structuring and implementing the
transfer of $1.7 billion of the United States' agricultural loan
portfolio to private investors.  This was achieved through an
innovative series of private and international public financings
that the firm was instrumental in developing.



<P>The firm also developed a menu of options to structure bids for
the purchase and servicing of a portfolio of loans by a
government agency to small rural projects.



<P>The firm is currently participating in various advisory roles in
the transition of the former Soviet Union and other Eastern
European countries from centrally planned systems to free market
economies.  Specifically, Steptoe & Johnson LLP attorneys assisted
clients in developing and presenting proposals for the
modernization of public services and structuring joint ventures
in areas such as telecommunications, environmental systems, and
computer applications.  We have also analyzed specific
privatization programs in Canada and the United Kingdom to
determine whether the proposed measures could be seen as
bestowing unfair competitive advantages on the newly privatized
entities.





<H4 align=center>Joint Ventures</H4>



<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP attorneys have assisted in the planning,
negotiation, and formation of cooperative arrangements among
companies with divergent corporate identities and
characteristics for operations in the United States and
overseas.  In addition to legal expertise, Steptoe & Johnson LLP
attorneys understand national peculiarities and idioms.  Our
attorneys have the requisite language skills and appreciate
cultural differences to assist in the forging of lasting joint
venture relationships.  We strive to document complex
transactions not only to satisfy regulatory requirements but to
accommodate individual preferences as to drafting and business
style.



<P>Much of our work involves the daily grist of international
commerce.  For instance, Steptoe & Johnson LLP recently assisted a
U.S. chemical company in its acquisition of new technology from
small research companies as well as in its dealings with a
multinational chemical concern.  Similarly, we have assisted
international companies in securing supply and requirements
arrangements with partners abroad.  The firm frequently assists
clients in the financing and other arrangements in establishing
overseas manufacturing facilities.




<P>The firm has special expertise in the area of East-West
trade and investment.  We have advised U.S. companies in a wide
variety of ventures, ranging from natural resource development
and agriculture to consumer and industrial products and services.  In this connection, we assisted a major
U.S. industrial company to develop a general approach for its
negotiations with Soviet partners of several projects ranging
from medical appliances to computer hardware with production
facilities in different parts of the former Soviet Union.



<P>Our transactional and financial experience is complemented by
expertise acquired through our handling of disputes between
private entities and state-owned enterprises.  Steptoe &
Johnson LLP's active participation in the development of U.S. law
and policy regarding investment protection and dispute resolution
allows us to spot strategic issues and deal with them
effectively.  We appreciate both sides' views on issues such as
sovereign immunity, choice of law and forum, and acts of host
government authorities.





<H4 align=center>Asset-Based Transactions</H4>



<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP attorneys have negotiated and documented the
financing of a significant number of asset-based projects around
the globe.  Common examples of such projects are the
construction of facilities and the acquisition of major
equipment.



<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP lawyers have worked on diverse types of
international facility construction projects, some of which illustrate the broad scope of the firm's
practice.  They have represented the unregulated subsidiary of
one of the largest utilities in the United States, in the
development of its international construction projects for
electric power generation facilities.  The firm is counsel to a
major Brazilian construction and engineering company, in its
construction of educational buildings and associated
infrastructure in Africa.  Steptoe & Johnson LLP's lawyers have
assisted U.S. companies in structuring and financing
"maquiladora" facilities in Mexico.  On behalf of international
investors, firm lawyers have structured the financing of
chemical production plants in Europe.  The firm represents a
British firm in its United States real estate investments.  It
has also represented conservation groups in structuring
debt-for-nature swaps to purchase nature preserves throughout
Latin America. 



<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has been extensively involved in many types of
international equipment financing.  The firm has represented
airlines in lease financing transactions ranging from DC-9
aircraft to Boeing 747 aircraft.  It has been counsel to a major
United States railroad company in transactions involving the
cross-border leasing of railcars.  The firm's lawyers have
negotiated the acquisition of steam boilers from abroad for
power generating facilities.



<P>In short, if it is a significant asset sold across borders,
Steptoe & Johnson LLP has the legal experience to structure the
financing of its construction or acquisition.





<H4 align=center>International Taxation</H4>



<P>In the course of rendering the services recounted above, the
firm has provided clients -- both individuals and corporations
-- with tax advice concerning the most advantageous ways to
structure investments and international business operations,
including establishing Foreign Sales Corporations, deferring
current taxation of income, and maximizing the availability of
foreign tax credits.  We have helped structure license
agreements and technology transfer arrangements to minimize U.S.
and foreign tax burdens.  In this regard, our tax specialists
keep closely abreast of developments in Washington so as to
advise clients of the tax legislative and regulatory climate
that may affect their transactions.



<P>In addition to representing clients in connection with the
planning of international transactions and the structuring of
operations carried out around the globe, the firm has advised a
number of foreign and domestic clients regarding the audit of
their returns by the Internal Revenue Service and foreign tax
collection agencies.  The firm has also participated in
Competent Authority matters involving government-to-government
negotiation of issues relating to the tax returns of specific
taxpayers.<p>

<blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></body></html>
