<html><head><title>Carol A. Mitchell Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
Carol A. Mitchell</h2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade Regulation</a> | Customs Law</center></blockquote>






<P>Carol Mitchell's practice focuses primarily on international trade regulation and customs law.  She has extensive unfair trade counselling and litigation experience in all phases of antidumping duty, countervailing duty, and escape clause proceedings before government agencies, courts, and dispute resolution panels.  Her experience includes the prosecution and defense of import relief cases involving market and non-market
economies and a variety of industries, including consumer products, steel, ferrous and non-ferrous metals, petrochemical products, manufacturing equipment, and paper.

<P>Ms. Mitchell has written and lectured on international trade and customs law topics.  She also serves as a member on the roster of panelists for dispute resolution under Chapter Nineteen of the North American Free Trade Agreement. 
<P>Prior to entering private practice, Ms. Mitchell worked as an import compliance specialist with the U.S. Department of Commerce.</P>
<P><DIR><LI> Marshall-Wythe School of Law, College of William and Mary J.D. 1982 Board of Editors, William & Mary Law Review
<LI>Vassar College A.B., with Honors, 1979</DIR>

