<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Tracy Zorpette Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><h2 align=center>Tracy Zorpette</H2>
<blockquote><center>Litigation</center></blockquote>
<hr>


<P>Tracy Zorpette's practice focuses on litigation, with a
particular emphasis on employment law and federal labor standards
issues.  She has assisted in the representation of employers in
all types of employment-related litigation, including actions
involving claims for age, sex, race, handicap, and religious
discrimination.  Ms. Zorpette also advises clients on a variety
of employment-related issues.  In the labor standards area, Ms.
Zorpette's practice includes advising employers on compliance
with the Fair Labor Standards Act, and representing employers in
litigation brought pursuant to that Act.
</P>
<P>Ms. Zorpette's practice also includes contract litigation,
primarily in the area of insurance coverage, and defending
professional malpractice suits brought against lawyers. Ms.
Zorpette chairs the Rights of Women Committee of the ABA Section
of Individual Rights and Responsibilities.  She is also a member
of the ABA's Section on Labor and Employment Law.  Prior to her
arrival at Steptoe & Johnson in 1990 she served as a law clerk to
the Honorable John S. Rhoades, Sr., United States District Court
for the Southern District of California.
</P>

