<html><head><title>Reid H. Weingarten Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>Reid H. Weingarten</h2>
<blockquote><center>Criminal Trials | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/apellate.htm">Criminal Appeals</a></center></blockquote>
<hr>


<P>Reid Weingarten's representations include complex criminal
matters at the pre-trial, trial and post-trial stages, including
cases involving RICO, public corruption, money laundering, bank
fraud, bribery, government procurement fraud, tax and security
matters.  In addition, Mr. Weingarten has served as counsel to
several public officials including former Agriculture Secretary
Mike Espy and former Commerce Secretary Ron Brown.  He also has served
as Senate Special Counsel for the "October Surprise"
investigation, Associate Independent Counsel in the "Iran-Contra
Affair", and Special Prosecutor for the Alaska U.S. Attorney's
Office.  He has had major representations in the Drexel, BCCI,
Ill Wind and Whitewater investigations.</P>

<P>Before coming to Steptoe & Johnson LLP in 1987, Mr. Weingarten
was Deputy District Attorney in Harrisburg, Pennsylvania from
1975-77, and Trial Attorney, Public Integrity Section, Department
of Justice, 1977-87.  While at the Department of Justice, Mr.
Weingarten successfully prosecuted two Congressmen, the Chief of
Police of Houston, a U.S. District Court Judge, a Federal
Prosecutor and many other federal, state and local officials.
</P>
<P>Mr. Weingarten served as the Chairman of the American Bar
Association, White Collar Crime Committee, 1992-94; and teaches
courses on Public Corruption and Professional Responsibility as
an Adjunct Professor of Law, Georgetown University Law School,
1990-94.  He is also a member of the American College of Trial
Lawyers.</P>

<P></p><DIR><L1>Dickinson Law School J.D. 1975
<L1>Hague Academy of International Law
Certificate of Attendance, 1974<BR>
<L1>University of Brussels 1974<BR>
<L1>Cornell University B.S. 1971</DIR>
