<html><head><title>Paul J. Ondrasik, Jr.</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>Paul J. Ondrasik, Jr.</h2>
<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/emplyben.htm">Employee Benefits</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/labor.htm">Labor</a> | Litigation</center></blockquote>
<hr>


<P>Paul Ondrasik practices primarily in the employee benefits field,
with a particular emphasis in ERISA litigation and the fiduciary
responsibility area.  </P>

<P>He currently serves as counsel to a number of Taft-Hartley and
other employee benefit plans, and has represented plans, employer
plan sponsors, and service providers to the benefit plan field on
a wide variety of matters.</P>  

<P>Mr. Ondrasik was lead counsel for the successful pension fund in
Republic Industries, Inc. v. Teamsters Joint Council No. 83 of
Virginia Pension Fund, 718 F.2d 628 (4th Cir. 1983), the first
court of appeals' decision to uphold the constitutionality of the
Multi- employer Pension Plan Amendments Act of 1980.  This case
created a Circuit conflict, subsequently resolved by the Supreme
Court in favor of the Act's constitutionality.</P>

<P>He also was the principal ERISA attorney involved in Steptoe &
Johnson LLP's successful representations of petitioners before the
Supreme Court of the United States in two recent decisions
dealing with the scope of remedies available in ERISA actions --
Massachusetts Mutual Life Ins. Co. v. Russell, 473 U.S. 134
(1985) (holding that punitive damages are not available under
ERISA in benefit claim cases) and Pilot Life Ins. Co. v. Dedeaux,
107 S. Ct. 1549 (1987) (holding that ERISA preempts state common
law remedies in cases involving claims under an employee benefit
plan).</P>

<P>Mr. Ondrasik was law clerk to the Honorable Collins J. Seitz,
Chief Judge, U.S. Court of Appeals, Third Circuit, 1975-76 and to
the Honorable Warren E. Burger, Chief Justice, the Supreme Court
of the United States, 1976-77.</P>

<P>He is an Advisory Director of the International Foundation of
Employee Benefit Plans and has served on the Attorneys' Committee
of that organization.  He is a frequent lecturer on fiduciary
responsibility, preemption and other ERISA matters for the
International Foundation, and other educational organizations. 
</P>
<P></p><ul><LI>University of Virginia J.D. 1975
Notes Editor, Virginia Law Review
Order of the Coif<BR>
<LI>Princeton University A.B. 1972 (Distinction in American
Civilization)</ul>
<hr>
<p><blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorneys</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Areas</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pubtoc.htm">Publications & Memos</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></center></body></html>
