<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mark J. Hulkower Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Mark J. Hulkower </H2>

<blockquote><center>White Collar Crime</center></blockquote>

<P>Mark Hulkower's practice focuses primarily on white collar criminal defense matters at all stages from investigation through trial and post trial proceedings.  Mr. Hulkower's practice has included criminal cases involving public corruption, government procurement fraud, antitrust, tax fraud and money laundering.

<P>Before coming to Steptoe & Johnson LLP, Mr. Hulkower was an Assistant United States Attorney in the Eastern District of Virginia for six years.  During that time Mr. Hulkower was lead counsel at more than 50 federal jury trials and before the Courts of Appeals in matters involving RICO, bank fraud, money laundering, tax fraud, public corruption, export violations involving arms and technology, and a wide variety of other areas.  Mr. Hulkower has also been lead prosecutor in a number of well known cases
including the successful espionage prosecution of Aldrich and Rosario Ames.

<P>While at the United States Attorney's office, Mr. Hulkower lectured and taught courses for the Department of Justice, the Federal Bureau of Investigation and elsewhere in trial advocacy,
conducting complex investigations, grand jury practice, the Federal Rules of Evidence and national security issues.

<p><dir><li> Georgetown University Law Center   J.D., magna cum laude, 1984   Editor, Georgetown Law Journal
