<HEAD>
<TITLE>Steptoe & Johnson LLP/Environmental Law Practice:  Pesticides Registration and Regulations Supplement
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H3><CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</CENTER></H3>

<H2><CENTER>Environmental Law Practice:</CENTER></H2>
<H2><CENTER>Pesticides Registration and Regulations Supplement</CENTER></H2>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has a nationally known and respected practice in the registration
and regulation of Pesticides products under the Federal
Insecticide, Fungicide and Rodenticide Act (FIFRA) and its state
equivalents.  Working with the Chemical Manufacturers
Association's Biocides Program Panel and many individual
registrants, Steptoe has represented the interests of the
industrial biocides industry before EPA, OMB, Congress, courts
and several states.  We have worked on a very wide range of
issues, including registrations, reregistration, data call-ins,
data compensation and FIFRA preemption of state law tort claims.
 In all these activities, Steptoe attorneys work to ensure that
there is rational regulation of this important group of
products, which considers the economics of the industry and the
real health and safety concerns that regulators should address. 

<P>Steptoe also represents individual companies seeking to register
Pesticides products.  We have an expert staff of non-lawyer
specialists in Pesticides matters, who deal with EPA registration
officials virtually every day.  By maintaining constant contact
with EPA's Office of Pesticides Programs, Steptoe has developed a
wealth of experience on the manner in which the registration
process should work and the problems other registrants and
applicants have encountered.  Steptoe's registration specialists
also regularly work with Pesticides regulatory officials in many
states.  

<P>In connection with EPA's Reregistration Program under the 1988
Amendments to FIFRA, Steptoe has been advising registrants, and
groups of registrants formed into data generation "consortiums,"
in responding to the demands of reregistration.  In this area,
we generally work with registrants to determine whether EPA has
properly evaluated existing data, and to ensure that new data
requirements are appropriate for the products and uses involved.


<P>Steptoe is set up to handle contracts among members of a data
development consortium and between a consortium and the testing
laboratories it engages, as well as the financing and
administration aspects of data development.  We currently are
working with registrants on the following data call-ins issued
by EPA:
<dir><LI>Antimicrobial Data Call In, including the ground breaking
antimicrobial applicator exposure assessment<P>
<LI>Inorganic Arsenical Wood Preservative Data Call In<P>
<LI>Chloropicrin Data Call In<P>
<LI>Tributyltin Data Call In<P>
<LI>Copper Naphthenate Data Call In</dir>



<P>Steptoe lawyers also assist Pesticides registrants in the data
compensation activities that have become increasingly important
as the value of data submitted to EPA expands.  We work with our
clients to develop defensible demands for data compensation,
negotiate with follow-on registrants, and handle FIFRA data
compensation arbitrations.



<P>Steptoe also has been very active on Pesticides issues at the
state level.  We coordinated the industrial biocides industry's
response to California's Birth Defects Prevention Act (also
known as SB 950), by developing an approach that responded to
the state's health and safety concerns while minimizing the
additional data requirements imposed on registrants.  Steptoe
also has been active on California's Proposition 65, and on
FIFRA Section 18 registrations and ground water protection fee
programs in several states.  We currently are working on
Pesticides issues in California, Florida, Minnesota, New York,
Oregon, Washington and Wisconsin, and have strong ties with
knowledgeable attorneys in these and other jurisdictions to ensure that both local and national
issues are fully addressed.




<p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pest.htm"><I>Pesticides Resource Center</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Areas Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a><br> <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></body></html>
