<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Seth Goldberg Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY> <H3 ALIGN=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Seth Goldberg</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/environ.htm">Environmental
Health and Safety</a></center></blockquote>

<P>Seth Goldberg's practice focuses on environmental, health and safety issues.  He is active in hazardous waste and Superfund matters, representing corporations in compliance and enforcement matters and trade associations in connection with the development and implementation of regulatory programs. Mr. Goldberg is involved in Environmental Protection Agency and state regulation of pesticides and toxic chemicals.  He has an active pesticide registration practice, working with individual registrants and a major national trade association on data call-in, registration standard and data compensation issues.  His litigation practice includes the defense of regulatory enforcement matters and private tort cases.  He has been lead counsel in hazardous waste cases and in toxic tort cases involving contaminated groundwater.  Mr. Goldberg also has experience coordinating industry-wide toxic tort defense programs. Mr. Goldberg is a frequent speaker on topics relating to environmental law and toxic torts.  He is the author of a recently published chapter on defending toxic tort cases which appears in Matthew Bender's A Guide to Toxic Torts.

