<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Tatiana K. Kovaleva Biography</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson International</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Tatiana K. Kovaleva</H2>

<blockquote><center>Russian Commercial Law | Russian Tax Law | Russian Property Law</center></blockquote>

<P>Tatiana Kovaleva is an attorney working in Steptoe & Johnson International's Moscow office.  Ms. Kovaleva's practice focuses primarily on Russian commercial law and taxation.  She has counselled companies involved in projects or making investments in telecommunications, oil and gas, real estate development and international trade.  

<P>Ms. Kovaleva has been a vital part of the registration process for numerous Western and Russian businesses.  She has dealt with emerging law and regulations relating to corporate forms and structures.  She is also a specialistin property law and has resolved ownership questions with federal and local authorities.

<P>In the area of oil and gas work, Ms. Kovaleva has dealt with intricate tax, tariff and licensing problems related to foreign investment, including bank licenses and currency regulations.

<P>Ms. Kovaleva is a Professor of Tax and Municipal Finance at Moscow State University.  She has published numerous articles and books on a wide variety of legal reform issues.

