<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>ELLEN D'ALELIO BIOGRAPHY</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Ellen d'Alelio</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/finserv.htm">Financial Services</a> |
Commercial Real Estate | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Corporate Law</a></center></blockquote>

<P>Ellen d'Alelio's practice concentrates on transactions and
litigation involving financial institutions, commercial real
estate and related corporate law matters. Over the years, Ellen
has counseled financial institutions and their officers and
directors in regulatory compliance and enforcement matters, as
well as in operational areas such as loan transactions,
electronic fund transfer, credit card operations and the
applicability of existing banking law to emerging electronic cash
technologies.  She has assisted clients with mergers,
acquisitions and changes in control of financial institutions and
in obtaining approval for new products and services. She
has substantial experience representing Federal Deposit
Insurance Corporation and Resolution Trust Corporation in a
wide range of matters, including offensive and
defensive litigation. She has advised them on a variety of
issues pertaining to their powers and to failing and
failed financial institutions.  She also has represented them
in transactions and contracting matters, and in recent years
has been lead counsel to RTC on transactions involving
formation of private/public sector partnership and
their acquisition of portfolios of loans and real estate
with market values of $450 million and $1.28 billion
respectively. Ellen's commercial real estate work over the
years has spanned a variety of projects and client and includes
representations involving, among others real estate acquisitions
of all kinds; acquisition, development and construction projects
and joint ventures; like-kind exchanges; commercial
leasing projects; ground leasing projects; and construction and
permanent loan closings.</P> <P>Ellen has written and lectured on
legal topics relating to FDIC/RTC, FIRREA, financial
institution, electronic cash and commercial real estate matters.
She taught French language and literature at New York
University, and authored several college textbooks published
by Harcourt, Brace & World, Inc. on those subjects, before
turning to the practice of law.</P>

<P></p><DIR><L1>Harvard University J.D. 1974 <BR><l1>New York University M.A. 1964<BR>
<L1>Universite de Caen, France Fulbright Scholar 1960-1961 <br><l1>St. Mary's College B.A. 1960</DIR><p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/partners.htm">Partner Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Area Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
