Mr. Alimirzoev's law practice is primarily focused in the areas of Russian corporate and tax law, international trade and investment and project finance.
<P>Before joining Steptoe & Johnson Company, Mr. Alimirzoev worked as a tax consultant with Ernst & Young in Moscow where he pro-vided advice on business and tax matters to a broad variety of companies.  In addition, he has worked on the privatization of Russian enterprises in Moscow with the Russian law firm "Status".

<P>Mr. Alimirzoev completed his law degree at Moscow State University Law School where he specialized in business and company law.  In 1995, he also obtained an LL.M. in Business Law and Taxation from Capital University Law School in Columbus, Ohio.

