<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>THOMAS P. BARLETTA BIOGRAPHY</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Thomas P. Barletta</H2>
<blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/govtcont.htm">Government Contracts</a> | Litigation</CENTER></blockquote>

<P>Tom Barletta concentrates in government procurement law and policy matters, including regulatory
compliance and enforcement issues, cost allowability and cost accounting matters, transactional advice,
technical data issues and government contract related litigation, including bid protests, disputes and False
Claims Act actions.</P> <P> Mr. Barletta has also handled federal litigation in a number of areas, with principal
emphasis in both large and small EEO matters. Mr. Barletta was law clerk to Chief Judge James R.
Browning, U.S. Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit, 1977-79, and was the Chair of the Accounting, Cost,
Pricing Committee of the American Bar Association's Section of Public Contract Law from 1991-94, and is
currently a Vice Chair of that Committee.</P>  <P>He also is the Chair of the Section's Annual and Quarterly
Programs Committee, and a Member of the Bid Protest and Defense Industrial Base Committees.  Mr.
Barletta has written and spoken on various topics in the Government procurement area, including access to
records, bid protests, False Claims Act litigation, the cost principles and the cost accounting standards,
contract debts and debt collection, attorney-client privilege, and employee rights.  He is the author of the
"Regulatory Report" in the Costs, Pricing & Accounting Report published monthly by Federal Publications.   </P>

<P></p><DIR><L1>University of California, Berkeley J.D. 1977 Editor, California Law Review Order of the Coif M.P.P. 1976<BR>
<L1>Georgetown University A.B. summa cum laude, 1973 Phi Beta Kappa</DIR>

