<html><head><title>John R. Labovitz Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
John R. Labovitz</h2>

<blockquote><center>Litigation | Administrative Law</center></blockquote>




<P>John Labovitz is a litigator, concentrating on complex economic cases.  He has extensive
experience in damage and valuation matters and has been involved in a number of large
antitrust cases.  

<P>Mr. Labovitz has also been involved in a variety of administrative law matters, chiefly
involving transportation.

<P>He was Associate Editor, President's Commission on Campus Unrest, 1970.  He served as
counsel, Impeachment Inquiry Staff, Committee on the Judiciary, House of Representatives in
1974 before coming to Steptoe & Johnson LLP.  He is the author of Presidential Impeachment
(Yale University Press, 1978).


<p><dir><li> University of Chicago  J.D., with honors, 1969  Editor-in-Chief, University  of Chicago Law Review
<li> Brown University A.B., summa cum laude, 1965</DIR>
