<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Greg Giammittorio Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Greg Giammittorio</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Corporate Finance</a> | Venture Capital | Commercial Transactions | Joint Ventures | Privatization</center></blockquote>



<P>Greg Giammittorio works primarily on domestic and international transactional matters.  His work includes commercial loan transactions, venture capital transactions, project finance, public securities offerings, private placements, purchases and sales of businesses, joint ventures and privatization. His representations have involved, among other things:  the project financing of (1) an independent power project, (2) a telecommunications project, and (3) an oil and gas exploration, production and distribution project; the structuring, negotiation, and documentation of credit facilities including term loans, revolving loans, letter of credit facilities and combinations thereof; the structuring, negotiation and documentation of domestic and international venture capital financing transactions; the sale by underwritten public offerings of common stock, debentures, bonds and asset-backed securities; the purchase and sale of businesses by domestic and foreign companies; the structuring of investments through various domestic and international joint venture vehicles; and advising governments and private parties in privatization
projects.
<p><DIR><LI>University of Virginia, J.D., 1988<BR>
<LI>University of Virginia, B.A. English, 1984</DIR>

