<HEAD>
<TITLE>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP/Environmental Law Practice:  Defense of Environmental Criminal Matters Supplement
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H3><CENTER>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP
</CENTER></H3>

<H2><CENTER>Environmental Law Practice: <br>
Defense of Environmental Criminal Matters Supplement</CENTER></h2>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has a national practice in defense of white collar criminal
matters generally, and environmental crimes in particular. 
Steptoe attorneys include former federal prosecutors from a wide
variety of backgrounds, including the Department of Justice's
Environmental Crimes Section and several U.S. Attorney's
offices.  Steptoe attorneys defend both corporate and individual
clients against alleged environmental, health and safety-related
criminal matters, at both the state and federal levels. 

<P>Among the matters in which the firm recently has been involved
are the following:
<ul><LI>Defense of a company under investigation for alleged burning
of hazardous wastes without required permits;<P>
<LI>Defense of an individual accused of hazardous waste violations;<P>
<LI>Defense of an employee of a large company suspected of
violations of an applicable NPDES permit;<P>
<LI>Defense of individuals accused of fraud in the testing of
generic drugs;<P>
<LI>Representation of employees of a drug manufacturer in
connection with a grand jury investigation of the manufacturer.</ul>

<P>The firm's strong background in both criminal law and the
underlying substantive areas have combined to provide the best
possible representation in these cases.  In this context, the
firm has developed an expertise in application of the new
Federal Sentencing Guidelines for Organizations to environmental
offenses and investigations, has commented upon the draft
Sentencing Guidelines for Environmental Crimes, and has worked
with clients to assess the adequacy of the clients' compliance
programs under the Sentencing Guidelines.  

<P>In addition, the firm has served as counsel to corporate clients
conducting independent reviews of the adequacy of their
environmental compliance systems.  Among our recent projects in
this area are compliance system investigations for a major
electronics manufacturer, a petrochemical manufacturer and a
chemical manufacturer.<p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/environ.htm">Environmental Law Practice Area Description</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Areas Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></body></html>
