<HEAD>
<TITLE>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP/Intellectual Property Practice
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H3><CENTER>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP
</CENTER></H3>

<H2><CENTER>Intellectual Property Practice</CENTER></H2>





<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP's attorneys in Washington, D.C. and Phoenix, Arizona specialize in intellectual property -- patents, copyrights, trademarks, trade secrets and related matters.  They do so nationally and internationally for a broad range of clients.  Our representations involve litigating, settling, prosecuting, counseling, auditing planning, licensing, exporting, teaming, joint venturing and regulation.  Often these matters require other Steptoe expertise, such as:
<DIR><LI>antitrust<P>
<LI>administrative law<P>
<LI>export controls<P>
<LI>financial<P>
<LI>government contracts<P>
<LI>international and trade<P>
<LI>transactional, corporate and tax</DIR>

<P>In such multidiscipline matters, Steptoe brings to bear efficiently and effectively the expertise needed, under the leadership of a specially selected partner.

<h4><CENTER>Patents and Inventions</CENTER></h4>

<P>Our patent attorneys provide a full range of services, e.g., infringement and other litigation in the courts and before the U. S. International Trade Commission; prosecution of patent applications; appellate and interference cases before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office; patent validity, enforceability, and
infringement opinions; licensing; settlement agreements; and advice on related issues such as antitrust.

<h4><CENTER>Copyright Law</CENTER></h4>

<P>Steptoe has represented a broad range of clients, on copyright matters in such diverse areas as computer software, publications and artistic works.  These representations have involved litigation, settlements, licensing, royalty agreements, and various forms of software agreements. In the artistic and publication worlds, this has included First Amendment litigation, prepublication reviews, contractual advice and responses to media subpoenas, prior restraints, and gag orders.

<h4><CENTER>Trademark Law</CENTER></h4>

<P>The firm offers a full range of services on trademarks (words, acronyms, and logos), including assistance on selection, preparation and prosecution, appellate, opposition, maintenance and cancellation, monitoring government publications for conflicting registrations and counsel opposition proceedings. 

<h4><CENTER>Trade Secrets and Other Proprietary Rights</CENTER></h4>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has expertise in the areas of trade secrets, trade dress, design rights, government technical data rights, and other proprietary rights.  We negotiate and draft confidentiality, on exploitation, licensing and other agreements, in employment and other contexts; and we represent in enforcement actions.

<h4><CENTER>Government Contracts</CENTER></h4>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP assists government contractors on their intellectual property rights, including patents, copyrights, and technical, proprietary and source selection data.

<h4><CENTER>International</CENTER></h4>

<P>The firm has advised and assisted U.S. and foreign clients on intellectual property -- patents, copyrights, trademarks and trade secrets -- in international contexts.  These have involved licensing, naming, joint venturing, enforcement, export controls, trade and related issues.

<h4><CENTER>Litigation & Alternative Dispute Resolution</CENTER></h4>

<P>When adversarial action becomes necessary, Steptoe & Johnson LLP offers a wide range of expertise, including seasoned trial lawyers, appellate advocates, and specialists in arbitration band mediation.
<p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Areas Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></body></html>
