<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Antonia B. Ianniello Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Antonia B. Ianniello</H2>

<blockquote><center>General Litigation | Malpractice Litigation | <br>ERISA Litigation | White Collar Criminal Defense</center></blockquote>



<P>Toni Ianniello handles a wide array of litigation, ranging from complex securities fraud/ RICO class action suits to routine breach of contract actions.  She has defended professional malpractice suits against lawyers and brokers and has represented major insurance carriers in coverage disputes relating to
professional liability insurance.  She also has significant experience litigating cases in the pension and employee benefits area, including breach of fiduciary duty actions, constitutional challenges to ERISA and general litigation involving Taft-Hartley plans.

<P>In addition to her civil litigation background, Ms. Ianniello has substantial experience in white collar criminal defense work.  She has represented both individuals and corporations in several major grand jury investigations involving allegations of government procurement fraud, securities, tax and bank fraud,
criminal food and drug violations and public corruption.  She served as an Associate Counsel in the Office of Independent Counsel Lawrence Walsh (Iran-Contra), during 1989-90 working on the prosecution team which brought perjury charges against Richard Secord.

<P>Ms. Ianniello is Co-Chair of the Amicus Curiae Committee of the Criminal Justice Section of the ABA.  Prior to her arrival at Steptoe & Johnson LLP in 1982, she served as law clerk to Chief Judge
James L. Latchum, U.S. District Court for the District of Delaware.  From 1975 to 1978, she served as an assistant to Senator Jacob K. Javits on his foreign policy staff.

<P><DIR><LI> Georgetown University J.D., cum laude, 1980 Editor, Georgetown University Law Review
<LI> Cornell University B.A. 1975</DIR>

