<HEAD>
<TITLE>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP/Communications Practice
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H3><CENTER>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP
</CENTER></H3>


<H2><CENTER>Communications Practice</CENTER></H2>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP's communications practice is in the forefront of the rapid evolution of
new telecommunications technologies, services, investment strategies and ideas.  Steptoe & Johnson LLP attorneys represent major telecommunications companies in the developing areas of
personal wireless communications, low earth orbit mobile satellite services, and direct broadcast satellite services. 

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP also advises electric utilities on a range of communications issues.  In addition, Steptoe & Johnson LLP represents the first foreign-owned carrier to be authorized to
provide facilities-based international service in the United States.  Steptoe & Johnson LLP also regularly advises clients on complicated legal issues arising from the development of the National Information Infrastructure. 

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has represented clients in significant communications matters for several decades.  Steptoe & Johnson LLP lawyers represented one of the earliest successful competitive
challengers to the long distance monopoly on both regulatory and antitrust matters.  Our lawyers were also present at the birth of the Corporation for Public Broadcasting, the Public Broadcasting Service and National Public Radio.  We assisted in the creation of one of the first systems used to distribute
network television and radio programs via satellite and were involved in the earliest stages of direct broadcasting satellites.  In addition, Steptoe & Johnson LLP has a long-standing, established expertise in all aspects of broadcasting, cable, common carrier and private radio regulation.   

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP regularly represents clients on international telecommunications matters.  Our experience includes issues involving the entry of foreign-owned carriers into the U.S. communications market; privatizations of government-owned telecommunications entities; international trade issues
involving communications services and equipment and other U.S. efforts to influence the structure of foreign and international telecommunications markets; and the evolving regulation of international telecommunications service providers.  In addition, Steptoe & Johnson LLP regularly advises clients on issues relating to telecommunications investment and regulations in foreign countries as well as regulation of telecommunications by international organizations.  

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP's communications attorneys practice in a wide range of forums.  In addition to working on Federal Communications Commission matters on a daily basis, Steptoe & Johnson LLP frequently represents communications clients in state and federal courts; before the Departments of Commerce, Justice, State, and Treasury; and in front of state, local, and international agencies.  <p><p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Areas Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></body></html>
</DOC>
