<HEAD>
<TITLE>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP/Immigration Law Practice
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H3><CENTER>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP
</CENTER></H3>


<H2><CENTER>Immigration Law Practice</CENTER></H2>

<P>Steptoe & Johnson LLP has an extensive immigration and citizenship practice, covering a
full range of issues under relevant U.S. statutes administered
by the Immigration and Naturalization Service, U.S. Department
of State, U.S. Information Agency, and the U.S. Department of
Labor.  The firm has handled all aspects of the numerous
business-related visas available to companies seeking to employ
foreign nationals for their U.S. operations.  We have counselled
clients on U.S. naturalization procedures, citizenship laws,
U.S. citizenship by descent, expatriation of U.S. citizenship,
employer sanctions and employment authorization compliance
matters.  

<P>The firm successfully has handled numerous administrative
appeals, motions to reopen or reconsider, federal district court
litigation, political asylum cases, and other controversy work
involving the INS, State Department and Labor Department.  We
have handled cases involving companies located throughout the
United States, as well as foreign nationals from twenty or more
different countries.

<P>The firm is expert and has extensive experience in handling L
(intracompany transferee), E (treatytrader/investor), H
(temporary worker), B1 (visitor for business), J (exchange
visitor), F (student) and TN (Free Trade Agreement) visa cases. 
The firm also represents individuals and companies in efforts to
obtain immigrant visas, based on sponsorship from U.S.
employers.  This work includes Labor Department labor
certifications, adjustment of status applications, visa
processing abroad, and naturalization applications.  These cases
often are follow-on representations to previous, successful
non-immigrant visa applications.

<P>The philosophy of the firm's immigration practice is to present
thoroughly documented and well-researched and argued visa
petitions and applications to U.S. government authorities.  Our
objective in any immigration matter is to obtain a positive
response in an expedited timeframe.  The firm believes in
working with its clients in structuring business transactions
and corporate relationships that anticipate and effectively deal
with U.S. visa/ immigration issues before they present problems
to the client.

<P>The principal attorneys of Steptoe & Johnson LLP's immigration
practice are:

<blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/krauland.htm">Ed Krauland</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/moran.htm">Mark Moran</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/fishburn.htm">Michelle Fishburne</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/emerson.htm">Eric Emerson</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/blakesle.htm">Merritt Blakeslee</a></CENTER></blockquote>


<P>The following is a representative list of cases the firm has
recently handled:

<dir><LI><B>Individual and blanket L visas </B>for senior executives and
managers of a large Scandinavian shipping company establishing
offices in the United States;<P>
<LI><B>H visa</B> for start-up export-import office of a French trading
company;<P>
<LI><B>J visa and L visa </B>change for biotechnology firm in U.S. owned
by French parent company;<P>
<LI>Appeal for Chinese nationals in <B>immigrant visa </B>cases involving
unconventional factual circumstances;<P>
<LI>Numerous <B>E visa</B> applications for large Japanese textile and
composite materials multinational corporations with offices in
the United States;<P>
<LI><B>E visa</B> application for a large French electronics and
communications multinational;<P>
<LI><B>H visa</B> for foreign lawyers coming to work for a U.S. law firm;<P>
<LI><B>L visa</B> for Russian investor and owner of pharmaceutical
company with start up trading company in the United States;<P>
<LI><B>TN visa</B> for Canadian consultant working for a U.S. employer;<P>
<LI><B>H visa</B> for senior executive of Mexican railroad with offices
located in Texas; <P>
<LI><B>H and L visa</B> for a large U.S. aviation/cargo company with
worldwide operations;<P>
<LI><B>Immigrant investor visas</B> for individuals from the former
Soviet Union;<P>
<LI><B>Employment-based immigrant visas</B> for high-technology and
electronics firms;<P> 
<LI>Visa for scientist of the former Soviet Union under Soviet
Scientists Immigration Act of 1992, along with waiver of foreign
residency requirements;<P>
<LI><B>L visa</B> for real estate investment and management company;<P>
<LI><B>H visa</B> for Russian sales/marketing manager; and<P>
<LI>Multiple <B>B-1 visas</B> for software technicians from European
countries.<p><p><blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/pgatoc.htm">Practice Areas Descriptions</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/sjbios.htm">Attorney Bios</a> | <a href="http://www.steptoe.com/welcome.htm">Home Page</a></CENTER></body></html>
