<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Sheldon E. Hochberg Bio</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
Sheldon E. Hochberg</H2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Trade</a> | Administrative Law</center></blockquote>


<P>Sheldon Hochberg joined Steptoe & Johnson LLP in January 1991, after being affiliated with the Washington, D.C. law firm of Pierson Semmes and Finley for twenty years.  The major areas of his practice include international and administrative law, and representation of the insurance indsutry.</P>  <P>Prior to entering private practice, he was an attorney in the Office of the Legal Adviser for Economic Affairs of the U.S. Department of State.

<P>Mr. Hochberg has been involved in major international arbitrations and international trade cases,
and has represented the title insurance industry and members thereof in a wide range of regulatory,
litigation, and legislative matters.  He has represented corporate and trade association clients in various
matters before independent agencies and Executive branch departments, and on legislative issues before the Congress. He has written articles on the standards applied by the federal courts in reviewing administrative interpretations of statutes, and on provisions of federal banking law relevant to the title insurance industry.

<P><DIR><LI> Harvard University LL.B. 1967<LI>Columbia College A.B. 1964 Pulitzer Scholar</DIR>

