<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>EDWARD J. KRAULAND BIOGRAPHY</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><H3 ALIGN=center>STEPTOE & JOHNSON LLP</H3><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Edward J. Krauland</H2>
<blockquote><CENTER><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/intltrad.htm">International Law/Trade</a> | 
<a href="http://www.steptoe.com/govtcont.htm">Government Procurement</a> | 
<a href="http://www.steptoe.com/immigrat.htm">Immigration</a></CENTER></blockquote>


<P>Ed Krauland practices in the areas of international law, trade and procurement.  His principal involvement has been in antidumping and countervailing duty investigations conducted by the U.S. government, export control regulations on high technology products, antiboycott and foreign sanctions compliance work, international dispute resolution, immigration, and the trade/security aspects of foreign acquisitions.

<P>Mr. Krauland assists clients in pursuing export and investment opportunities abroad, including the preparation and negotiation of contractual and distribution agreements.  He has practiced before the U.S.-Iran Claims Tribunal in The Hague and U.S District Court for the District of Columbia.  He has been
involved in handling complex internal investigations in the areas of antitrust, export controls and government procurement enforcement matters.

<P>He is a member of the American Bar Association's Sections of International Law and Practice and Public Contract Law, and is Vice-Chairman of the International Procurement Committee of the ABA Section of Public Contract Law.

<P>Mr. Krauland was a foreign policy analyst at the U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission for a year before attending law school.  After graduation, he was law clerk to Judge Albert J. Engel, U.S. Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit, 1980-81.

