<P>Cecil J. Olmstead is Of Counsel to the firm and a Visiting
Scholar at Yale University School of Law.  He was made Commander
of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire (Honorary) at a
ceremony at the British Embassy on November 13, 1990.  Professor
Olmstead was honored for his work in the development of inter-
national law and his contributions to the International Law
Association, headquartered in London.  He earlier was presented
with the Gold Medal of the City of Brussels, Belgium, by the
Mayor and in 1984 was presented with the Medal of the City of
Paris in the name of mayor Jacques Chirac at the Hotel de Ville
in Paris.  Professor Olmstead has served both as President of the
International Law Association and Chairman of its Executive
Council.  </P>
<P>Presently, he, along with Lord Wilberforce, is a Patron of the
International Law Association.  At Steptoe & Johnson LLP, Professor
Olmstead advises with respect to international law and inter-
national trade and investment matters, and is a leading expert in
the field of international arbitration.

