<html><head><title>Robert E. McLaughlin Bio</title></head><body><h3 align=center>Steptoe & Johnson LLP</h3><h2 align=center>
Robert E. McLaughlin</h2>

<blockquote><center><a href="http://www.steptoe.com/corpsecu.htm">Securities Regulation</a> | General Business Law</center></blockquote>

<P>Bob McLaughlin has long experience in securities regulation and general corporate matters including mergers, acquisitions, financings and venture capital and real estate transactions.</P>

<P>Before coming to Steptoe & Johnson LLP, Mr. McLaughlin served first as a financial analyst, and later as an Attorney Advisor, Division of Corporation Finance, Securities and Exchange Commission.  He is a member of the Small Business Committee of the American Bar Association's Section of Business Law and currently serves as Chairman of its Subcommittee on Financing.  He has lectured on the federal securities laws and acts as a
Public Arbitrator for the National Association of Securities Dealers, Inc.  Mr. McLaughlin is a Director of Attorneys' Liability Assurance Society (Bermuda), Ltd.

<P><DIR><LI> Georgetown University J.D. 1965
<LI>Iowa State University  B.S. 1960</DIR>
