<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE></HEAD>
<body background="images/paper1.gif"><P>
<A HREF="index.html"><img border=0 SRC="images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="index.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="images/company.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=3>Elan is an NYSE listed global organisation  of over 1,200 skilled people which spent US$68 million during 1995 on research and development of drug delivery technology and products.<P>
Elan has rolled back the feasibility thresholds in drug delivery. Throughout it's 26 year history Elan has broken new ground with products such as Tetrabid&reg;, Theolan&reg; and Duranol&reg; in the '70s, Cardizem&reg; SR, Verelan&reg; and Nifelan&reg; in the '80s and Cardizem&reg; CD, ProStep&reg;, Naprelan&reg; and Theodur&reg; paediatric to date in the '90s.<P>
Elan has achieved a pre-eminent status as a technological innovator, a dynamic developer of new product formulations and a world-class manufacturer of cost-effective new pharmaceutical therapies. 
Elan has achieved many firsts in drug delivery.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><h1><b>first</b></h1></ul></ul><P>
to eradicate the food effect of long-acting verapamil<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><h1><b>first</b></h1></ul></ul><P> 
to achieve a US hypertension claim for diltiazem<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><h1><b>first</b></h1></ul></ul><P>
to introduce controlled release paediatric dosage forms of theophylline<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><h1><b>first</b></h1></ul></ul><P>  
to double oral bioavailability and half dosage regimes of antibiotics like tetracycline and erythromycin<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><h1><b>first</b></h1></ul></ul><P> 
to develop transdermal nicotine smoking cessation therapy<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><h1><b>first</b></h1></ul></ul><P>
to develop effective taste-masking systems for paediatric products.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><h1><b>first</b></h1></ul></ul><P>
to bring to market a once-daily NSAID (Non Steroidal Antiinflammatory Drug) with arthritic and analgesia indications - Naprelan.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
Elan's success in achieving "firsts" has added up  to 22 new products in over 40 of the world's markets and billions of dollars in additional sales revenues for our partners. Elan's "firsts" have also meant that many excellent therapeutic agents can be utilized more effectively in patients, extending the life cycle for drug products and adding efficiencies across the medical cost-spectrum.<P>
Elan's "firsts" have meant that patients benefit in many ways - and by getting a better therapeutic response, by finding it easier to take their medication, by experiencing less side effects and by taking less drug less frequently.<P>
Elan will continue to lead the way in the field of conventional oral and transdermal drug delivery 
as it has since 1969, and is now also on the threshold of taking drug delivery into a whole new realm of scientific and therapeutic application, of meeting a new array of biomedical challenges, and ultimately of bringing sophisticated, yet viable and effective new cures to those who need them most - patients.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
