<head><title>Elan Corporation plc.</title></head>



<BODY BACKGROUND="images/paper1.gif" TEXT="#03056b"><p>
<a href="index.html"><img border=0 src="images/elnmain.gif" width=525 height=75 ismap usemap="index.html"></a><p>

<img src="images/quarter.gif">
<p><ul>
<a href="#top">Elan Corporation plc., 1st Quarter Report ended June 30, 1996</a>
<br>
<a href="q_report2.html">Elan Corporation plc., 2nd Quarter Report ended September 30, 1996</a>
<br>
<a href="q_report3.html">Elan Corporation plc., 3rd Quarter Report, Fiscal 1996</a>
<br>

<p>
<br>

<a name="top">
<b>Elan Corporation plc., 1st Quarter Report ended June 30, 1996</b>

<p>
<br>

<a href="#table">Consolidated Balance Sheet</a>

<p>
<br>

Dear Shareholders,

<p>
<br>
I am pleased to report to you an increase in net income of 51% to $27,982,000 and earnings per share by 30% to $0.34 for the quarter ended 30th June.<P>
<br><P>
Total revenue for the first quarter was $67,620,000, an increase of 39% from $48,691,000 in the first quarter of the previous year. Revenue from product sales rose 50% to $33,301,000 from $22,186,000 for the quarter, largely reflecting the launch of Naprelan&reg; in the United States in April 1996.<P>
<br>
Royalties and fees in the quarter were $22,155,000, up from $17,503,000 in the first quarter of last year. Licence and option fees reflected 6 new agreements entered into during the quarter and revenue from agreements where milestone payments were earned in the quarter.<P>
<br>
Research revenues increased to $12,164,000 for the quarter from $9,002,000 in the first quarter of fiscal 1996. Research revenues included $10,596,000 received from Advanced Therapeutic Systems Limited, up from $6,391,000, reflecting a high level of payments for external work done on behalf of ATS in the quarter.<P>
<br>
The gross margin declined reflecting, primarily, the significant increase in funded research projects for which no milestone payments were achieved, and the early stages of production and the large quantities of samples of Naprelan&reg;.<P>
<br>
Unfunded research and development expenditures declined to $5,511,000 from $6,608,000 in the first quarter of the previous year reflecting the launch of products over the preceding 12 months.<P>
<br>
Interest and other income increased by 64% to $7,006,000 from $4,265,000 reflecting primarily higher levels of cash and cash equivalents in the current quarter compared to the previous year.<P>
<br>
This was an extremely important quarter in the long-term development of Elan. The approval of the merger with Athena Neurosciences during the quarter, and its completion on July 1, 1996, brings important new capabilities to Elan. For the first time, Elan will have drug discovery research and sales and marketing capability in its chosen therapeutic niche of diseases of the central nervous system. The results to June 30 do not, of course, reflect in any way the effect or benefits of the merger. The results of Athena will be consolidated from July 1.<P>
<br>
The launch of Naprelan in the United States in April by our licensing partner, the Wyeth-Ayerst division of American Home Products Corporation was a major event for the company. Naprelan continues to build market share and is well placed to become a major product in its category. The progress of Cardizem CD and Verelan is also very satisfactory in difficult market conditions. We are excited about the opportunities 
for our products in the Far East, particularly in Japan.<P>
<br>
I am optimistic about the challenges and prospects facing the enlarged Elan Corporation. The combination of our leading edge position as preferred industry partner for drug delivery technologies supported by a strong cash flow and balance sheet leaves Elan well positioned to maximise future opportunities.<P>
<br>
As previously announced, we have changed the reporting currency from Irish pounds to U.S. dollars with effect from April 1, 1996. The company's fiscal year also changed from March 31 to December 31. Therefore, for 1996 the company will report a shortened fiscal period from April 1, 1996 to December 31, 1996. Also, on August 15 the stock split was implemented (following its approval at the stockholder meeting on June 27) and the per share numbers give effect to this charge.<P>

<p>
<br>
<br>
<b>

Sincerely yours<P>
<br><P>
<br>
Donal Geaney<br>
President & Chief Executive Officer<br>
August 30, 1996<br>
</b>

<p>
<br>
<br>
