<DOCNO>WT04-B38-337</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA026-000282-B027-165</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.elan.ie:80/technologies.html 194.125.133.25 19970113212101 text/html 6314
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Commerce/1.12
Date: Monday, 13-Jan-97 21:21:00 GMT
Last-modified: Friday, 21-Jun-96 10:43:26 GMT
Content-length: 6131
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE></HEAD>
<body background="images/paper1.gif" TEXT="#03056b"><P>
<A HREF="index.html"><img border=0 SRC="images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="index.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="images/techno.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=3>Elan's  unique and innovative drug delivery technologies provide the framework to meet the formidable challenges of delivering complex peptide and protein molecules, of targeting therapy to distinct tissues and cells, of tailoring pharmacological intervention to individual patient biorhythms and response-peaks. Much of Elan's technology base in this field has already entered clinical trials and we expect to register and introduce  to the market in conjunction with our partners, several innovative products by the end of this decade - we intend  to be first to do so.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>PANODERM&reg; XL</b><P></I>Transcutaneous Macromolecule Delivery</i></ul></ul><P>
Panoderm XL is Elan's patch technology that delivers drug through a concealed miniature probe which penetrates the stratum corneum. Panoderm XL is fully disposable and and is programmed to deliver drugs to preset bolus, continuous or pulsed regimen, or a combination thereof, delivering for up to 72 hours. The complexity of the device is hidden from the patient and is simple to use.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>PANODERM&reg;</b><P></I>Electro-Transdermal Drug Delivery</i></ul></ul><P>
Transdermal delivery is a more acceptable alternative to parenteral therapy for drugs where oral administration is not viable. Few compounds, however, will permeate the skin passively. Elan's PANODERM technology overcomes these barriers through the use of a low level electric current to transport the drug through the skin. Elan has completed phase I testing of products such as fentanyl, hydromorphone, calcitonin and LHRH.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>PANOJECT&reg;</b><P></I>Subcutaneous Micro-infusion Delivery</i></ul></ul><P>
Panoject is a low cost lightweight pump designed for continuous or intermittent subcutaneous delivery of small volume injectables (20 ml) for up to 72 hours. Panoject is a two-component system comprising of a reusable control unit which fits over a disposable cartridge containing  the drug solution and is attached to the body via an adhesive base or strap.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>BEODAS&reg;</b><P></I>Oral Peptide Delivery</i></ul></ul><P>
BEODAS is applied to the oral delivery of proteins, peptides  and other macromolecules. BEODAS is a matrix technology in which drug particles are trapped in a biodegradable polymer to form particles in the submicron size range.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>INDAS&reg;</b><P></ul></ul>
INDAS is a unique high-energy matrix tablet designed specifically to improve the solubility and absorption characteristics of poorly water soluble drugs. The INDAS technology boty improves the inherent solubility of the drug and controls its delivery over a prolonged pre-determined period. The gel-forming erodable tablet system allows for smooth and continuous absorption, eliminating the wide peak to trough pharmacokinetic fluctuations experienced with poorly soluble drugs.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>EFVDAS&reg;</b><P></ul></ul>
EFVDAS is a rapid and completely dissolving system and provides for pleasant tasting drinkable solutions which are particularly suitable for the administration of drugs to paediatric and geriatric patents. With the increasing emphasis by health regulatory authorities on the switching of many drugs from prescription to ITC status, Elan will employ its EFVDAS technology in providing new formulations of such drugs.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>MODAS&reg;</b><P></ul></ul>
MODAS is specifically designed to control absorption of highly water soluble drugs. Each MODAS tablet formulation employs a differentially permeable membrane which controls drug dissolution and allows gentle diffusion from the micro environment of the tablet into the G.I. tract. This facilitates uniform drug absorption and thus avoids the attendant hazards of aggressive monodirectional of bolus delivery.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>IPDAS&reg;</b><P></ul></ul>
IPDAS is a specilised multiparticulate high-density bead system which Elan has developed specifically to minimise the adverse gastro-intestinal effects commonly encountered with certain irritant drug compounds, the most notable of which are the Non-Steroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drug (NSAID) class.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>PHARMAZOMES&reg;</b><P></ul></ul>
Elan's Pharmazomes drug delivery system is a highly adaptable drug/polymer micromatrix technology. Suitable for long-acting parental administration from 10-90 days duration of delivery, Pharmazomes are minute spheroidal polymer microparticles into which a wide variety of drugs may be incorporated. It provides a particularly suitable method for administering drugs to paediatric and geriatric patients.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>DERMAFLEX&reg;</b><P></ul></ul>
Dermaflex is a unique passive transfermal patch system which employs a hydrogel matrix into which the drug is incorporated. Dermaflex regulates both the availability and absorption of the drug in a manner which allows for controlled and efficient systemic delivery. Dermaflex ensures efficient delivery of the dose employed at the required release rate without significant wastage of drug.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<b><ul><ul>SODAS&reg;</b><P></ul></ul>
SODAS is a multiparticulate drug delivery technology which precisely controls the release and absorption rate of the drug. Microspheroidal beads, each with a diameter in the range of 0.5mm to 2.0mm, are formulated using Elan's unique absorption optimising and rate controlling processes. The formulation techniques employed in the production of each SODAS bead caters to the physicochemical, pharmacokinetic and clinical characteristics and requirements of each individual drug.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
<h5 align=center> <a href="index.html">HOME</a>| <a  href="anrep.html"> Annual Report</h5></FONT></body>











