<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT04-B38-342</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA026-000282-B027-347</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.elan.ie:80/productdev.html 194.125.133.25 19970113212423 text/html 12110
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Commerce/1.12
Date: Monday, 13-Jan-97 21:24:25 GMT
Last-modified: Friday, 21-Jun-96 10:43:23 GMT
Content-length: 11926
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE></HEAD>
<body background="images/paper1.gif"><P>
<A HREF="anrep.html"><img border=0 SRC="images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="anrep.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="images/prodev.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=3>The Elan development pipeline now reflects the mature business base of the Company and provides a balance in the terms of the number of projects, stages of development, the complexity of the delivery problem and the timeframe to commercialisation.<P>

Our new and emerging technologies being developed at our research laboratories in Trinity College, Dublin show significant progress in the area of improved delivery of macromolecules. These developments have been further augmented by a range of strategic alliances that add to Elan's core expertise. During the year 37  products were evaluated in clinical trials. Regulatory filings were prepared for 17 countries and 31 approvals for 10 products were received in 17 countries. During 1996 we anticipate making 6 FDA filings in the United States and up to 70 filings in 41 other countries. This level of activity reflects the successful conclusion of a number of our pipeline projects.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><H3>Elan's Emerging and New Technologies</H3></ul></ul>
Elan's new technologies are designed to address problems associated with many new chemical entities and products from the biotechnology sector such as site selective absorption, narrow therapeutic windows etc. As a result, we are developing a range of options to overcome these issues including enhanced oral dosage forms with biodegradable polymers, electrically assisted transdermals, long-acting injectables and pulmonary formulations for delivery to the lower lung. This has produced a rich pipeline of over 65 products spanning a broad range of therapies which are being developed both through our own research activities and together with partners in strategic alliances.<P>

BEODAS is designed to achieve oral absorption of macromolecules. A number of Phase I studies have shown encouraging bioavailability. The lead product in this group being our Beodas formulation of LMWH (low molecular weight Heparin). We are also adapting this technology to an application in pulmonary delivery where we have now completed Phase I studies.<P>

Panoderm. We have now completed two Phase II analgesia studies in Europe and have filed an IND (Investigational New Drug) application in the United States under which clinical studies in pain control are underway as part of continuing programmes to achieve macromolecule delivery across the skin. Phase I studies in Calcitonin are also now in progress.<P>

Medipad has been developed in Israel by our medical device technology division. This device delivery group has significant engineering and device experience and is developing a number of new device based delivery systems. The first of these is Medipad which provides the convenience and appearance of a transdermal product with the accuracy and consistency of parenteral systems. We are presently evaluating a number of compounds in this area including a partnership with a major pharmaceutical company to confirm the performance characteristics in this new innovative system of one of their new chemical entities.<P>

<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><H3>Key Collaborative Research Relationships</H3></ul></ul>
Our strategy of developing collaborative research relationships gives Elan access to a broad range of drug delivery technology systems.<P>

<ul><ul><b>Ethical</b></ul>	<P>
The alliance with Ethical Holdings gives Elan access to Ethical's MultiporÅ technology and broadens our ability in transdermal delivery. A range of transdermal and oral products have been identified to be developed under this alliance.</ul><P>

<ul><ul><b>Dura</b></ul><P>
The strong continuing relationship with Dura Pharmaceuticals progresses Elan's interests in the area of pulmonary delivery. Dura's DryhalerÅ device and other pulmonary expertise together with Elan's technologies will allow us to explore improved delivery of established respiratory products as well as systemic delivery of complex macromolecules.</ul><P>
<ul><ul><b>Emisphere</ul></b><P>
This collaborative research agreement to evaluate Emisphere's proprietary technology for oral macro-molecule delivery is now entering Phase I evaluation following successful filing of the relevant IND. We believe this alliance has the potential for complimentary collaboration in combining Emisphere's technology and Elan's capability in oral macromolecule absorption.</ul><P>
<ul><ul><b>Cytogen</b></ul><P>
This agreement allows us to exploit new development technologies and techniques in the area of molecular biology. We hope to develop advanced targeting and drug delivery systems focused on specific physiological barriers and receptors that play a role in drug absorption. Cytogen's combinatorial library technology and expertise in chemistry will add to Elan's programme in the development of advanced drug delivery targeted systems.</ul><P>
<ul><ul><b>Athena	</b></ul><P>
This alliance originally allowed for the application of Elan's drug delivery technology to a range of neurological products being developed by Athena Neurosciences. Under the agreement Elan had access to exciting early stage compounds and would have worked closely with Athena in developing the optimum dosage form. In addition Elan would carry out the development and manufacturing of a specific range of products. All of these features and others described elsewhere led to our announcement in March 1996 of the acquisition of Athena and its integration into the Elan group of companies.</ul><P>
<ul><ul><b>Other Alliances</b></ul><P>
Elan has initiated the development of four solid oral dosage forms for new over-the-counter presentations for an OTC division of a major pharmaceutical company and a number of other contract development projects on existing licenced products have been initiated utilising various new delivery mechanisms.</ul><P>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><H3>Cardizem/Diltiazem</H3></ul></ul>
Once and twice-daily formulations of Diltiazem continue to show growth globally with sales of over $900 million in North America alone. This product has been approved in 21 countries and is awaiting approval in 13 others. It is showing strong growth in Japan where our partner Tanabe is now marketing a new and improved version developed by Elan. Similar product enhancements are now being assessed by all our licencees worldwide.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><H3>Verelan</H3></ul></ul>
We have recently introduced two line extensions to this product in the United States:-<P>
Verelan Sprinkle and Verelan High Dose (360 mg)<P>
We are also developing a chronotherapeutic formulation which takes advantage of natural circadian rhythms within the human body. Ambulatory blood pressure monitoring has highlighted inherent variations in blood pressure levels throughout the day. This particular profile demonstrates that blood pressure generally drops during night-time by approximately 20% and rises rapidly again in the waking hours of the morning (6a.m. to 12 noon). Elan's Verelan Chrono will be taken at night but the release rate is formulated so as to have maximum effect in the early hours of morning.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><H3>EL530/532</H3></ul></ul>
These non-cytotoxic anti-cancer drugs preferentially inhibit the growth of cancerous cells and have shown efficiency with minimal toxicity against a variety of solid tumours and leukemias in Phase II studies conducted at multiple sites by the National Cancer Institute of the USA in conjunction with Elan.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><H3>Neurelan</H3></ul></ul>
Multiple sclerosis affects more than 250,000 people in the United States. Elan has developed a controlled absorption formulation of FampridineÅ a potassium channel blocker which addresses the toxicity issues and narrow therapeutic window of the active ingredient. This is the first treatment designed to provide symptomatic relief for sufferers of multiple sclerosis and is now entering Phase III studies. Neurelan has Orphan drug status in the U.S.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><H3>Ibuscent (Ibuprofen Effervescent)</H3></ul></ul>
Ibuprofen is a proven analgesic and antipyretic with good tolerability and was one of the first NSAIDs to achieve OTC status as an analgesic. The Elan effervescent formulation ensures rapid dissolution of the dosage form and hence allows Ibuprofen to be absorbed faster than traditional dosage forms. This ensures rapid onset of analgesic effect. Elan's Ibuscent 200mg formulation is presently approved in Sweden and Norway with approval imminent in a number of other European countries. A major launch by our European licencee is planned in the coming year.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><H3>Morphelan (Morphine Once-Daily)</H3></ul></ul>
Elan has developed a once-daily morphine sulphate formulation using its proprietary SODAS technology. This multiparticulate product is designed to provide a rapid onset of action together with a sustained therapeutic effect over 24 hours. Once daily administration will improve compliance and help eliminate breakthrough pain which is a feature of many twice daily products thereby providing better quality of pain management.<P>
<BR Clear=All>
<ul><ul><H3>Naprelan</H3></ul></ul>
Our once-daily version of naproxen sodium has been launched in the United States by Wyeth-Ayerst Laboratories (a division of American Home Products). This is the first prescription product in the United States to offer once daily dosing of the popular arthritis medication NaprosynÅ together with an analgesic claim.<P>

Naprelan offers a unique combination of rapid onset of pain relief, a sustained release mechanism allowing for once daily dosing and 24 hour effectiveness. This is made possible by Elan's innovative delivery technology IPDAS (Intestinal Protective Drug Absorption System). The sustained release component of Naprelan is designed to widely disperse the sustained release micro-particles through the gastro-intestinal tract allowing for gradual absorption and thus providing a full day's duration of activity.<P>

Currently 38 million people suffer from arthritis in the United States which is one of the leading causes of work related disability. It is estimated that by the year 2020 the number of arthritis sufferers will increase to in excess of 59 million. Many arthritis sufferers frequently switch medications because of inconvenient dosing, lack of efficacy or undesirable side effects. We believe that Naprelan with the benefits of IPDAS will provide an important new option for physicians to treat patients.<P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<ul><ul><H3>IPDAS Facts</H3></ul></ul>
Chronic treatment with non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) is associated with irritation of the gastro-intestinal tract, sometimes causing bleeding, ulceration and perforation. IPDAS provides a unique delivery and dispersal profile that minimises naproxen concentration in any one area of the gastro-intestinal tract.<P>

IPDAS enables convenient once daily dosing of Naprelan by simultaneously delivering rapid onset of action and sustained release of medication over a 24 hour period. The immediate release component delivers 30% of the drug in granulate form and after ingestion this portion quickly dissolves in the gastro-intestinal tract. The extended release component consists of micro-particles coated with rate-controlling polymer membrane. These micro-particles provide an extended absorption period that prolongs therapeutic levels of the drug for 24 hours and disperses drug concentrations over a wide area of the gastro-intestinal tract to minimise local irritation.<P><P>
<P>
<h5 align=center> <a href="index.html">HOME</a>| <a  href="anrep.html"> Annual Report</h5></FONT></body>











