<head><title>Elan Corporation plc.</title></head>
<BODY BACKGROUND="images/paper1.gif" TEXT="#03056b"><p>
<a href="index.html"><img border=0 src="images/elnmain.gif" width=525 height=75 ismap usemap="index.html"></a><p>



<img src="images/quarter.gif" width=525 height=47>
<p>
<ul>
<a href="q_report.html">Elan Corporation plc., 1st Quarter Report ended June 30, 1996</a>
<br>
<a href="q_report2.html">Elan Corporation plc., 2nd Quarter Report ended September 30, 1996</a>
<br>

<p>
<br>
<br>

<b>Elan Corporation plc., 3rd Quarter Report, Fiscal '96</b>

<p>
<br>

<a href="#table">Consolidated Balance Sheet</a>

<p>
<br>

Dear Shareholders,

<p>
<br>

I am pleased to report that Elan has achieved record earnings for the quarter ended January 5, 1996. Net income for the quarter was IR£14,430,000 (US$23,088,000) and earnings per share of IR£0.38 (US$0.61) compared with net income of IR£11,246,000 and IR£0.32 in the third quarter, fiscal 1995, increases of 28 per cent and 21 per cent respectively. Net income for the nine months was IR£38,417,000 (US$61,466,000) compared to IR£30,830,000 in the comparable period in the prior year. Per share net income increased from IR£0.87 to IR£1.06 (US$1.69).

<p>
<br>

Revenue in the third quarter of fiscal 1996 increased by 14 per cent from IR£30,124,000 in fiscal 1995 to IR£34,479,000 (US$55,166,000) principally arising from the increase in revenue from royalties and fees which increased from IR£9,123,000 in fiscal 1995 to IR£16,776,000 (US$26,842,000). This reflected (i) attainment of milestone payments on existing license agreements; (ii) the signing of a number of new agreements completed in the quarter; and (iii) increased royalties including contributions from new product launches in Japan. Revenue from product sales was IR£13,244,000 (US$21,190,000) in the quarter compared to IR£13,625,000 in the comparable period in fiscal 1995. This reflected principally reduced shipments of nutrition and diagnostic products. Research revenue was IR£4,459,000 (US$7,134,000) in the quarter (including IR£3,355,000 (1994: IR£5,267,000) from Advanced Therapeutic Systems, Limited (ATS)). This reflected the timing of clinical trials on a number of ATS funded projects.

<p>
<br>

The change in the gross margin on goods and services sold from 51 per cent in the third quarter of fiscal 1995 to 32per cent in the third quarter of fiscal 1996 reflected (i) costs associated with the scale-up and manufacture of pre-launch inventory requirements of Naprelanª (including personnel recruitment, training and associated facility costs) and (ii) a higher level of activity on client sponsored development projects.
I am pleased that we recorded a 28 per cent increase in net income for the quarter while absorbing heavy scale-up costs associated with Naprelanª recently approved by the Food and Drug Administration for marketing in the United States. We also shipped our first batches of pre-launch inventory at the end of the quarter and I am also pleased to note that product sales in the quarter included a contribution from two new product launches in Japan.

<p>
<br>

I look forward to the launch later this quarter of Naprelanª by the Wyeth-Ayerst division of American Home Products which will likely result in a significant increase in product sales by Elan. The conclusion in the quarter of a research alliance with Emisphere Technologies, Inc and an extended commercial arrangement with Dura Pharmaceuticals Inc were two significant corporate events in the quarter. I look forward to 1996 with confidence that we will build from our successes in 1995. I would like to thank our shareholders and employees for their support during what has been a challenging period in the companyÕs development. I am very pleased that your confidence in Elan has enabled us to achieve good financial results and a major new product approval.

<p>
<br>
<br>
<b>

Donal Geaney<br>
President & Chief Executive Officer<br>
January 15, 1996<br>

<p>

