<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4><ul><ul><h2>Elan and Axogen Announce Completion of Public Offering of Units</h2></ul></ul><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<b>DUBLIN, IRELAND (November 20, 1996): Elan Corporation, plc (NYSE: ELN) ("ELAN") and Axogen Limited ("Axogen"), a newly formed Bermuda company, announced today the public offering of 4.6 million units at a price of $18.00 per unit.  Each unit consists of one common share of Axogen and one five-year warrant to acquire an Elan American Depositary Share.  The units have been listed on the American Stock Exchange and will trade under the symbol "AXG" until December 31, 1998.  Thereafter, the Axogen common shares and the Elan warrants will trade separately.  The warrants are exercisable at anytime from January 1, 1999 until December 31, 2001 at an exercise price of $37.54.  Elan has an exclusive option to purchase all of the issued Axogen common shares at fixed premiums over the offering price which option terminates no later than December 31, 2001.</b><P>

Merrill Lynch & Co. is managing the offering.  Axogen and Elan have granted the underwriter a 30-day over-allotment option to purchase an additional 690,000 units.  A copy of the final prospectus relating to these securities may be obtained from Merrill Lynch & Co., Prospectus Department, 250 Vesey Street, World Financial Center, North Tower, New York, New York 10281.<P>

Axogen Limited was formed in September 1996 to develop therapeutic products for the treatment of neurological disorders.  Substantially all of the proceeds of the offering and interest thereon will be used to undertake clinical testing, final product development, including regulatory approval, and commercialization of products designated under a development agreement between Axogen and Elan.  The designated products have been under development by Elan and its wholly-owned subsidiary, Athena Neurosciences, Inc.<P>

Elan Corporation, plc is a leading worldwide drug delivery and biopharmaceutical company.  Its innovative drug absorption technologies are designed to improve patient care in a cost-effective manner.  Elan's principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland, and through its subsidiaries in the United States and Israel.  Athena Neurosciences, Inc., a wholly-owned subsidiary of Elan, discovers, develops and markets products to be used primarily for the treatment and diagnosis of central nervous system diseases and disorders. <P>
