<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body background="../images/paper1.gif"><P>
<A HREF="index.html"><img border=0 SRC="../images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="index.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="../images/press.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4><ul><ul><h2>FDA Advisory Committee Recommends Approval for Elan's Diastat&reg; Product</h2></ul></ul><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<b>DUBLIN, IRELAND (November 18, 1996): Elan Corporation, plc (NYSE:ELN) ("ELAN") announced today that the Peripheral and Central Nervous System Drugs Advisory Committee ("Committee") convened by the Food and Drug Administration ("FDA") on November 15, 1996 has unanimously recommended approval of the New Drug Application ("NDA") for Diastat&reg; (diazepam rectal gel).  The NDA was submitted by Elan's wholly-owned subsidiary, Athena Neurosciences, Inc. in December 1995.</b><P>

Diastat is a proprietary gel formulation of diazepam for rectal administration and is designed for home use in the treatment of a severe epilepsy condition previously defined as acute repetitive seizures.  This condition primarily affects children and young adults, and is characterized by a predictable cluster of seizures that may lead to injury and death.  Currently these seizures are treated primarily in hospitals and home treatment will enable faster administration of the appropriate medication and the possibility of improved outcomes for lower cost.<P>

The Committee found the evidence submitted by Elan supports approval of the NDA.  At the request of the FDA the Committee recommended that certain aspects of this epilepsy condition be taken into account in arriving at the product's final labelling.  The Committee's recommendation on labelling is consistent with Elan's views on how the product should be used.<P>

While not bound by the recommendations of the Committee, the FDA often follows such recommendation in reaching its decision to approve or deny an NDA.  Under the Prescription Drug User Fee Act of 1992, an FDA response to the approvability of an NDA filing generally would be expected within a year of its submission.<P>

Elan Corporation, plc is a leading worldwide drug delivery and biopharmaceutical company.  Its innovative drug absorption technologies are designed to improve patient care in a cost-effective manner.  Elan's principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland, and through its subsidiaries in the United States and Israel.  Athena Neurosciences, Inc. a wholly-owned subsidiary of Elan, discovers, develops and markets products to be used primarily for the treatment and diagnosis of central nervous system diseases and disorders. 
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Except for historical information, the statements made in this press release contain certain forward-looking statements that involve a number of risks and uncertainties, including final FDA approval, product demand, market acceptance and pricing of Diastat, as well as the other risks detailed from time to time in the SEC reports filed by Elan, including its report on Form 20-F for the year ended March 31, 1996, as amended November 1996.</FONT><P>

