<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body background="../images/paper1.gif"><P>
<A HREF="index.html"><img border=0 SRC="../images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="index.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="../images/press.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4><ul><ul><h2>Elan Announces Revenue increase of 70% and Net Income increase of 39%</h2></ul></ul><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<b>DUBLIN, IRELAND, October 29, 1996: Elan Corporation, plc (NYSE: ELN) today announced net income for the quarter ended September 30, 1996 of $28.5m and earnings per share of $0.29, before a one-time charge, compared with net income of $20.4m and earnings per share of $0.29 in the three months ended September 30, 1995, an increase of 39% in net income. The results for the quarter reflect the acquisition of Athena Neurosciences, Inc. on July 1, 1996 and an increase in outstanding ordinary and equivalent shares of 39 per cent.</b>
<P>
<p>
The one-time charge of $484.8m on the acquisition of Athena Neurosciences, Inc. largely represents the value of the acquired in-process research related to the Athena acquisition which has been written off in the income statement in accordance with Statement of Financial Accounting Standard No.2 "Accounting for Research and Development Costs". The one-time charge includes a provision of $30m for the integration, rationalisation and repositioning of certain Elan businesses including the disposal of non-strategic interests. The acquisition of Advanced Therapeutic Systems, Limited announced in September will be completed on October 30, 1996 and the accounting adjustments arising on this acquisition will be reflected in the results for the quarter to December 31, 1996.
<p>
Total revenues for the quarter were $83.3m, an increase of 70% from $49.0m in the same quarter of the previous year. Excluding the revenue contribution from Athena, the underlying revenue growth rate was 36%. Revenue from product sales rose 78% for the quarter, largely reflecting the launch of Naprelan and the inclusion of Athena revenues for the first time, including Permax, which recorded an increase of 53% compared with the comparable quarter in the preceding year.
<p>
Research revenues were $18.2m, compared to $10.0m in the same quarter of the previous year. Research revenues included $15.4m received from Advanced Therapeutics Systems, Limited, reflecting the high level of payments for external work done on behalf of ATS in the quarter.
<p>
Royalties and fees in the quarter were $27.5m, up from $17.8m in the same quarter of the previous year. The growth in royalties of 72% reflected the inclusion of Naprelan royalties together with growth in royalties from sales of Cardizem CD and Verelan offset in part by a decline in Cardizem SR royalties. Licence and option fees reflected new agreements entered into in the quarter and milestone payments from existing agreements.
<p>
Unfunded research and development expenditure increased to $12.6m from $7.4m reflecting the inclusion of Athena research activities for the first time. Selling, general and administrative costs increased to $15.2m from $8.5m also reflecting the inclusion of Athena costs for the first time including 
the  costs of its sales and marketing activities.
<p>
Interest and other income grew by 48% to $7.7m from $5.2m reflecting primarily the higher levels of cash and cash equivalents in the balance sheet in the current quarter compared to the previous year.
<p>
The merger with Athena was completed on July 1 and the task of integrating the enlarged Elan group is now under-way. At the same time, a process of review and re-focusing of the drug delivery business is in progress to maximise the opportunities for our drug delivery technologies and to ensure that our manufacturing facilities operate at maximum efficiency. During the quarter, we announced with CYTOGEN Corporation the formation of Targon Corporation to develop and commercialise differentiated oncology products. The announcement in early September of the results of the Phase I trials for oral heparin carried out on behalf of the Emisphere-Elan join venture were encouraging. At our investor conference held in September, we also announced exciting progress in the Alzheimer's Disease research programmes where prototype compounds that reduce the protein which forms the plaques found in the brains 
of Alzheimer patients where shown to be orally active in Athena's model of Alzheimer's disease. These and other developments continue to broaden the scientific base and range of products marketed by the enlarged Elan group.
<P>
Elan Corporation, plc is a leading world-wide drug delivery company with innovative drug absorption technologies designed to improve patient care in a cost-effective manner. Its principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland and its wholly-owned subsidiaries in the United States and Israel. Athena Neurosciences, Inc., a wholly-owned subsidiary of Elan, discovers, develops and markets products to be used primarily by neurologists for the treatment and diagnosis of neurological disorders.   
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Except for the historical information contained herein, the matters discussed herein contain forward looking statements that involve risks and uncertainties which may cause the company's actual results in future periods to be materially different from any future performances suggested herein. Such factors include actual and potential competition, the timing and outcome of regulatory approvals and other risks.

<P>
