<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body background="../images/paper1.gif"><P>
<A HREF="index.html"><img border=0 SRC="../images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="index.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="../images/press.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4><ul><ul><h2>Elan Corporation and Janssen Pharmaceutica to develop once daily formulation of major Janssen Compound
</h2></ul></ul><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<b>ATHLONE, IRELAND,  October 7, 1996:  Elan Pharmaceutical Technologies, a division of Elan Corporation, plc (NYSE: ELN) today announced the development of a once daily formulation of an undisclosed major Janssen compound with Janssen Pharmaceutica, an affiliate of Johnson & Johnson.</b><P>

The parties have been working on the co-development for a number of years and have recently signed a licence agreement to regulate commercialisation of the product.  It is expected that Phase III trials will commence early next year.<P>

In commenting on the announcement Elan's President and Chief Executive Officer, Donal Geaney, stated  "we are very pleased to have the opportunity to provide drug delivery technology to Janssen and in particular to be involved with a major Janssen compound.  This agreement is another important step in helping us realise our objective of being the leading provider of drug delivery technology to the Pharmaceutical Industry".<P>

Elan Corporation, plc is a leading world-wide drug delivery and biopharmaceutical company.  Its innovative drug absorption technologies are designed to improve patient care in a cost effective manner.  Its Athena Neuroscience subsidiary discovers, develops and markets products to be used by neurologists for the treatment and diagnosis of neurological disorders.  Elan's principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland, the United States and Israel.  Elan's shares trade on the New York, London and Dublin Stock Exchanges.

<P>

<P><BR><P>
