<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body background="../images/paper1.gif"><P>
<A HREF="index.html"><img border=0 SRC="../images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="index.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="../images/press.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4><ul><ul><h2>Donald E. Panoz retires as Chairman of the Board on December 31, 1996  -  to be succeeded by Donal J. Geaney

</h2></ul></ul><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<b>Athlone, Ireland (September 30, 1996) --  Elan Corporation, plc (NYSE:  ELN) ("Elan") announced today that Donal J. Geaney, President and Chief Executive Officer of Elan has been named to the additional post of Chairman of the Board, succeeding Donald E. Panoz, effective January 1, 1997.  Mr. Panoz, who founded Elan in 1969 and retired as Chief Executive Officer in December 1994, will become Chairman Emeritus.  He also remains a non-executive director of the company. </b><P>

"Elan has reached significant milestones over the past 27 years under the vision and guidance of Donald E. Panoz" said Mr. Geaney.  "We plan to continue to grow and expand our business as we move into the 21st Century.  In achieving this, we will continue to draw upon Donald Panoz's experience and understanding of our business".<P>

Mr. Geaney, 45, joined Elan as Executive Vice President in 1987, with responsibility for strategic planning, and in 1989, he became Chief Financial Officer.  In 1992, Mr. Geaney was elected to Elan's Board of Directors and was appointed President and Chief Operating Officer.  In January 1995, Mr. Geaney became Elan's Chief Executive Officer following Donald Panoz's retirement from his executive responsibilities.<P>

"We have achieved an orderly and successful transition to our new management team and I am pleased as both a shareholder and founder of the company to entrust Elan to the very capable leadership of Donal Geaney", said Mr. Panoz.  "I am confident that Elan will continue to flourish and I look forward to its continuing success".<P>

Elan Corporation, plc is a leading world-wide drug delivery and biopharmaceutical company.  Its innovative drug absorption technologies are designed to improve patient care in a cost-effective manner. Its Athena Neurosciences subsidiary discovers, develops and markets products to be used by neurologists for the treatment and diagnosis of neurological disorders.  Elan's principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland, the United States and Israel.  Elan's shares trade on the New York, London and Dublin Stock Exchanges.
<P>

<P><BR><P>
<P><P>
