<IMG SRC="../images/press.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4><ul><ul><h2>Elan Exercises option to acquire Advanced Therapeutic Systems, Limited ("ATS")
</h2></ul></ul><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<b>Dublin, Ireland, September 10, 1996: Elan Corporation, plc (NYSE:ELN) today announced that it intends to exercise its option to acquire 100% of the outstanding stock of Advanced Therapeutic Systems, Limited (AMEX: ATH) at a price of $36.00 per share payable in cash, at a total cost to Elan of $141 million pursuant to the purchase option granted by ATS in July 1993.  The transaction will be completed before the end of October 1996.  As a result of the ATS transaction, Elan will incur a one-time charge of approximately $141 million in the quarter to September 30, 1996.</b><P>

ATS was formed in May 1993 and subsequently funded through a rights offering to Elan shareholders.  It is funding both drug delivery research using Elan¹s ETDAS, BEODAS and MIDAS technologies and new chemical entity and drug development research.<P>

Commenting on this decision, Elan's President and Chief Executive Officer, Donal Geaney, said "the decision to buy back ATS follows a detailed review of the value of the ATS portfolio and represents a major vote of confidence in the future of Elan as well as giving an excellent return to those Elan shareholders who participated in the ATS offering".<P>

Elan Corporation, plc is a leading worldwide drug delivery company with innovative drug absorption technologies designed to improve patient care in a cost-effective manner.  Athena Neurosciences, a division of Elan, discovers, develops and markets products to be used primarily by neurologists for the treatment and diagnosis of neurological disorders.  Elan's principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland, the United States and Israel.<P>

<P><BR><P>
