<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body background="../images/paper1.gif"><P>
<A HREF="index.html"><img border=0 SRC="../images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="index.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="../images/press.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4><ul><ul><h2>Elan details arrangements for the closing of the Athena merger and stock split.</h2></ul></ul><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<b>Dublin, Ireland, June 25, 1996: As a result of requests from stockholders and the financial community, Elan Corporation, plc (NYSE:ELN)  issued a statement clarifying out the remaining stages in the completion of the merger agreement with Athena Neurosciences, Inc. (Nasdaq: ATHN) and the previously announced stock split.</b><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
The Elan Extraordinary General Meeting and the Athena Special Meeting of Stockholders to approve the merger transaction between the companies will both be held on Thursday next, June 27th in Dublin and South San Francisco respectively.  Based on proxies received to date, both companies are confident that the requisite stockholder approval will be received.<P>
The merger will become effective at the time of filing of a certificate of merger with the Secretary of State of the State of Delaware.  It is intended to make this filing on Monday next, July 1st.  Once this has been done, each issued share in Athena will be converted into the right to receive 0.2956 Elan ADRs.  Transmittal forms to Athena stockholders will be sent to them on July 1st.  Signed transmittal forms should then be sent to the transfer agent, The Bank of New York, who will arrange for the new Elan share certificates to be issued.<P>
As announced on March 15th last, Elan will make a stock split, whereby holders will receive one new share for each share currently held, to holders of record on August 15th.  Such new shares will be posted on August 22nd.  Athena stockholders who have not submitted their transmittal forms before that date will participate in the stock split.<P>
Elan Corporation, plc is a leading worldwide drug delivery company with innovative drug absorption technologies designed to improve patient care in a cost-effective manner.  Its principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland, the United States and Israel.<P>
<P>
<P><P>
