<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body background="../images/paper1.gif"><P>
<A HREF="index.html"><img border=0 SRC="../images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="index.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="../images/press.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>

<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4>


 




<p>

<ul><ul><h2><b> Current Press Release</b></h2></ul></ul>


<br>
<p>

<ul><ul>

<h3>May 2, 1996
</h3>

<p>
<br>
<b>
ELAN ANNOUNCES 66 PER CENT GAIN IN FOURTH QUARTER NET INCOME AND 35 PER CENT GAIN FOR YEAR

</b>
</ul></ul>
<br>
<p>


Dublin, Ireland, May 2, 1996: Elan Corporation, plc (NYSE: ELN) today announced net income of IR£18,027,000 (US$28,338,000) or 44 pence ($.70) per share for the quarter ended March 31, 1996, an increase of 66 per cent from net income of IR£10,852,000 or 30 pence per share for the quarter ended March 31, 1995.  Total revenues for the quarter increased by 58 per cent to IR£47,117,000 ($74,068,000) for the quarter from IR£29,749,000.

<br>
<p>

Net income for the year ended March 31, 1996 rose 35 per cent to IR£56,444,000 (US$88,730,000) or IR£1.51 ($2.38) per share from IR£41,682,000 or IR£1.17 per share for the year ended March 31, 1995.  Total revenues increased by 19 per cent to IR£141,686,000 ($222,730,000) for the year from IR£118,899,000.  For fiscal 1996, operating income increased by 25 per cent.

<br>
<p>

Product sales, which include sales from contract manufacturing activities for Elans client companies and sales of Elan-marketed products, increased by 82 per cent to IR£25,662,000 ($40,341,000) for the fourth quarter of 1996, compared to IR£14,043,000 for the fourth quarter of 1995, due to initial shipments of Naprelan® CR to the Wyeth-Ayerst division of American Home Products, our marketing partner in the United States of America; Herbesser® HP (a high potency once-daily formulation of diltiazem) to Tanabe Seiyaku Co., Ltd, our marketing partner in Japan; and Theodur® Sprinkle to Mitsubishi Kasei Corporation our marketing partner in Japan.  For fiscal 1996, product sales increased by 15 per cent to IR£65,569,000 ($103,075,000).  For the fourth quarter of fiscal 1996 revenue from product sales (including royalties) comprised 70 per cent of total revenues compared with 65 per cent in the fourth quarter of fiscal 1995.

<br>
<p>

Royalties and fees for the fourth quarter of 1996 increased to IR£14,834,000 (US$23,319,000) compared to IR£12,648,000, an increase of 17 per cent.  Royalty income increased by 37 per cent over the fourth quarter of fiscal 1995, reflecting primarily increased royalties from the sales of Cardizem® CD and other marketed products in Europe and Asia.

<br>
<p>

Research and development revenues, reflecting reimbursement by client companies, increased to IR£6,621,000 (US$10,408,000) for the fourth quarter of 1996 compared to IR£3,058,000 in the fourth quarter of 1995.  Research revenue received from Advanced Therapeutic Systems, Ltd (ATS) was IR£4,709,000 ($7,403,000) for the quarter where ATS is funding the development of seven new drug delivery technologies and in excess of 15 products in varying stages of clinical development from pre-clinical through Phase III clinical trials.

<br>
<p>

Research and development expenditure, not otherwise funded by Elans clients, increased to IR£7,084,000 ($11,136,000) in the fourth quarter of fiscal 1996 compared to IR£4,966,000 in the fourth quarter of fiscal 1995.  Cost of goods and services (primarily research) sold increased to IR£19,973,000 ($31,398,000) compared to IR£9,767,000 reflecting (1) the cost associated with new product launches in the United States of America and in Japan and (2) clinical trial costs on funded research activities where milestone payments pursuant to licence agreements have yet to be met.  Selling, general and administrative costs increased by 1 per cent in the fourth quarter to IR£5,362,000 ($8,429,000).

<br>
<p>
 
Reflecting all of the above, operating income increased by 52 per cent to IR£14,698,000 ($23,105,000) in the fourth quarter of fiscal 1996 compared to IR£9,690,000 in the fourth quarter of 1995.  Reflecting essentially higher interest and similar income offset in part by a higher share of losses of associates, net income before tax for the fourth quarter of fiscal 1996 increased by 67 per cent to IR£18,073,000 ($28,410,000) compared to IR£10,834,000 in the fourth quarter of 1995.

<br>
<p>

The number of weighted average common and common share equivalent shares increased by 5 per cent over the preceding year and by 14 per cent over the comparable quarter in the preceding year reflecting the issuance of the 1990 Series warrants in November 1995 and the increase in the share price since December 1995 resulting in a higher number of common share equivalents in the calculation.

<br>
<p>

Elan expects its pending merger with Athena Neurosciences, Inc to close by June 30, 1996.

<br>
<p>

Elan Corporation, plc is a leading world-wide drug delivery company with innovative drug absorption technologies designed to improve patient care in a cost-effective manner.  Its principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland, the United States and Israel.

<br>
<p>

 Elan Corporation, plc.

<p>
