<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4><ul><ul><h2>Elan announces warrant expiration</h2></ul></ul><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<b>ATHLONE, IRELAND, November 7, 1995. Elan Corporation, plc (NYSE: ELN) today announced that pursuant to the terms of the prospectus dated November 12, 1992, the above Elan Corporation, plc. warrants expire after 5.00 p.m. on November 14, 1995. Each warrant allows the holder to purchase one Elan Corporation, plc. American Depositary Share ("ADS") at an exercise price of $15.25 .<P>
A fee of $.05 per Elan Corporation ADS issued will be charged by the Bank of New York as Depositary, for an aggregate payment of $15.30 per Elan Corporation ADS issued.</b><P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
Holders choosing to exercise their Elan Corporation Warrants must deliver the Elan Corporation Warrants and a check payable to "The Bank of New York, Ref: Elan Corporation Warrants" in the amount of $15.30 per Elan Corporation Warrant exercised so that both are received at The Bank of New York no later than 5.00 p.m. on November 14, 1995.<P>
After November 14, 1995, the warrants will no longer be exercisable.<P>
Elan is a leading worldwide drug delivery company with innovative drug absorption technologies designed to improve patient care in a cost effective manner. Its principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland and the United States of America.<P>
<b>For further information please contact:</b><br>
Bank of New York<br>
1-800-524-4458
