<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body background="../images/paper1.gif"><P>
<A HREF="index.html"><img border=0 SRC="../images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="index.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="../images/press.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4><ul><ul><h2>Elan Corporation and Ethical Holdings announce major technology collaboration</h2></ul></ul><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<b>ATHLONE, IRELAND, September 5, 1995: Elan Corporation, plc. (NYSE:ELN) today announced that it had signed a far-reaching global technology collaboration and product development agreement with Ethical Holdings plc. (NASDAQ-ETHCY).</b><P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
Under the terms of the agreement Ethical will grant Elan access to its Multipor<SUP><SMALL>TM</SMALL></SUP> oral controlled-release technology and to its patented transdermal controlled release technologies for certain products. Elan and Ethical will cooperate in development a number of oral controlled release and transdermal products. New drug delivery technologies that emerge as a result of the venture will Be the property of both companies.<P>
Elan has paid a licence fee of US$8 million to access Ethical's technology and manufacture certain of Ethical's products. In return for its contribution to the research and development programme, Ethical will also receive development stage payments, a share of licence fees and royalties of between 5% and 8% on all individual marketed products.<P>
In addition, Ethical has issued 700,000 ordinary shares to Elan at US$8.25 per share, representing a holding of approximately 5 per cent. The shares were issued at a premium of about 11 per cent to the average closing price over the preceding thirty trading days. Elan has also purchased warrants to buy an additional 950,000 shares.<P>
Access to Ethical's other oral technologies will be on a product-by-product basis. The agreement specifically excludes Ethical's development of products for use in hormone replacement therapy (HRT).<P>
The joint research and development programme will be co-ordinated by teams consisting of senior management and scientific staff from both companies. There will be a strong emphasis on new product development particularly in the oral field where both companies possess complimentary capabilities.<P>
Elan's president and chief executive officer, Donal Geaney said: "We are particularly pleased to be able to announce this innovative collaboration. Combining forces with Ethical will give Elan access to Ethical's sophisticated drug delivery systems and products and enable us to accelerate the growth of a number of our product development programmes."<P>
Dr. Geoffrey Guy, chairman and chief executive of the Ethical Group, commented: "Our collaboration with Elan, potentially one of the largest and most far-reaching agreements the company has signed to date, heralds the next important stage in the company's drive to become a global force in the drug delivery sector. We expect that the joint venture will significantly increase the market penetration of products based upon our technologies. Furthermore, the availability of Elan's production facilities will help us in planning our future manufacturing requirements."<P>
Dr. Guy added: "Elan is one of very few companies in the world with the expertise and knowledge necessary to benefit fully from Ethical's leading edge technologies. We are therefore very happy to entrust our scientific know-how to such a prestigious partner. Longer term it is our strong belief that this unique arrangement offers tremendous scope for developing entirely new drug delivery systems based upon the unrivalled research and development expertise that both companies possess."<P>
Ethical Holdings plc. is one of the world's leading specialist drug delivery groups specialising in pharmaceutical products utilising the company's proprietary drug delivery systems, including controlled release tablets and transdermal patches.<P>
Elan is a leading world wide drug delivery company with innovative drug absorption technologies designed to improve patient care in a cost effective manner. Its principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland and the United States of America.<P>
<P>
<P><P>
