<HEAD><TITLE>Elan Corporation plc</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body background="../images/paper1.gif"><P>
<A HREF="index.html"><img border=0 SRC="../images/elnmain.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=75 ISMAP USEMAP="index.html"></A><P>
<IMG SRC="../images/press.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=47><P>
<UL><FONT COLOR="03056B"><FONT SIZE=4><ul><ul><h2>Elan units will separate effective August 14, 1995</h2></ul></ul><P>
<BR Clear=All><P>
<b>ATHLONE, IRELAND, August 11, 1995 -- Elan Corporation plc. (NYSE:ELN) said that the unit (AMEX:ELN.E) issued in 1993 which consists of one Callable Common Share of Advanced Therapeutic Systems Limited ("ATS") and one Warrant to purchase an American Depositary Share ("ADS") of Elan at an exercise price of $39.26 per ADS will separate into its constituent parts on August 14, 1995. The Warrant will become exercisable on August 14, 1995 through August 12, 1998.</b><P>
<BR Clear=All>
<BR Clear=All>
The ATS Callable Common Share will trade on the American Stock Exchange under the symbol ATH. The Warrant will trade on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol ELN.A.WS.<P>
Elan is a leading world wide drug delivery company with innovative drug absorption technologies designed to improve patient care in a cost effective manner. Its principal research and manufacturing facilities are in Ireland and the United States of America.<P>
<P><P>
<P>
