<HEAD>

<TITLE>Directors' Report</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<body background="images/paper1.gif" text="#03056b"><p>
<a href="index.html"><img border=0 src="images/elnmain.gif" width=525 height=75 ismap usemap="index.html"></a><p>
<p>
<img src="images/finstat.gif" width=525 height=47>

<ul>
<ul><ul><h2>Directors' Report</h2></ul></ul>

<P>
The Directors have pleasure in submitting their annual report
together with the audited financial statements of the Company
for the year ended 31 March, 1996.
<ul><ul><h3>Review of the Development of the Business</h3></ul></ul>

<P>
Elan (together with its subsidiaries the "Company")
is a diversified healthcare company which develops, manufactures
and distributes pharmaceutical, diagnostic and medical nutrition
products.
<P>
A review of the development of the business of the Company and
its affiliates during the year, the background to its results
and of its position at 31 March, 1996 is set out on pages 20 to
23 of this report.
<ul><ul><h3>Future Developments and Post Balance Sheet Events</h3></ul></ul>

<P>
The Company expects future growth in revenues from its 20 products
marketed in 44 countries, which include Cardizem CD, Verelan,
Naprelan and Prostep&#153; in the United States of America. Regulatory
approval is being actively pursued for 12 products in the US and
other major markets. The Directors believe that these products
will ensure continued long-term growth for the Company. 
<P>
The Company announced on 18 March, 1996 that it had entered into
a definitive merger agreement whereby Athena Neurosciences, Inc.
will become a wholly owned subsidiary of the Company. The merger
which is subject to the approval of the shareholders of Elan and
Athena Neurosciences, Inc. is expected to be completed by the
early summer, 1996.
<P>
On 28 March, 1996, Elan advanced a short term interest bearing
loan of IR&#163;91,669,000 to a subsidiary of Nal&eacute; Laboratories,
plc, an associated undertaking, as a bridging loan facility, pending
finalisation of financing for the acquisition of certain assets
of Warner Chilcott, a division of the Warner-Lambert Company.
This loan was repaid in full on 26 April, 1996. As part of the
funding or this acquisition Nal&eacute; offered, via a private
placement, 69,000 units at US$1,400 per unit. A subsidiary of
Elan, purchased 26.6% of the units at a total cost of US$25,696,000.
A second subsidiary of Elan committed to purchase any unsubscribed
units. At 30 April, 1996 that subsidiary held 24,130 units with
a total cost of US$33,782,000 and such units are expected to be
disposed of in the immediate future.
<P>
On 15 March, 1996 the board of directors approved a two for one
share split subject to approval at the annual general meeting
of shareholders, a change in the Company's fiscal year
end to 31 December from 31 March and a change in reporting currency
from the Irish Pound to the United States Dollar.
<ul><ul><h3>Research and Development</h3></ul></ul>

<P>
During fiscal 1996, the Company's expenditure on research
and development not otherwise funded by partners amounted to IR&#163;20,311,000
(1995:IR&#163;17,663,000), reflecting the continued commitment
of the Company to developing its technologies and products.
<ul><ul><h3>Results and Dividends</h3></ul></ul>

<P>
The results for the financial year are set out on page 25 of this
report. The directors do not propose the payment of a dividend.
<P>
<br>

<ul><ul>
<h3>Safety Statement</h3>
</ul></ul>
<P>
The Company operates a safety policy set out in its Safety Statement.
In the opinion of the directors, the policy set out therein has
been complied with and is operating satisfactorily.
<ul><ul><h3>Directors</h3></ul></ul>

<P>
In accordance with the Articles of Association, Dr. Howard C.
Ansel, Dr. Garo Armen and Mr. Brendan Boushel retire, and being
eligible, offer themselves for re-election. Mr. David R. Bethune
was appointed to the board on 6 July, 1995. Mr. Laurence G. Crowley
was appointed to the board on 15 February, 1996. Dr. Alan R. Gillespie
and the Honourable Richard Thornburgh were appointed to the board
on 14 March, 1996. Mr. Bethune, Mr. Crowley, Dr. Gillespie and
the Hon. Mr. Thornburgh retire and offer themselves for election.
<ul><ul><h3>Directors' Interests</h3></ul></ul>

<P>
The beneficial interests of the directors of Elan, their spouses
and children under eighteen years of age at 31 March, 1995, 31
March, 1996 and 30 April, 1996 in the Ordinary Shares of the Company
are as follows:
<P>
  
