<TITLE>Phi Alpha Delta</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="whtmarb.gif">
<CENTER>
<H1>PHI   ALPHA   DELTA</H1><IMG SRC="pad.gif"></CENTER>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<H3>Upcoming Activities:</H3>
</CENTER>
<P><STRONG>October 25, 1996</STRONG> <BR>2nd Annual Halloween Party <BR>Location
and time to be announced. <BR>Free prizes, food &amp; beer for all D.C.L.
students. <BR>Tickets will be on sale soon.</P>
<P>You can contact one of the current officers of the D.C.L. P.A.D. Chapter:</P>
<DL>
<DD>Justice Sepideh Behram  (<A HREF="mailto:magnum39@mail.alliance.net">Internet
id: magnum39@mail.alliance.net</A>)</DD>
<DD>Vice Justice Molly Zappitell</DD>
<DD>Clerk Erin Blake</DD>
<DD>Treasurer Janet Wyatt  (<A HREF="mailto:jwyatt1217@aol.com">Internet id:
jwyatt1217@aol.com</A>)</DD>
<DD>Marshall Mark Awada</DD></DL>
<P></P>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<H3>Tangible Benefits of P.A.D.</H3></CENTER>
<P>Members and potential members of <B>Phi Alpha Delta</B> often ask what
tangible benefits will come their way through membership in our Fraternity.</P>
<P><B>International Organization</B>: <B>P.A.D</B>. has chartered 173
chapters in ABA accredited law schools throughout the United States, Canada,
Puerto Rico and Mexico.<B>  P.A.D.</B> Pre-law Chapters are chartered at over
130 undergraduate campuses in the United States and Puerto Rico.  <B>P.A.D.</B>
alumni chapters throughout North America</P>
<P><B>Leadership Development</B>: <B>P.A.D.</B> encourages student leaders to
discover and develop such important skills as leadership, public speaking,
public relations and working with people through the coordination of <B>P.A.D.</B>
programs with students, faculty, attorneys, and judges.  <B>P.A.D. </B>fosters
professional competence which benefits the legal community and the community as
a whole.</P>
<P><B>First Year Survival Material</B>: <B>P.A.D.</B> provides each of its
law school chapters with a supply of first year study aids.  These first year
aids include: Gilbert's &quot;First Year Survival Manuals&quot;; West's &quot;Study
Guides&quot;; &quot;How to Brief a Case&quot;; and &quot;How to Write a Resume&quot;.
 In addition, there are some course outlines available from current members.</P>
<P><B>Alumni Contacts</B>: <B>P.A.D.</B> students and alumni can meet other
members in their community and worldwide to obtain different perspectives on the
law, make business contacts and answer questions regarding legal careers.</P>
<P><B>Job Preparation</B>: <B>P.A.D.</B> can help law school members learn
how to prepare resumes, interview for job opportunities, obtain permanent and
summer positions, and learn other skills incident to preparing for a career in
law.</P>
<P>**Created October 1996 by Justice Sepideh Behram</P></BODY></HTML>
